function GetLifeData(){return Life.data}var Life={data:[{lessontitle:"Afraid",lessonscriptures:"Isaiah\\43:1-5;Mark\\4:35-41",id:"1",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\43:1-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  But now thus says Yahweh who created you, Jacob, and he who formed you, Israel: Don't be afraid, for I have redeemed you. I have called you by your name. You are mine.\r {BR}2  When you pass through the waters, I will be with you; and through the rivers, they will not overflow you. When you walk through the fire, you will not be burned, and flame will not scorch you.\r {BR}3  For I am Yahweh your God, the Holy One of Israel, your Savior. I have given Egypt as your ransom, Ethiopia and Seba in your place.\r {BR}4  Since you have been precious and honored in my sight, and I have loved you; therefore I will give people in your place, and nations instead of your life.\r {BR}5  Don't be afraid; for I am with you. I will bring your seed from the east, and gather you from the west.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Mark\\4:35-41{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}35  On that day, when evening had come, he said to them, {I}{B}Let's go over to the other side.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}36  Leaving the multitude, they took him with them, even as he was, in the boat. Other small boats were also with him.\r {BR}37  A big wind storm arose, and the waves beat into the boat, so much that the boat was already filled.\r {BR}38  He himself was in the stern, asleep on the cushion, and they woke him up, and told him, Teacher, don't you care that we are dying?\r {BR}39  He awoke, and rebuked the wind, and said to the sea, {I}{B}Peace! Be still!{/B}{/I} The wind ceased, and there was a great calm.\r {BR}40  He said to them, {I}{B}Why are you so afraid? How is it that you have no faith?{/B}{/I}\r {BR}41  They were greatly afraid, and said to one another, Who then is this, that even the wind and the sea obey him?\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Anxious",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\46:1-11;James\\5:7-11",id:"2",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\46:1-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  God is our refuge and strength, a very present help in trouble.\r {BR}2  Therefore we won't be afraid, though the earth changes, though the mountains are shaken into the heart of the seas;\r {BR}3  though its waters roar and are troubled, though the mountains tremble with their swelling. Selah.\r {BR}4  There is a river, the streams of which make the city of God glad, the holy place of the tents of the Most High.\r {BR}5  God is in her midst. She shall not be moved. God will help her at dawn.\r {BR}6  The nations raged. The kingdoms were moved. He lifted his voice, and the earth melted.\r {BR}7  Yahweh of Armies is with us. The God of Jacob is our refuge. Selah.\r {BR}8  Come, see Yahweh's works, what desolations he has made in the earth.\r {BR}9  He makes wars cease to the end of the earth. He breaks the bow, and shatters the spear. He burns the chariots in the fire.\r {BR}10  Be still, and know that I am God. I will be exalted among the nations. I will be exalted in the earth.\r {BR}11  Yahweh of Armies is with us. The God of Jacob is our refuge. Selah.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\5:7-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Be patient therefore, brothers, until the coming of the Lord. Behold, the farmer waits for the precious fruit of the earth, being patient over it, until it receives the early and late rain.\r {BR}8  You also be patient. Establish your hearts, for the coming of the Lord is at hand.\r {BR}9  Don't grumble, brothers, against one another, so that you won't be judged. Behold, the judge stands at the door.\r {BR}10  Take, brothers, for an example of suffering and of patience, the prophets who spoke in the name of the Lord.\r {BR}11  Behold, we call them blessed who endured. You have heard of the patience of Job, and have seen the Lord in the outcome, and how the Lord is full of compassion and mercy.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Bereaved",lessonscriptures:"2 Corinthians\\4:16-18;2 Corinthians\\5:5-5;John\\14:1-31",id:"3",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\4:16-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  Therefore we don't faint, but though our outward man is decaying, yet our inward man is renewed day by day.\r {BR}17  For our light affliction, which is for the moment, works for us more and more exceedingly an eternal weight of glory;\r {BR}18  while we don't look at the things which are seen, but at the things which are not seen. For the things which are seen are temporal, but the things which are not seen are eternal.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\5:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Now he who made us for this very thing is God, who also gave to us the down payment of the Spirit.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\14:1-31{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  {I}{B}Don't let your heart be troubled. Believe in God. Believe also in me.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}2  {I}{B}In my Father's house are many homes. If it weren't so, I would have told you. I am going to prepare a place for you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}3  {I}{B}If I go and prepare a place for you, I will come again, and will receive you to myself; that where I am, you may be there also.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}4  {I}{B}Where I go, you know, and you know the way.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}5  Thomas said to him, Lord, we don't know where you are going. How can we know the way?\r {BR}6  Jesus said to him, {I}{B}I am the way, the truth, and the life. No one comes to the Father, except through me.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}7  {I}{B}If you had known me, you would have known my Father also. From now on, you know him, and have seen him.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}8  Philip said to him, Lord, show us the Father, and that will be enough for us.\r {BR}9  Jesus said to him, {I}{B}Have I been with you such a long time, and do you not know me, Philip? He who has seen me has seen the Father. How do you say, 'Show us the Father?'{/B}{/I}\r {BR}10  {I}{B}Don't you believe that I am in the Father, and the Father in me? The words that I tell you, I speak not from myself; but the Father who lives in me does his works.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}11  {I}{B}Believe me that I am in the Father, and the Father in me; or else believe me for the very works' sake.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}12  {I}{B}Most certainly I tell you, he who believes in me, the works that I do, he will do also; and he will do greater works than these, because I am going to my Father.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}13  {I}{B}Whatever you will ask in my name, that will I do, that the Father may be glorified in the Son.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}14  {I}{B}If you will ask anything in my name, I will do it.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}15  {I}{B}If you love me, keep my commandments.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}16  {I}{B}I will pray to the Father, and he will give you another Counselor, that he may be with you forever,-{/B}{/I}\r {BR}17  {I}{B}the Spirit of truth, whom the world can't receive; for it doesn't see him, neither knows him. You know him, for he lives with you, and will be in you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}18  {I}{B}I will not leave you orphans. I will come to you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}19  {I}{B}Yet a little while, and the world will see me no more; but you will see me. Because I live, you will live also.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}20  {I}{B}In that day you will know that I am in my Father, and you in me, and I in you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}21  {I}{B}One who has my commandments, and keeps them, that person is one who loves me. One who loves me will be loved by my Father, and I will love him, and will reveal myself to him.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}22  Judas (not Iscariot) said to him, Lord, what has happened that you are about to reveal yourself to us, and not to the world?\r {BR}23  Jesus answered him, {I}{B}If a man loves me, he will keep my word. My Father will love him, and we will come to him, and make our home with him.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}24  {I}{B}He who doesn't love me doesn't keep my words. The word which you hear isn't mine, but the Father's who sent me.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}25  {I}{B}I have said these things to you, while still living with you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}26  {I}{B}But the Counselor, the Holy Spirit, whom the Father will send in my name, he will teach you all things, and will remind you of all that I said to you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}27  {I}{B}Peace I leave with you. My peace I give to you; not as the world gives, give I to you. Don't let your heart be troubled, neither let it be fearful.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}28  {I}{B}You heard how I told you, 'I go away, and I come to you.' If you loved me, you would have rejoiced, because I said 'I am going to my Father;' for the Father is greater than I.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}29  {I}{B}Now I have told you before it happens so that, when it happens, you may believe.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}30  {I}{B}I will no more speak much with you, for the prince of the world comes, and he has nothing in me.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}31  {I}{B}But that the world may know that I love the Father, and as the Father commanded me, even so I do. Arise, let us go from here.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Depressed",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\37:1-9;Romans\\8:28-39",id:"4",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\37:1-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Don't fret because of evildoers, neither be envious against those who work unrighteousness.\r {BR}2  For they shall soon be cut down like the grass, and wither like the green herb.\r {BR}3  Trust in Yahweh, and do good. Dwell in the land, and enjoy safe pasture.\r {BR}4  Also delight yourself in Yahweh, and he will give you the desires of your heart.\r {BR}5  Commit your way to Yahweh. Trust also in him, and he will do this:\r {BR}6  he will make your righteousness go forth as the light, and your justice as the noon day sun.\r {BR}7  Rest in Yahweh, and wait patiently for him. Don't fret because of him who prospers in his way, because of the man who makes wicked plots happen.\r {BR}8  Cease from anger, and forsake wrath. Don't fret, it leads only to evildoing.\r {BR}9  For evildoers shall be cut off, but those who wait for Yahweh shall inherit the land.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\8:28-39{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  We know that all things work together for good for those who love God, to those who are called according to his purpose.\r {BR}29  For whom he foreknew, he also predestined to be conformed to the image of his Son, that he might be the firstborn among many brothers.\r {BR}30  Whom he predestined, those he also called. Whom he called, those he also justified. Whom he justified, those he also glorified.\r {BR}31  What then shall we say about these things? If God is for us, who can be against us?\r {BR}32  He who didn't spare his own Son, but delivered him up for us all, how would he not also with him freely give us all things?\r {BR}33  Who could bring a charge against God's chosen ones? It is God who justifies.\r {BR}34  Who is he who condemns? It is Christ who died, yes rather, who was raised from the dead, who is at the right hand of God, who also makes intercession for us.\r {BR}35  Who shall separate us from the love of Christ? Could oppression, or anguish, or persecution, or famine, or nakedness, or peril, or sword?\r {BR}36  Even as it is written, For your sake we are killed all day long. We were accounted as sheep for the slaughter.\r {BR}37  No, in all these things, we are more than conquerors through him who loved us.\r {BR}38  For I am persuaded, that neither death, nor life, nor angels, nor principalities, nor things present, nor things to come, nor powers,\r {BR}39  nor height, nor depth, nor any other created thing, will be able to separate us from the love of God, which is in Christ Jesus our Lord.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Doubting Your Faith",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\30:5-5;John\\20:24-29",id:"5",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\30:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Every word of God is flawless. He is a shield to those who take refuge in him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\20:24-29{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  But Thomas, one of the twelve, called Didymus, wasn't with them when Jesus came.\r {BR}25  The other disciples therefore said to him, We have seen the Lord! But he said to them, Unless I see in his hands the print of the nails, and put my hand into his side, I will not believe.\r {BR}26  After eight days again his disciples were inside, and Thomas was with them. Jesus came, the doors being locked, and stood in the midst, and said, {I}{B}Peace be to you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}27  Then he said to Thomas, {I}{B}Reach here your finger, and see my hands. Reach here your hand, and put it into my side. Don't be unbelieving, but believing.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}28  Thomas answered him, My Lord and my God!\r {BR}29  Jesus said to him, {I}{B}Because you have seen me, you have believed. Blessed are those who have not seen, and have believed.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Ill Or In Pain",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\6:1-10;2 Corinthians\\12:7-10",id:"6",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\6:1-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Yahweh, don't rebuke me in your anger, neither discipline me in your wrath.\r {BR}2  Have mercy on me, Yahweh, for I am faint. Yahweh, heal me, for my bones are troubled.\r {BR}3  My soul is also in great anguish. But you, Yahweh--how long?\r {BR}4  Return, Yahweh. Deliver my soul, and save me for your loving kindness' sake.\r {BR}5  For in death there is no memory of you. In Sheol, who shall give you thanks?\r {BR}6  I am weary with my groaning. Every night I flood my bed. I drench my couch with my tears.\r {BR}7  My eye wastes away because of grief. It grows old because of all my adversaries.\r {BR}8  Depart from me, all you workers of iniquity, for Yahweh has heard the voice of my weeping.\r {BR}9  Yahweh has heard my supplication. Yahweh accepts my prayer.\r {BR}10  May all my enemies be ashamed and dismayed. They shall turn back, they shall be disgraced suddenly.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\12:7-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  By reason of the exceeding greatness of the revelations, that I should not be exalted excessively, there was given to me a thorn in the flesh, a messenger of Satan to torment me, that I should not be exalted excessively.\r {BR}8  Concerning this thing, I begged the Lord three times that it might depart from me.\r {BR}9  He has said to me, My grace is sufficient for you, for my power is made perfect in weakness. Most gladly therefore I will rather glory in my weaknesses, that the power of Christ may rest on me.\r {BR}10  Therefore I take pleasure in weaknesses, in injuries, in necessities, in persecutions, in distresses, for Christ's sake. For when I am weak, then am I strong.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Lonely",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\22:1-31;Psalms\\42:1-11;John\\14:15-21",id:"7",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\22:1-31{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  My God, my God, why have you forsaken me? Why are you so far from helping me, and from the words of my groaning?\r {BR}2  My God, I cry in the daytime, but you don't answer; in the night season, and am not silent.\r {BR}3  But you are holy, you who inhabit the praises of Israel.\r {BR}4  Our fathers trusted in you. They trusted, and you delivered them.\r {BR}5  They cried to you, and were delivered. They trusted in you, and were not disappointed.\r {BR}6  But I am a worm, and no man; a reproach of men, and despised by the people.\r {BR}7  All those who see me mock me. They insult me with their lips. They shake their heads, saying,\r {BR}8  He trusts in Yahweh; let him deliver him. Let him rescue him, since he delights in him.\r {BR}9  But you brought me out of the womb. You made me trust at my mother's breasts.\r {BR}10  I was thrown on you from my mother's womb. You are my God since my mother bore me.\r {BR}11  Don't be far from me, for trouble is near. For there is none to help.\r {BR}12  Many bulls have surrounded me. Strong bulls of Bashan have encircled me.\r {BR}13  They open their mouths wide against me, lions tearing prey and roaring.\r {BR}14  I am poured out like water. All my bones are out of joint. My heart is like wax; it is melted within me.\r {BR}15  My strength is dried up like a potsherd. My tongue sticks to the roof of my mouth. You have brought me into the dust of death.\r {BR}16  For dogs have surrounded me. A company of evildoers have enclosed me. They have pierced my hands and feet.\r {BR}17  I can count all of my bones. They look and stare at me.\r {BR}18  They divide my garments among them. They cast lots for my clothing.\r {BR}19  But don't be far off, Yahweh. You are my help: hurry to help me.\r {BR}20  Deliver my soul from the sword, my precious life from the power of the dog.\r {BR}21  Save me from the lion's mouth! Yes, from the horns of the wild oxen, you have answered me.\r {BR}22  I will declare your name to my brothers. In the midst of the assembly, I will praise you.\r {BR}23  You who fear Yahweh, praise him! All you descendants of Jacob, glorify him! Stand in awe of him, all you descendants of Israel!\r {BR}24  For he has not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the afflicted, Neither has he hidden his face from him; but when he cried to him, he heard.\r {BR}25  Of you comes my praise in the great assembly. I will pay my vows before those who fear him.\r {BR}26  The humble shall eat and be satisfied. They shall praise Yahweh who seek after him. Let your hearts live forever.\r {BR}27  All the ends of the earth shall remember and turn to Yahweh. All the relatives of the nations shall worship before you.\r {BR}28  For the kingdom is Yahweh's. He is the ruler over the nations.\r {BR}29  All the rich ones of the earth shall eat and worship. All those who go down to the dust shall bow before him, even he who can't keep his soul alive.\r {BR}30  Posterity shall serve him. Future generations shall be told about the Lord.\r {BR}31  They shall come and shall declare his righteousness to a people that shall be born, for he has done it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\42:1-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  As the deer pants for the water brooks, so my soul pants after you, God.\r {BR}2  My soul thirsts for God, for the living God. When shall I come and appear before God?\r {BR}3  My tears have been my food day and night, while they continually ask me, Where is your God?\r {BR}4  These things I remember, and pour out my soul within me, how I used to go with the crowd, and led them to the house of God, with the voice of joy and praise, a multitude keeping a holy day.\r {BR}5  Why are you in despair, my soul? Why are you disturbed within me? Hope in God! For I shall still praise him for the saving help of his presence.\r {BR}6  My God, my soul is in despair within me. Therefore I remember you from the land of the Jordan, the heights of Hermon, from the hill Mizar.\r {BR}7  Deep calls to deep at the noise of your waterfalls. All your waves and your billows have swept over me.\r {BR}8  Yahweh will command his loving kindness in the daytime. In the night his song shall be with me: a prayer to the God of my life.\r {BR}9  I will ask God, my rock, Why have you forgotten me? Why do I go mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?\r {BR}10  As with a sword in my bones, my adversaries reproach me, while they continually ask me, Where is your God?\r {BR}11  Why are you in despair, my soul? Why are you disturbed within me? Hope in God! For I shall still praise him, the saving help of my countenance, and my God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\14:15-21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  {I}{B}If you love me, keep my commandments.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}16  {I}{B}I will pray to the Father, and he will give you another Counselor, that he may be with you forever,-{/B}{/I}\r {BR}17  {I}{B}the Spirit of truth, whom the world can't receive; for it doesn't see him, neither knows him. You know him, for he lives with you, and will be in you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}18  {I}{B}I will not leave you orphans. I will come to you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}19  {I}{B}Yet a little while, and the world will see me no more; but you will see me. Because I live, you will live also.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}20  {I}{B}In that day you will know that I am in my Father, and you in me, and I in you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}21  {I}{B}One who has my commandments, and keeps them, that person is one who loves me. One who loves me will be loved by my Father, and I will love him, and will reveal myself to him.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Needing Assurance",lessonscriptures:"Isaiah\\41:1-20;1 John\\3:1-3",id:"8",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\41:1-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Keep silent before me, islands, and let the peoples renew their strength. Let them come near, then let them speak. Let's meet together for judgment.\r {BR}2  Who has raised up one from the east? Whom called him to his foot in righteousness? He hands over nations to him, and makes him rule over kings. He gives them like the dust to his sword, like the driven stubble to his bow.\r {BR}3  He pursues them, and passes by safely, Even by a way that he had not gone with his feet.\r {BR}4  Who has worked and done it, calling the generations from the beginning? I, Yahweh, the first, and with the last, I am he.\r {BR}5  The islands have seen, and fear. The ends of the earth tremble. They approach, and come.\r {BR}6  Everyone helps his neighbor. They say to their brothers, Be strong!\r {BR}7  So the carpenter encourages the goldsmith. He who smoothes with the hammer encourages him who strikes the anvil, saying of the soldering, It is good; and he fastens it with nails, that it might not totter.\r {BR}8  But you, Israel, my servant, Jacob whom I have chosen, the seed of Abraham my friend,\r {BR}9  You whom I have taken hold of from the ends of the earth, and called from its corners, and said to you, 'You are my servant, I have chosen you and not cast you away;'\r {BR}10  Don't you be afraid, for I am with you. Don't be dismayed, for I am your God. I will strengthen you. Yes, I will help you. Yes, I will uphold you with the right hand of my righteousness.\r {BR}11  Behold, all those who are incensed against you will be disappointed and confounded. Those who strive with you will be like nothing, and shall perish.\r {BR}12  You will seek them, and won't find them, even those who contend with you. Those who war against you will be as nothing, as a non-existent thing.\r {BR}13  For I, Yahweh your God, will hold your right hand, saying to you, 'Don't be afraid. I will help you.'\r {BR}14  Don't be afraid, you worm Jacob, and you men of Israel. I will help you, says Yahweh, and your Redeemer is the Holy One of Israel.\r {BR}15  Behold, I have made you into a new sharp threshing instrument with teeth. You will thresh the mountains, and beat them small, and will make the hills like chaff.\r {BR}16  You will winnow them, and the wind will carry them away, and the whirlwind will scatter them. You will rejoice in Yahweh. You will glory in the Holy One of Israel.\r {BR}17  The poor and needy seek water, and there is none. Their tongue fails for thirst. I, Yahweh, will answer them. I, the God of Israel, will not forsake them.\r {BR}18  I will open rivers on the bare heights, and springs in the midst of the valleys. I will make the wilderness a pool of water, and the dry land springs of water.\r {BR}19  I will put cedar, acacia, myrtle, and oil trees in the wilderness. I will set fir trees, pine, and box trees together in the desert;\r {BR}20  that they may see, know, consider, and understand together, that the hand of Yahweh has done this, and the Holy One of Israel has created it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\3:1-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Behold, how great a love the Father has bestowed on us, that we should be called children of God! For this cause the world doesn't know us, because it didn't know him.\r {BR}2  Beloved, now we are children of God, and it is not yet revealed what we will be. But we know that, when he is revealed, we will be like him; for we will see him just as he is.\r {BR}3  Everyone who has this hope set on him purifies himself, even as he is pure.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Needing Encouragement",lessonscriptures:"Romans\\15:1-6;Hebrews\\12:1-3",id:"9",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\15:1-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Now we who are strong ought to bear the weaknesses of the weak, and not to please ourselves.\r {BR}2  Let each one of us please his neighbor for that which is good, to be building him up.\r {BR}3  For even Christ didn't please himself. But, as it is written, The reproaches of those who reproached you fell on me.\r {BR}4  For whatever things were written before were written for our learning, that through patience and through encouragement of the Scriptures we might have hope.\r {BR}5  Now the God of patience and of encouragement grant you to be of the same mind one with another according to Christ Jesus,\r {BR}6  that with one accord you may with one mouth glorify the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\12:1-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Therefore let us also, seeing we are surrounded by so great a cloud of witnesses, lay aside every weight and the sin which so easily entangles us, and let us run with patience the race that is set before us,\r {BR}2  looking to Jesus, the author and perfecter of faith, who for the joy that was set before him endured the cross, despising its shame, and has sat down at the right hand of the throne of God.\r {BR}3  For consider him who has endured such contradiction of sinners against himself, that you don't grow weary, fainting in your souls.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Needing Forgiveness",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\51:1-19;1 John\\1:8-8;1 John\\2:2-2",id:"10",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\51:1-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Have mercy on me, God, according to your loving kindness. According to the multitude of your tender mercies, blot out my transgressions.\r {BR}2  Wash me thoroughly from my iniquity. Cleanse me from my sin.\r {BR}3  For I know my transgressions. My sin is constantly before me.\r {BR}4  Against you, and you only, have I sinned, and done that which is evil in your sight; that you may be proved right when you speak, and justified when you judge.\r {BR}5  Behold, I was brought forth in iniquity. In sin my mother conceived me.\r {BR}6  Behold, you desire truth in the inward parts. You teach me wisdom in the inmost place.\r {BR}7  Purify me with hyssop, and I will be clean. Wash me, and I will be whiter than snow.\r {BR}8  Let me hear joy and gladness, That the bones which you have broken may rejoice.\r {BR}9  Hide your face from my sins, and blot out all of my iniquities.\r {BR}10  Create in me a clean heart, O God. Renew a right spirit within me.\r {BR}11  Don't throw me from your presence, and don't take your holy Spirit from me.\r {BR}12  Restore to me the joy of your salvation. Uphold me with a willing spirit.\r {BR}13  Then I will teach transgressors your ways. Sinners shall be converted to you.\r {BR}14  Deliver me from bloodguiltiness, O God, the God of my salvation. My tongue shall sing aloud of your righteousness.\r {BR}15  Lord, open my lips. My mouth shall declare your praise.\r {BR}16  For you don't delight in sacrifice, or else I would give it. You have no pleasure in burnt offering.\r {BR}17  The sacrifices of God are a broken spirit. A broken and contrite heart, O God, you will not despise.\r {BR}18  Do well in your good pleasure to Zion. Build the walls of Jerusalem.\r {BR}19  Then you will delight in the sacrifices of righteousness, in burnt offerings and in whole burnt offerings. Then they will offer bulls on your altar.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\1:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  If we say that we have no sin, we deceive ourselves, and the truth is not in us.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\2:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  And he is the atoning sacrifice for our sins, and not for ours only, but also for the whole world.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Needing Guidance",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\32:8-10;Proverbs\\3:1-35",id:"11",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\32:8-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  I will instruct you and teach you in the way which you shall go. I will counsel you with my eye on you.\r {BR}9  Don't be like the horse, or like the mule, which have no understanding, who are controlled by bit and bridle, or else they will not come near to you.\r {BR}10  Many sorrows come to the wicked, but loving kindness shall surround him who trusts in Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:1-35{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  My son, don't forget my teaching; but let your heart keep my commandments:\r {BR}2  for length of days, and years of life, and peace, will they add to you.\r {BR}3  Don't let kindness and truth forsake you. Bind them around your neck. Write them on the tablet of your heart.\r {BR}4  So you will find favor, and good understanding in the sight of God and man.\r {BR}5  Trust in Yahweh with all your heart, and don't lean on your own understanding.\r {BR}6  In all your ways acknowledge him, and he will make your paths straight.\r {BR}7  Don't be wise in your own eyes. Fear Yahweh, and depart from evil.\r {BR}8  It will be health to your body, and nourishment to your bones.\r {BR}9  Honor Yahweh with your substance, with the first fruits of all your increase:\r {BR}10  so your barns will be filled with plenty, and your vats will overflow with new wine.\r {BR}11  My son, don't despise Yahweh's discipline, neither be weary of his reproof:\r {BR}12  for whom Yahweh loves, he reproves; even as a father reproves the son in whom he delights.\r {BR}13  Happy is the man who finds wisdom, the man who gets understanding.\r {BR}14  For her good profit is better than getting silver, and her return is better than fine gold.\r {BR}15  She is more precious than rubies. None of the things you can desire are to be compared to her.\r {BR}16  Length of days is in her right hand. In her left hand are riches and honor.\r {BR}17  Her ways are ways of pleasantness. All her paths are peace.\r {BR}18  She is a tree of life to those who lay hold of her. Happy is everyone who retains her.\r {BR}19  By wisdom Yahweh founded the earth. By understanding, he established the heavens.\r {BR}20  By his knowledge, the depths were broken up, and the skies drop down the dew.\r {BR}21  My son, let them not depart from your eyes. Keep sound wisdom and discretion:\r {BR}22  so they will be life to your soul, and grace for your neck.\r {BR}23  Then you shall walk in your way securely. Your foot won't stumble.\r {BR}24  When you lie down, you will not be afraid. Yes, you will lie down, and your sleep will be sweet.\r {BR}25  Don't be afraid of sudden fear, neither of the desolation of the wicked, when it comes:\r {BR}26  for Yahweh will be your confidence, and will keep your foot from being taken.\r {BR}27  Don't withhold good from those to whom it is due, when it is in the power of your hand to do it.\r {BR}28  Don't say to your neighbor, Go, and come again; tomorrow I will give it to you, when you have it by you.\r {BR}29  Don't devise evil against your neighbor, seeing he dwells securely by you.\r {BR}30  Don't strive with a man without cause, if he has done you no harm.\r {BR}31  Don't envy the man of violence. Choose none of his ways.\r {BR}32  For the perverse is an abomination to Yahweh, but his friendship is with the upright.\r {BR}33  Yahweh's curse is in the house of the wicked, but he blesses the habitation of the righteous.\r {BR}34  Surely he mocks the mockers, but he gives grace to the humble.\r {BR}35  The wise will inherit glory, but shame will be the promotion of fools.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Needing Peace",lessonscriptures:"Isaiah\\26:1-9;Philippians\\4:4-9",id:"12",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\26:1-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  In that day, this song will be sung in the land of Judah: We have a strong city. God appoints salvation for walls and bulwarks.\r {BR}2  Open the gates, that the righteous nation may enter: the one which keeps faith.\r {BR}3  You will keep whoever's mind is steadfast in perfect peace, because he trusts in you.\r {BR}4  Trust in Yahweh forever; for in Yah, Yahweh, is an everlasting Rock.\r {BR}5  For he has brought down those who dwell on high, the lofty city. He lays it low. He lays it low even to the ground. He brings it even to the dust.\r {BR}6  The foot shall tread it down; Even the feet of the poor, and the steps of the needy.\r {BR}7  The way of the just is uprightness. You who are upright make the path of the righteous level.\r {BR}8  Yes, in the way of your judgments, Yahweh, have we waited for you. Your name and your renown are the desire of our soul.\r {BR}9  With my soul have I desired you in the night. Yes, with my spirit within me will I seek you earnestly; for when your judgments are in the earth, the inhabitants of the world learn righteousness.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\4:4-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  Rejoice in the Lord always! Again I will say, Rejoice!\r {BR}5  Let your gentleness be known to all men. The Lord is at hand.\r {BR}6  In nothing be anxious, but in everything, by prayer and petition with thanksgiving, let your requests be made known to God.\r {BR}7  And the peace of God, which surpasses all understanding, will guard your hearts and your thoughts in Christ Jesus.\r {BR}8  Finally, brothers, whatever things are true, whatever things are honorable, whatever things are just, whatever things are pure, whatever things are lovely, whatever things are of good report; if there is any virtue, and if there is any praise, think about these things.\r {BR}9  The things which you learned, received, heard, and saw in me: do these things, and the God of peace will be with you.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Tempted",lessonscriptures:"James\\1:12-18;Matthew\\4:1-11",id:"13",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\James\\1:12-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  Blessed is the man who endures temptation, for when he has been approved, he will receive the crown of life, which the Lord promised to those who love him.\r {BR}13  Let no man say when he is tempted, I am tempted by God, for God can't be tempted by evil, and he himself tempts no one.\r {BR}14  But each one is tempted, when he is drawn away by his own lust, and enticed.\r {BR}15  Then the lust, when it has conceived, bears sin; and the sin, when it is full grown, brings forth death.\r {BR}16  Don't be deceived, my beloved brothers.\r {BR}17  Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, coming down from the Father of lights, with whom can be no variation, nor turning shadow.\r {BR}18  Of his own will he brought us forth by the word of truth, that we should be a kind of first fruits of his creatures.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\4:1-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Then Jesus was led up by the Spirit into the wilderness to be tempted by the devil.\r {BR}2  When he had fasted forty days and forty nights, he was hungry afterward.\r {BR}3  The tempter came and said to him, If you are the Son of God, command that these stones become bread.\r {BR}4  But he answered, {I}{B}It is written, 'Man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word that proceeds out of the mouth of God.' {/B}{/I}\r {BR}5  Then the devil took him into the holy city. He set him on the pinnacle of the temple,\r {BR}6  and said to him, If you are the Son of God, throw yourself down, for it is written, 'He will put his angels in charge of you.' and, 'On their hands they will bear you up, so that you don't dash your foot against a stone.' \r {BR}7  Jesus said to him, {I}{B}Again, it is written, 'You shall not test the Lord, your God.' {/B}{/I}\r {BR}8  Again, the devil took him to an exceedingly high mountain, and showed him all the kingdoms of the world, and their glory.\r {BR}9  He said to him, I will give you all of these things, if you will fall down and worship me.\r {BR}10  Then Jesus said to him, {I}{B}Get behind me, Satan! For it is written, 'You shall worship the Lord your God, and you shall serve him only.' {/B}{/I}\r {BR}11  Then the devil left him, and behold, angels came and served him.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Thankful",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\136:1-26;Luke\\17:11-19",id:"14",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\136:1-26{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Give thanks to Yahweh, for he is good; for his loving kindness endures forever.\r {BR}2  Give thanks to the God of gods; for his loving kindness endures forever.\r {BR}3  Give thanks to the Lord of lords; for his loving kindness endures forever:\r {BR}4  To him who alone does great wonders; for his loving kindness endures forever:\r {BR}5  To him who by understanding made the heavens; for his loving kindness endures forever:\r {BR}6  To him who spread out the earth above the waters; for his loving kindness endures forever:\r {BR}7  To him who made the great lights; for his loving kindness endures forever:\r {BR}8  The sun to rule by day; for his loving kindness endures forever;\r {BR}9  The moon and stars to rule by night; for his loving kindness endures forever:\r {BR}10  To him who struck down the Egyptian firstborn; for his loving kindness endures forever;\r {BR}11  And brought out Israel from among them; for his loving kindness endures forever;\r {BR}12  With a strong hand, and with an outstretched arm; for his loving kindness endures forever:\r {BR}13  To him who divided the Red Sea apart; for his loving kindness endures forever;\r {BR}14  And made Israel to pass through its midst; for his loving kindness endures forever;\r {BR}15  But overthrew Pharaoh and his army in the Red Sea; for his loving kindness endures forever:\r {BR}16  To him who led his people through the wilderness; for his loving kindness endures forever:\r {BR}17  To him who struck great kings; for his loving kindness endures forever;\r {BR}18  And killed mighty kings; for his loving kindness endures forever:\r {BR}19  Sihon king of the Amorites; for his loving kindness endures forever;\r {BR}20  Og king of Bashan; for his loving kindness endures forever;\r {BR}21  And gave their land as an inheritance; for his loving kindness endures forever;\r {BR}22  Even a heritage to Israel his servant; for his loving kindness endures forever:\r {BR}23  Who remembered us in our low estate; for his loving kindness endures forever;\r {BR}24  And has delivered us from our adversaries; for his loving kindness endures forever:\r {BR}25  Who gives food to every creature; for his loving kindness endures forever.\r {BR}26  Oh give thanks to the God of heaven; for his loving kindness endures forever.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\17:11-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  It happened as he was on his way to Jerusalem, that he was passing along the borders of Samaria and Galilee.\r {BR}12  As he entered into a certain village, ten men who were lepers met him, who stood at a distance.\r {BR}13  They lifted up their voices, saying, Jesus, Master, have mercy on us!\r {BR}14  When he saw them, he said to them, {I}{B}Go and show yourselves to the priests.{/B}{/I} It happened that as they went, they were cleansed.\r {BR}15  One of them, when he saw that he was healed, turned back, glorifying God with a loud voice.\r {BR}16  He fell on his face at Jesus' feet, giving him thanks; and he was a Samaritan.\r {BR}17  Jesus answered, {I}{B}Weren't the ten cleansed? But where are the nine?{/B}{/I}\r {BR}18  {I}{B}Were there none found who returned to give glory to God, except this stranger?{/B}{/I}\r {BR}19  Then he said to him, {I}{B}Get up, and go your way. Your faith has healed you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Troubled",lessonscriptures:"Matthew\\6:25-34;2 Corinthians\\4:7-15",id:"15",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\6:25-34{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  {I}{B}Therefore, I tell you, don't be anxious for your life: what you will eat, or what you will drink; nor yet for your body, what you will wear. Isn't life more than food, and the body more than clothing?{/B}{/I}\r {BR}26  {I}{B}See the birds of the sky, that they don't sow, neither do they reap, nor gather into barns. Your heavenly Father feeds them. Aren't you of much more value than they?{/B}{/I}\r {BR}27  {I}{B}Which of you, by being anxious, can add one moment to his lifespan?{/B}{/I}\r {BR}28  {I}{B}Why are you anxious about clothing? Consider the lilies of the field, how they grow. They don't toil, neither do they spin,{/B}{/I}\r {BR}29  {I}{B}yet I tell you that even Solomon in all his glory was not dressed like one of these.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}30  {I}{B}But if God so clothes the grass of the field, which today exists, and tomorrow is thrown into the oven, won't he much more clothe you, you of little faith?{/B}{/I}\r {BR}31  {I}{B}Therefore don't be anxious, saying, 'What will we eat?', 'What will we drink?' or, 'With what will we be clothed?'{/B}{/I}\r {BR}32  {I}{B}For the Gentiles seek after all these things, for your heavenly Father knows that you need all these things.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}33  {I}{B}But seek first God's Kingdom, and his righteousness; and all these things will be given to you as well.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}34  {I}{B}Therefore don't be anxious for tomorrow, for tomorrow will be anxious for itself. Each day's own evil is sufficient.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\4:7-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  But we have this treasure in clay vessels, that the exceeding greatness of the power may be of God, and not from ourselves.\r {BR}8  We are pressed on every side, yet not crushed; perplexed, yet not to despair;\r {BR}9  pursued, yet not forsaken; struck down, yet not destroyed;\r {BR}10  always carrying in the body the putting to death of the Lord Jesus, that the life of Jesus may also be revealed in our body.\r {BR}11  For we who live are always delivered to death for Jesus' sake, that the life also of Jesus may be revealed in our mortal flesh.\r {BR}12  So then death works in us, but life in you.\r {BR}13  But having the same spirit of faith, according to that which is written, I believed, and therefore I spoke. We also believe, and therefore also we speak;\r {BR}14  knowing that he who raised the Lord Jesus will raise us also with Jesus, and will present us with you.\r {BR}15  For all things are for your sakes, that the grace, being multiplied through the many, may cause the thanksgiving to abound to the glory of God.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Weary",lessonscriptures:"Isaiah\\40:21-31;Matthew\\11:25-30",id:"16",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\40:21-31{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  Haven't you known? Haven't you heard, yet? Haven't you been told from the beginning? Haven't you understood from the foundations of the earth?\r {BR}22  It is he who sits above the circle of the earth, and its inhabitants are like grasshoppers; who stretches out the heavens like a curtain, and spreads them out like a tent to dwell in;\r {BR}23  who brings princes to nothing; who makes the judges of the earth like meaningless.\r {BR}24  They are planted scarcely. They are sown scarcely. Their stock has scarcely taken root in the ground. He merely blows on them, and they wither, and the whirlwind takes them away as stubble.\r {BR}25  To whom then will you liken me? Who is my equal? says the Holy One.\r {BR}26  Lift up your eyes on high, and see who has created these, who brings out their army by number. He calls them all by name. by the greatness of his might, and because he is strong in power, Not one is lacking.\r {BR}27  Why do you say, Jacob, and speak, Israel, My way is hidden from Yahweh, and the justice due me is disregarded by my God?\r {BR}28  Haven't you known? Haven't you heard? The everlasting God, Yahweh, The Creator of the ends of the earth, doesn't faint. He isn't weary. His understanding is unsearchable.\r {BR}29  He gives power to the weak. He increases the strength of him who has no might.\r {BR}30  Even the youths faint and get weary, and the young men utterly fall;\r {BR}31  But those who wait for Yahweh will renew their strength. They will mount up with wings like eagles. They will run, and not be weary. They will walk, and not faint.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\11:25-30{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  At that time, Jesus answered, {I}{B}I thank you, Father, Lord of heaven and earth, that you hid these things from the wise and understanding, and revealed them to infants.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}26  {I}{B}Yes, Father, for so it was well-pleasing in your sight.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}27  {I}{B}All things have been delivered to me by my Father. No one knows the Son, except the Father; neither does anyone know the Father, except the Son, and he to whom the Son desires to reveal him.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}28  {I}{B}Come to me, all you who labor and are heavily burdened, and I will give you rest.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}29  {I}{B}Take my yoke upon you, and learn from me, for I am gentle and lowly in heart; and you will find rest for your souls.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}30  {I}{B}For my yoke is easy, and my burden is light.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Acceptance",lessonscriptures:"Ephesians\\1:14-14;Romans\\15:7-7;Ecclesiastes\\10:12-12;Genesis\\1:27-27;Proverbs\\22:1-1;Psalms\\5:12-12;John\\6:37-37;Genesis\\4:7-7;Galatians\\1:10-10;2 Timothy\\2:15-15;Psalms\\145:9-9;Proverbs\\3:3-4",id:"17",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\1:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  who is a pledge of our inheritance, to the redemption of God's own possession, to the praise of his glory.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\15:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Therefore accept one another, even as Christ also accepted you, to the glory of God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ecclesiastes\\10:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  The words of a wise man's mouth are gracious; but a fool is swallowed by his own lips.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Genesis\\1:27-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}27  God created man in his own image. In God's image he created him; male and female he created them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\22:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  A good name is more desirable than great riches, and loving favor is better than silver and gold.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\5:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  For you will bless the righteous. Yahweh, you will surround him with favor as with a shield.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\6:37-37{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}37  {I}{B}All those who the Father gives me will come to me. Him who comes to me I will in no way throw out.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Genesis\\4:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  If you do well, will it not be lifted up? If you don't do well, sin crouches at the door. Its desire is for you, but you are to rule over it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Galatians\\1:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  For am I now seeking the favor of men, or of God? Or am I striving to please men? For if I were still pleasing men, I wouldn't be a servant of Christ.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Timothy\\2:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Give diligence to present yourself approved by God, a workman who doesn't need to be ashamed, properly handling the Word of Truth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\145:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  Yahweh is good to all. His tender mercies are over all his works.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:3-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Don't let kindness and truth forsake you. Bind them around your neck. Write them on the tablet of your heart.\r {BR}4  So you will find favor, and good understanding in the sight of God and man.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Work",lessonscriptures:"Colossians\\3:23-23;Haggai\\2:4-4;Deuteronomy\\28:12-12;Deuteronomy\\16:15-15;1 Thessalonians\\4:11-12;2 Chronicles\\15:7-7;Psalms\\127:2-2;Ecclesiastes\\5:19-19;Hebrews\\4:10-10",id:"18",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Colossians\\3:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  And whatever you do, work heartily, as for the Lord, and not for men,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Haggai\\2:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  Yet now be strong, Zerubbabel,' says Yahweh. 'Be strong, Joshua, son of Jehozadak, the high priest. Be strong, all you people of the land,' says Yahweh, 'and work, for I am with you,' says Yahweh of Armies.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\28:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  Yahweh will open to you his good treasure in the sky, to give the rain of your land in its season, and to bless all the work of your hand: and you shall lend to many nations, and you shall not borrow.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\16:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  You shall keep a feast to Yahweh your God seven days in the place which Yahweh shall choose; because Yahweh your God will bless you in all your increase, and in all the work of your hands, and you shall be altogether joyful.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Thessalonians\\4:11-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  and that you make it your ambition to lead a quiet life, and to do your own business, and to work with your own hands, even as we instructed you;\r {BR}12  that you may walk properly toward those who are outside, and may have need of nothing.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Chronicles\\15:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  But you be strong, and don't let your hands be slack; for your work shall be rewarded.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\127:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  It is vain for you to rise up early, to stay up late, eating the bread of toil; for he gives sleep to his loved ones.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ecclesiastes\\5:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  Every man also to whom God has given riches and wealth, and has given him power to eat of it, and to take his portion, and to rejoice in his labor--this is the gift of God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\4:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  For he who has entered into his rest has himself also rested from his works, as God did from his.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Wisdom",lessonscriptures:"James\\1:5-5;Proverbs\\24:14-14;Daniel\\12:3-3;Job\\12:13-13;James\\3:17-17;Proverbs\\3:13-13;Psalms\\119:98-98;Proverbs\\2:6-6;Psalms\\90:12-12;Proverbs\\4:6-7;Psalms\\107:43-43;1 Corinthians\\1:25-25;Colossians\\2:2-3;Psalms\\5:8-8;Psalms\\25:4-5;Psalms\\25:9-9;Psalms\\27:11-11;Psalms\\32:8-8;Psalms\\37:23-23;Psalms\\73:24-24;Psalms\\119:18-18;Psalms\\119:105-105;Psalms\\119:130-130;Psalms\\143:8-8;Proverbs\\3:5-6;Proverbs\\6:22-22;Isaiah\\42:16-16;Isaiah\\50:4-4;Isaiah\\58:11-11;Jeremiah\\10:23-23;Jeremiah\\31:9-9;2 Corinthians\\5:7-7;Hebrews\\4:12-12;2 Chronicles\\19:6-6;Proverbs\\2:3-6;Proverbs\\16:1-1;Proverbs\\28:5-5;Isaiah\\11:2-3;Daniel\\1:17-17;Psalms\\143:10-11;Proverbs\\1:5-5;Proverbs\\12:15-15;Proverbs\\15:22-22;Proverbs\\19:20-20;Proverbs\\20:18-18;Proverbs\\24:6-6;John\\7:24-24;2 Corinthians\\13:1-1",id:"19",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\James\\1:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  But if any of you lacks wisdom, let him ask of God, who gives to all liberally and without reproach; and it will be given to him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\24:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  so you shall know wisdom to be to your soul; if you have found it, then there will be a reward, your hope will not be cut off.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Daniel\\12:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Those who are wise shall shine as the brightness of the expanse; and those who turn many to righteousness as the stars forever and ever.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Job\\12:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  With God is wisdom and might. He has counsel and understanding.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\3:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  But the wisdom that is from above is first pure, then peaceful, gentle, reasonable, full of mercy and good fruits, without partiality, and without hypocrisy.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  Happy is the man who finds wisdom, the man who gets understanding.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:98-98{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}98  Your commandments make me wiser than my enemies, for your commandments are always with me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\2:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  For Yahweh gives wisdom. Out of his mouth comes knowledge and understanding.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\90:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  So teach us to number our days, that we may gain a heart of wisdom.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\4:6-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Don't forsake her, and she will preserve you. Love her, and she will keep you.\r {BR}7  Wisdom is supreme. Get wisdom. Yes, though it costs all your possessions, get understanding.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\107:43-43{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}43  Whoever is wise will pay attention to these things. They will consider the loving kindnesses of Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\1:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  Because the foolishness of God is wiser than men, and the weakness of God is stronger than men.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Colossians\\2:2-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  that their hearts may be comforted, they being knit together in love, and gaining all riches of the full assurance of understanding, that they may know the mystery of God, both of the Father and of Christ,\r {BR}3  in whom are all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge hidden.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\5:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Lead me, Yahweh, in your righteousness because of my enemies. Make your way straight before my face.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\25:4-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  Show me your ways, Yahweh. Teach me your paths.\r {BR}5  Guide me in your truth, and teach me, For you are the God of my salvation, I wait for you all day long.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\25:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  He will guide the humble in justice. He will teach the humble his way.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\27:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  Teach me your way, Yahweh. Lead me in a straight path, because of my enemies.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\32:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  I will instruct you and teach you in the way which you shall go. I will counsel you with my eye on you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\37:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  A man's goings are established by Yahweh. He delights in his way.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\73:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  You will guide me with your counsel, and afterward receive me to glory.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  Open my eyes, that I may see wondrous things out of your law.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:105-105{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}105  Your word is a lamp to my feet, and a light for my path.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:130-130{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}130  The entrance of your words gives light. It gives understanding to the simple.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\143:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Cause me to hear your loving kindness in the morning, for I trust in you. Cause me to know the way in which I should walk, for I lift up my soul to you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:5-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Trust in Yahweh with all your heart, and don't lean on your own understanding.\r {BR}6  In all your ways acknowledge him, and he will make your paths straight.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\6:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  When you walk, it will lead you. When you sleep, it will watch over you. When you awake, it will talk with you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\42:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  I will bring the blind by a way that they don't know. I will lead them in paths that they don't know. I will make darkness light before them, and crooked places straight. I will do these things, and I will not forsake them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\50:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  The Lord Yahweh has given me the tongue of those who are taught, that I may know how to sustain with words him who is weary: he wakens morning by morning, he wakens my ear to hear as those who are taught.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\58:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  and Yahweh will guide you continually, and satisfy your soul in dry places, and make strong your bones; and you shall be like a watered garden, and like a spring of water, whose waters don't fail.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\10:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  Yahweh, I know that the way of man is not in himself: it is not in man who walks to direct his steps.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\31:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  They shall come with weeping; and with petitions will I lead them: I will cause them to walk by rivers of waters, in a straight way in which they shall not stumble; for I am a father to Israel, and Ephraim is my firstborn.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\5:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  for we walk by faith, not by sight.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\4:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  For the word of God is living, and active, and sharper than any two-edged sword, and piercing even to the dividing of soul and spirit, of both joints and marrow, and is able to discern the thoughts and intentions of the heart.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Chronicles\\19:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  and said to the judges, Consider what you do: for you don't judge for man, but for Yahweh; and ({I}{B}he is{/B}{/I}) with you in the judgment.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\2:3-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Yes, if you call out for discernment, and lift up your voice for understanding;\r {BR}4  If you seek her as silver, and search for her as for hidden treasures:\r {BR}5  then you will understand the fear of Yahweh, and find the knowledge of God.\r {BR}6  For Yahweh gives wisdom. Out of his mouth comes knowledge and understanding.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\16:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  The plans of the heart belong to man, but the answer of the tongue is from Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\28:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Evil men don't understand justice; but those who seek Yahweh understand it fully.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\11:2-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  The Spirit of Yahweh will rest on him: the spirit of wisdom and understanding, the spirit of counsel and might, the spirit of knowledge and of the fear of Yahweh.\r {BR}3  His delight will be in the fear of Yahweh. He will not judge by the sight of his eyes, neither decide by the hearing of his ears;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Daniel\\1:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Now as for these four youths, God gave them knowledge and skill in all learning and wisdom: and Daniel had understanding in all visions and dreams.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\143:10-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Teach me to do your will, for you are my God. Your Spirit is good. Lead me in the land of uprightness.\r {BR}11  Revive me, Yahweh, for your name's sake. In your righteousness, bring my soul out of trouble.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\1:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  that the wise man may hear, and increase in learning; that the man of understanding may attain to sound counsel:\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\12:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  The way of a fool is right in his own eyes, but he who is wise listens to counsel.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\15:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  Where there is no counsel, plans fail; but in a multitude of counselors they are established.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\19:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  Listen to counsel and receive instruction, that you may be wise in your latter end.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\20:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  Plans are established by advice; by wise guidance you wage war!\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\24:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  for by wise guidance you wage your war; and victory is in many advisors.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\7:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  {I}{B}Don't judge according to appearance, but judge righteous judgment.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\13:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  This is the third time I am coming to you. At the mouth of two or three witnesses shall every word be established.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Values",lessonscriptures:"1 Peter\\3:3-4;2 Corinthians\\6:6-6;2 Peter\\1:5-5;Ephesians\\4:2-2;Ephesians\\4:28-28;Matthew\\5:9-9;Matthew\\7:12-12;Proverbs\\4:18-18;Psalms\\106:3-3;Psalms\\37:16-16;Psalms\\84:11-11;Romans\\12:9-9",id:"20",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\3:3-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Let your beauty be not just the outward adorning of braiding the hair, and of wearing jewels of gold, or of putting on fine clothing;\r {BR}4  but in the hidden person of the heart, in the incorruptible adornment of a gentle and quiet spirit, which is in the sight of God very precious.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\6:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  in pureness, in knowledge, in patience, in kindness, in the Holy Spirit, in sincere love,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Peter\\1:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Yes, and for this very cause adding on your part all diligence, in your faith supply moral excellence; and in moral excellence, knowledge;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\4:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  with all lowliness and humility, with patience, bearing with one another in love;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\4:28-28{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  Let him who stole steal no more; but rather let him labor, working with his hands the thing that is good, that he may have something to give to him who has need.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\5:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  {I}{B}Blessed are the peacemakers, for they shall be called children of God.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\7:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  {I}{B}Therefore whatever you desire for men to do to you, you shall also do to them; for this is the law and the prophets.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\4:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  But the path of the righteous is like the dawning light, that shines more and more until the perfect day.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\106:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Blessed are those who keep justice. Blessed is one who does what is right at all times.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\37:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  Better is a little that the righteous has, than the abundance of many wicked.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\84:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  For Yahweh God is a sun and a shield. Yahweh will give grace and glory. He withholds no good thing from those who walk blamelessly.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\12:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  Let love be without hypocrisy. Abhor that which is evil. Cling to that which is good.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Understanding",lessonscriptures:"1 Peter\\3:8-8;Hebrews\\2:18-18;Isaiah\\50:4-4;Isaiah\\54:8-8;Isaiah\\66:13-13;Job\\36:5-5;Matthew\\5:7-7;Proverbs\\28:27-27;Proverbs\\29:7-7;Psalms\\146:8-8;Psalms\\22:24-24;Psalms\\34:18-18",id:"21",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\3:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Finally, be all like-minded, compassionate, loving as brothers, tenderhearted, courteous,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\2:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  For in that he himself has suffered being tempted, he is able to help those who are tempted.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\50:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  The Lord Yahweh has given me the tongue of those who are taught, that I may know how to sustain with words him who is weary: he wakens morning by morning, he wakens my ear to hear as those who are taught.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\54:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  In overflowing wrath I hid my face from you for a moment; but with everlasting loving kindness will I have mercy on you, says Yahweh your Redeemer.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\66:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  As one whom his mother comforts, so will I comfort you; and you shall be comforted in Jerusalem.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Job\\36:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Behold, God is mighty, and doesn't despise anyone. He is mighty in strength of understanding.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\5:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  {I}{B}Blessed are the merciful, for they shall obtain mercy.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\28:27-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}27  One who gives to the poor has no lack; but one who closes his eyes will have many curses.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\29:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  The righteous care about justice for the poor. The wicked aren't concerned about knowledge.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\146:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Yahweh opens the eyes of the blind. Yahweh raises up those who are bowed down. Yahweh loves the righteous.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\22:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  For he has not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the afflicted, Neither has he hidden his face from him; but when he cried to him, he heard.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  Yahweh is near to those who have a broken heart, and saves those who have a crushed spirit.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Trust",lessonscriptures:"James\\1:17-17;Jeremiah\\17:7-7;Malachi\\3:6-6;Nahum\\1:7-7;Proverbs\\3:5-6;Psalms\\143:8-8;Psalms\\40:4-4;Psalms\\9:10-10",id:"22",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\James\\1:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, coming down from the Father of lights, with whom can be no variation, nor turning shadow.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\17:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Blessed is the man who trusts in Yahweh, and whose trust Yahweh is.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Malachi\\3:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  For I, Yahweh, don't change; therefore you, sons of Jacob, are not consumed.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Nahum\\1:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Yahweh is good, a stronghold in the day of trouble; and he knows those who take refuge in him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:5-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Trust in Yahweh with all your heart, and don't lean on your own understanding.\r {BR}6  In all your ways acknowledge him, and he will make your paths straight.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\143:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Cause me to hear your loving kindness in the morning, for I trust in you. Cause me to know the way in which I should walk, for I lift up my soul to you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\40:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  Blessed is the man who makes Yahweh his trust, and doesn't respect the proud, nor such as turn aside to lies.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\9:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Those who know your name will put their trust in you, for you, Yahweh, have not forsaken those who seek you.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Teamwork",lessonscriptures:"1 Corinthians\\12:12-12;1 Corinthians\\12:17-18;1 Corinthians\\12:7-7;Ecclesiastes\\4:9-10;Ephesians\\4:16-16;Ephesians\\4:3-3;Hebrews\\10:24-25;Matthew\\18:20-20;Philippians\\2:1-2;Psalms\\133:1-1;Psalms\\34:3-3;Romans\\15:5-5",id:"23",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\12:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  For as the body is one, and has many members, and all the members of the body, being many, are one body; so also is Christ.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\12:17-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  If the whole body were an eye, where would the hearing be? If the whole were hearing, where would the smelling be?\r {BR}18  But now God has set the members, each one of them, in the body, just as he desired.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\12:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  But to each one is given the manifestation of the Spirit for the profit of all.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ecclesiastes\\4:9-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  Two are better than one, because they have a good reward for their labor.\r {BR}10  For if they fall, the one will lift up his fellow; but woe to him who is alone when he falls, and doesn't have another to lift him up.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\4:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  from whom all the body, being fitted and knit together through that which every joint supplies, according to the working in measure of each individual part, makes the body increase to the building up of itself in love.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\4:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  being eager to keep the unity of the Spirit in the bond of peace.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\10:24-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  Let us consider how to provoke one another to love and good works,\r {BR}25  not forsaking our own assembling together, as the custom of some is, but exhorting one another; and so much the more, as you see the Day approaching.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\18:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  {I}{B}For where two or three are gathered together in my name, there I am in the midst of them.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\2:1-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  If there is therefore any exhortation in Christ, if any consolation of love, if any fellowship of the Spirit, if any tender mercies and compassion,\r {BR}2  make my joy full, by being like-minded, having the same love, being of one accord, of one mind;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\133:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  See how good and how pleasant it is for brothers to live together in unity!\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Oh magnify Yahweh with me. Let us exalt his name together.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\15:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Now the God of patience and of encouragement grant you to be of the same mind one with another according to Christ Jesus,\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Support",lessonscriptures:"1 Peter\\5:10-10;2 Corinthians\\3:5-5;Deuteronomy\\8:18-18;Galatians\\6:2-2;Hebrews\\13:16-16;Isaiah\\40:29-29;Job\\22:28-28;Joshua\\23:10-10;Nahum\\1:7-7;Philippians\\4:19-19;Proverbs\\3:26-26;Psalms\\125:1-1",id:"24",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\5:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  But may the God of all grace, who called you to his eternal glory by Christ Jesus, after you have suffered a little while, perfect, establish, strengthen, and settle you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\3:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  not that we are sufficient of ourselves, to account anything as from ourselves; but our sufficiency is from God;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\8:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  But you shall remember Yahweh your God, for it is he who gives you power to get wealth; that he may establish his covenant which he swore to your fathers, as at this day.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Galatians\\6:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  Bear one another's burdens, and so fulfill the law of Christ.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\13:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  But don't forget to be doing good and sharing, for with such sacrifices God is well pleased.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\40:29-29{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}29  He gives power to the weak. He increases the strength of him who has no might.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Job\\22:28-28{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  You shall also decree a thing, and it shall be established to you. Light shall shine on your ways.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Joshua\\23:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  One man of you shall chase a thousand; for it is Yahweh your God who fights for you, as he spoke to you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Nahum\\1:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Yahweh is good, a stronghold in the day of trouble; and he knows those who take refuge in him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\4:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  My God will supply every need of yours according to his riches in glory in Christ Jesus.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:26-26{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}26  for Yahweh will be your confidence, and will keep your foot from being taken.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\125:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Those who trust in Yahweh are as Mount Zion, which can't be moved, but remains forever.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Strength",lessonscriptures:"2 Samuel\\22:33-33;2 Thessalonians\\3:3-3;Colossians\\1:11-12;Ephesians\\6:10-10;Ephesians\\6:13-13;Exodus\\15:2-2;Habakkuk\\3:19-19;Isaiah\\30:15-15;Isaiah\\40:31-31;Isaiah\\41:10-10;Isaiah\\58:11-11;Jeremiah\\10:12-12;Nehemiah\\8:10-10;Philippians\\4:13-13;Psalms\\1:1-3;Psalms\\18:32-32;Psalms\\89:21-21;Exodus\\23:25-25;2 Kings\\20:5-5;1 Chronicles\\11:9-9;Psalms\\21:1-1;Psalms\\21:4-4;Psalms\\21:6-6;Psalms\\34:20-20;Psalms\\71:17-18;Psalms\\112:7-7;Psalms\\144:12-12;Proverbs\\3:23-23;3 John\\1:2-2;Deuteronomy\\20:4-4;1 Chronicles\\28:20-20;2 Chronicles\\32:8-8;Psalms\\8:2-2;Psalms\\18:29-32;Psalms\\20:7-7;Psalms\\27:13-14;Psalms\\28:7-8;Psalms\\37:39-39;Psalms\\73:26-26;Psalms\\84:5-7;Psalms\\118:14-14;Psalms\\119:28-28;Isaiah\\25:4-4;Isaiah\\40:29-29;Matthew\\19:26-26;Romans\\8:31-31;2 Corinthians\\3:5-5;2 Corinthians\\10:4-4;2 Corinthians\\12:9-10;Ephesians\\3:16-16;Philippians\\4:13\\;1 John\\4:4-4;Joshua\\1:9-9;Jeremiah\\5:14-14;Zechariah\\10:12-12;Matthew\\10:20-20;Acts\\1:8-8;Acts\\4:13-13;1 Corinthians\\1:18-18;1 Corinthians\\2:4-5",id:"25",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\2 Samuel\\22:33-33{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}33  God is my strong fortress. He makes my way perfect.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Thessalonians\\3:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  But the Lord is faithful, who will establish you, and guard you from the evil one.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Colossians\\1:11-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  strengthened with all power, according to the might of his glory, for all endurance and perseverance with joy;\r {BR}12  giving thanks to the Father, who made us fit to be partakers of the inheritance of the saints in light;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\6:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Finally, be strong in the Lord, and in the strength of his might.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\6:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  Therefore, put on the whole armor of God, that you may be able to withstand in the evil day, and, having done all, to stand.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Exodus\\15:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  Yah is my strength and song. He has become my salvation. This is my God, and I will praise him; my father's God, and I will exalt him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Habakkuk\\3:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  Yahweh, the Lord, is my strength. He makes my feet like deer's feet, and enables me to go in high places. For the music director, on my stringed instruments.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\30:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  For thus said the Lord Yahweh, the Holy One of Israel, You will be saved in returning and rest. Your strength will be in quietness and in confidence. You refused,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\40:31-31{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}31  But those who wait for Yahweh will renew their strength. They will mount up with wings like eagles. They will run, and not be weary. They will walk, and not faint.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\41:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Don't you be afraid, for I am with you. Don't be dismayed, for I am your God. I will strengthen you. Yes, I will help you. Yes, I will uphold you with the right hand of my righteousness.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\58:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  and Yahweh will guide you continually, and satisfy your soul in dry places, and make strong your bones; and you shall be like a watered garden, and like a spring of water, whose waters don't fail.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\10:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  He has made the earth by his power, he has established the world by his wisdom, and by his understanding has he stretched out the heavens:\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Nehemiah\\8:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Then he said to them, Go your way, eat the fat, and drink the sweet, and send portions to him for whom nothing is prepared; for this day is holy to our Lord. Don't be grieved; for the joy of Yahweh is your strength.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\4:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  I can do all things through Christ, who strengthens me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\1:1-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Blessed is the man who doesn't walk in the counsel of the wicked, nor stand in the way of sinners, nor sit in the seat of scoffers;\r {BR}2  but his delight is in Yahweh's law. On his law he meditates day and night.\r {BR}3  He will be like a tree planted by the streams of water, that brings forth its fruit in its season, whose leaf also does not wither. Whatever he does shall prosper.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\18:32-32{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}32  the God who arms me with strength, and makes my way perfect?\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\89:21-21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  with whom my hand shall be established. My arm will also strengthen him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Exodus\\23:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  You shall serve Yahweh your God, and he will bless your bread and your water, and I will take sickness away from your midst.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Kings\\20:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Turn back, and tell Hezekiah the prince of my people, Thus says Yahweh, the God of David your father, I have heard your prayer, I have seen your tears: behold, I will heal you; on the third day you shall go up to the house of Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Chronicles\\11:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  David grew greater and greater; for Yahweh of Armies was with him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\21:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  The king rejoices in your strength, Yahweh! How greatly he rejoices in your salvation!\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\21:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  He asked life of you, you gave it to him, even length of days forever and ever.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\21:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  For you make him most blessed forever. You make him glad with joy in your presence.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  He protects all of his bones. Not one of them is broken.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\71:17-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  God, you have taught me from my youth. Until now, I have declared your wondrous works.\r {BR}18  Yes, even when I am old and gray-haired, God, don't forsake me, until I have declared your strength to the next generation, your might to everyone who is to come.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\112:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  He will not be afraid of evil news. His heart is steadfast, trusting in Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\144:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  Then our sons will be like well-nurtured plants, our daughters like pillars carved to adorn a palace.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  Then you shall walk in your way securely. Your foot won't stumble.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\3 John\\1:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  Beloved, I pray that you may prosper in all things and be healthy, even as your soul prospers.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\20:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  for Yahweh your God is he who goes with you, to fight for you against your enemies, to save you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Chronicles\\28:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  David said to Solomon his son, Be strong and of good courage, and do it: don't be afraid, nor be dismayed; for Yahweh God, even my God, is with you; he will not fail you, nor forsake you, until all the work for the service of the house of Yahweh is finished.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Chronicles\\32:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  with him is an arm of flesh; but with us is Yahweh our God to help us, and to fight our battles. The people rested themselves on the words of Hezekiah king of Judah.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\8:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  From the lips of babes and infants you have established strength, because of your adversaries, that you might silence the enemy and the avenger.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\18:29-32{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}29  For by you, I advance through a troop. By my God, I leap over a wall.\r {BR}30  As for God, his way is perfect. The word of Yahweh is tried. He is a shield to all those who take refuge in him.\r {BR}31  For who is God, except Yahweh? Who is a rock, besides our God,\r {BR}32  the God who arms me with strength, and makes my way perfect?\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\20:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Some trust in chariots, and some in horses, but we trust the name of Yahweh our God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\27:13-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  I am still confident of this: I will see the goodness of Yahweh in the land of the living.\r {BR}14  Wait for Yahweh. Be strong, and let your heart take courage. Yes, wait for Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\28:7-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Yahweh is my strength and my shield. My heart has trusted in him, and I am helped. Therefore my heart greatly rejoices. With my song I will thank him.\r {BR}8  Yahweh is their strength. He is a stronghold of salvation to his anointed.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\37:39-39{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}39  But the salvation of the righteous is from Yahweh. He is their stronghold in the time of trouble.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\73:26-26{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}26  My flesh and my heart fails, but God is the strength of my heart and my portion forever.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\84:5-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Blessed are those whose strength is in you; who have set their hearts on a pilgrimage.\r {BR}6  Passing through the valley of Weeping, they make it a place of springs. Yes, the autumn rain covers it with blessings.\r {BR}7  They go from strength to strength. Everyone of them appears before God in Zion.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\118:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  Yah is my strength and song. He has become my salvation.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:28-28{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  My soul is weary with sorrow: strengthen me according to your word.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\25:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  For you have been a stronghold to the poor, a stronghold to the needy in his distress, a refuge from the storm, a shade from the heat, when the blast of the dreaded ones is like a storm against the wall.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\40:29-29{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}29  He gives power to the weak. He increases the strength of him who has no might.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\19:26-26{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}26  Looking at them, Jesus said, {I}{B}With men this is impossible, but with God all things are possible.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\8:31-31{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}31  What then shall we say about these things? If God is for us, who can be against us?\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\3:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  not that we are sufficient of ourselves, to account anything as from ourselves; but our sufficiency is from God;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\10:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  for the weapons of our warfare are not of the flesh, but mighty before God to the throwing down of strongholds,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\12:9-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  He has said to me, My grace is sufficient for you, for my power is made perfect in weakness. Most gladly therefore I will rather glory in my weaknesses, that the power of Christ may rest on me.\r {BR}10  Therefore I take pleasure in weaknesses, in injuries, in necessities, in persecutions, in distresses, for Christ's sake. For when I am weak, then am I strong.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\3:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  that he would grant you, according to the riches of his glory, that you may be strengthened with power through his Spirit in the inward man;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\4:13\\{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  I can do all things through Christ, who strengthens me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\4:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  You are of God, little children, and have overcome them; because greater is he who is in you than he who is in the world.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Joshua\\1:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  Haven't I commanded you? Be strong and of good courage. Don't be afraid, neither be dismayed: for Yahweh your God is with you wherever you go.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\5:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  Therefore thus says Yahweh, the God of Armies, Because you speak this word, behold, I will make my words in your mouth fire, and this people wood, and it shall devour them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Zechariah\\10:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  I will strengthen them in Yahweh; and they will walk up and down in his name, says Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\10:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  {I}{B}For it is not you who speak, but the Spirit of your Father who speaks in you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Acts\\1:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  {I}{B}But you will receive power when the Holy Spirit has come upon you. You will be witnesses to me in Jerusalem, in all Judea and Samaria, and to the uttermost parts of the earth.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Acts\\4:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, and had perceived that they were unlearned and ignorant men, they marveled. They recognized that they had been with Jesus.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\1:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  For the word of the cross is foolishness to those who are dying, but to us who are saved it is the power of God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\2:4-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  My speech and my preaching were not in persuasive words of human wisdom, but in demonstration of the Spirit and of power,\r {BR}5  that your faith wouldn't stand in the wisdom of men, but in the power of God.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Salvation",lessonscriptures:"1 Thessalonians\\5:9-9;2 Corinthians\\5:17-18;Habakkuk\\3:18-18;Hebrews\\9:28-28;Isaiah\\12:2-2;Isaiah\\45:22-22;Isaiah\\61:10-10;Isaiah\\63:1-1;Isaiah\\9:6-6;John\\3:16-16;John\\3:17-18;Lamentations\\3:26-26;Psalms\\13:5-5;Psalms\\50:15-15;Psalms\\62:1-2;Psalms\\62:7-7;Psalms\\74:12-12",id:"26",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Thessalonians\\5:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  For God didn't appoint us to wrath, but to the obtaining of salvation through our Lord Jesus Christ,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\5:17-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Therefore if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation. The old things have passed away. Behold, all things have become new.\r {BR}18  But all things are of God, who reconciled us to himself through Jesus Christ, and gave to us the ministry of reconciliation;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Habakkuk\\3:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  yet I will rejoice in Yahweh. I will be joyful in the God of my salvation!\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\9:28-28{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  so Christ also, having been offered once to bear the sins of many, will appear a second time, without sin, to those who are eagerly waiting for him for salvation.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\12:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  Behold, God is my salvation. I will trust, and will not be afraid; for Yah, Yahweh, is my strength and song; and he has become my salvation.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\45:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  Look to me, and be saved, all the ends of the earth; for I am God, and there is no other.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\61:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  I will greatly rejoice in Yahweh, my soul shall be joyful in my God; for he has clothed me with the garments of salvation, he has covered me with the robe of righteousness, as a bridegroom decks himself with a garland, and as a bride adorns herself with her jewels.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\63:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Who is this who comes from Edom, with dyed garments from Bozrah? this who is glorious in his clothing, marching in the greatness of his strength? It is I who speak in righteousness, mighty to save.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\9:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  For to us a child is born. To us a son is given; and the government will be on his shoulders. His name will be called Wonderful, Counselor, Mighty God, Everlasting Father, Prince of Peace.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\3:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  {I}{B}For God so loved the world, that he gave his one and only Son, that whoever believes in him should not perish, but have eternal life.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\3:17-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  {I}{B}For God didn't send his Son into the world to judge the world, but that the world should be saved through him.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}18  {I}{B}He who believes in him is not judged. He who doesn't believe has been judged already, because he has not believed in the name of the one and only Son of God.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Lamentations\\3:26-26{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}26  It is good that a man should hope and quietly wait for the salvation of Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\13:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  But I trust in your loving kindness. My heart rejoices in your salvation.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\50:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Call on me in the day of trouble. I will deliver you, and you will honor me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\62:1-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  My soul rests in God alone. My salvation is from him.\r {BR}2  He alone is my rock and my salvation, my fortress-- I will never be greatly shaken.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\62:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  With God is my salvation and my honor. The rock of my strength, and my refuge, is in God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\74:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  Yet God is my King of old, working salvation in the midst of the earth.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Reward",lessonscriptures:"1 Samuel\\26:23-23;2 Chronicles\\20:20-20;Hebrews\\6:10-10;Isaiah\\3:10-10;Isaiah\\49:4-4;Jeremiah\\17:10-10;Luke\\6:35-35;Matthew\\10:42-42;Matthew\\5:9-9;Matthew\\6:4-4;Proverbs\\11:18-18;Proverbs\\16:20-20;Proverbs\\19:17-17;Psalms\\41:1-2;Psalms\\58:11-11;Revelation\\22:12-12;Romans\\2:7-7",id:"27",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Samuel\\26:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  Yahweh will render to every man his righteousness and his faithfulness; because Yahweh delivered you into my hand today, and I wouldn't put forth my hand against Yahweh's anointed.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Chronicles\\20:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  They rose early in the morning, and went forth into the wilderness of Tekoa: and as they went forth, Jehoshaphat stood and said, Hear me, Judah, and you inhabitants of Jerusalem: believe in Yahweh your God, so you shall be established; believe his prophets, so you shall prosper.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\6:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  For God is not unrighteous, so as to forget your work and the labor of love which you showed toward his name, in that you served the saints, and still do serve them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\3:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Tell the righteous Good! For they shall eat the fruit of their deeds.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\49:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  But I said, I have labored in vain, I have spent my strength for nothing and vanity; yet surely the justice ({I}{B}due{/B}{/I}) to me is with Yahweh, and my reward with my God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\17:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  I, Yahweh, search the mind, I try the heart, even to give every man according to his ways, according to the fruit of his doings.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\6:35-35{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}35  {I}{B}But love your enemies, and do good, and lend, expecting nothing back; and your reward will be great, and you will be children of the Most High; for he is kind toward the unthankful and evil.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\10:42-42{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}42  {I}{B}Whoever gives one of these little ones just a cup of cold water to drink in the name of a disciple, most certainly I tell you he will in no way lose his reward.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\5:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  {I}{B}Blessed are the peacemakers, for they shall be called children of God.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\6:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  {I}{B}so that your merciful deeds may be in secret, then your Father who sees in secret will reward you openly.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\11:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  Wicked people earn deceitful wages, but one who sows righteousness reaps a sure reward.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\16:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  He who heeds the Word finds prosperity. Whoever trusts in Yahweh is blessed.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\19:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  He who has pity on the poor lends to Yahweh; he will reward him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\41:1-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Blessed is he who considers the poor. Yahweh will deliver him in the day of evil.\r {BR}2  Yahweh will preserve him, and keep him alive. He shall be blessed on the earth, and he will not surrender him to the will of his enemies.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\58:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  so that men shall say, Most certainly there is a reward for the righteous. Most certainly there is a God who judges the earth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Revelation\\22:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  {I}{B}Behold, I come quickly. My reward is with me, to repay to each man according to his work.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\2:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  to those who by patience in well-doing seek for glory, honor, and incorruptibility, eternal life;\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Rest",lessonscriptures:"2 Corinthians\\12:9-9;Acts\\3:19-20;Exodus\\33:14-14;Isaiah\\30:15-15;Jeremiah\\31:25-25;Matthew\\11:28-28;Proverbs\\19:23-23;Psalms\\3:5-5;Psalms\\51:12-12;Psalms\\55:22-22;Psalms\\62:1-1;Psalms\\71:20-20;1 Samuel\\9:27-27;2 Chronicles\\14:7-7;Psalms\\4:4-4;Psalms\\27:14-14;Psalms\\37:7-7;Psalms\\40:1-1;Psalms\\46:10-10;Psalms\\62:8-8;Isaiah\\26:3-3;Isaiah\\32:17-17;Isaiah\\40:31-31;Jeremiah\\17:7-8;Jeremiah\\29:11-13;Lamentations\\3:25-26;Matthew\\11:28-30;Philippians\\4:7-7;2 Timothy\\1:12-12;1 Peter\\5:7-7",id:"28",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\12:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  He has said to me, My grace is sufficient for you, for my power is made perfect in weakness. Most gladly therefore I will rather glory in my weaknesses, that the power of Christ may rest on me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Acts\\3:19-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  Repent therefore, and turn again, that your sins may be blotted out, so that there may come times of refreshing from the presence of the Lord,\r {BR}20  and that he may send Christ Jesus, who was ordained for you before,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Exodus\\33:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  He said, My presence will go with you, and I will give you rest.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\30:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  For thus said the Lord Yahweh, the Holy One of Israel, You will be saved in returning and rest. Your strength will be in quietness and in confidence. You refused,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\31:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  For I have satiated the weary soul, and every sorrowful soul have I replenished.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\11:28-28{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  {I}{B}Come to me, all you who labor and are heavily burdened, and I will give you rest.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\19:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  The fear of Yahweh leads to life, then contentment; he rests and will not be touched by trouble.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\3:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  I laid myself down and slept. I awakened; for Yahweh sustains me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\51:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  Restore to me the joy of your salvation. Uphold me with a willing spirit.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\55:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  Cast your burden on Yahweh, and he will sustain you. He will never allow the righteous to be moved.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\62:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  My soul rests in God alone. My salvation is from him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\71:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  You, who have shown us many and bitter troubles, you will let me live. You will bring us up again from the depths of the earth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Samuel\\9:27-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}27  As they were going down at the end of the city, Samuel said to Saul, Bid the servant pass on before us  (and he passed on), but stand still first, that I may cause you to hear the word of God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Chronicles\\14:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  For he said to Judah, Let us build these cities, and make about them walls, and towers, gates, and bars; the land is yet before us, because we have sought Yahweh our God; we have sought him, and he has given us rest on every side. So they built and prospered.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\4:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  Stand in awe, and don't sin. Search your own heart on your bed, and be still. Selah.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\27:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  Wait for Yahweh. Be strong, and let your heart take courage. Yes, wait for Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\37:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Rest in Yahweh, and wait patiently for him. Don't fret because of him who prospers in his way, because of the man who makes wicked plots happen.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\40:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  I waited patiently for Yahweh. He turned to me, and heard my cry.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\46:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Be still, and know that I am God. I will be exalted among the nations. I will be exalted in the earth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\62:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Trust in him at all times, you people. Pour out your heart before him. God is a refuge for us. Selah.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\26:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  You will keep whoever's mind is steadfast in perfect peace, because he trusts in you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\32:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  The work of righteousness will be peace; and the effect of righteousness, quietness and confidence forever.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\40:31-31{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}31  But those who wait for Yahweh will renew their strength. They will mount up with wings like eagles. They will run, and not be weary. They will walk, and not faint.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\17:7-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Blessed is the man who trusts in Yahweh, and whose trust Yahweh is.\r {BR}8  For he shall be as a tree planted by the waters, who spreads out its roots by the river, and shall not fear when heat comes, but its leaf shall be green; and shall not be careful in the year of drought, neither shall cease from yielding fruit.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\29:11-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  For I know the thoughts that I think toward you, says Yahweh, thoughts of peace, and not of evil, to give you hope in your latter end.\r {BR}12  You shall call on me, and you shall go and pray to me, and I will listen to you.\r {BR}13  You shall seek me, and find me, when you shall search for me with all your heart.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Lamentations\\3:25-26{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  Yahweh is good to those who wait for him, to the soul that seeks him.\r {BR}26  It is good that a man should hope and quietly wait for the salvation of Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\11:28-30{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  {I}{B}Come to me, all you who labor and are heavily burdened, and I will give you rest.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}29  {I}{B}Take my yoke upon you, and learn from me, for I am gentle and lowly in heart; and you will find rest for your souls.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}30  {I}{B}For my yoke is easy, and my burden is light.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\4:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  And the peace of God, which surpasses all understanding, will guard your hearts and your thoughts in Christ Jesus.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Timothy\\1:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  For this cause I also suffer these things. Yet I am not ashamed, for I know him whom I have believed, and I am persuaded that he is able to guard that which I have committed to him against that day.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\5:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  casting all your worries on him, because he cares for you.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Reputation",lessonscriptures:"1 Corinthians\\10:16-17;1 Peter\\2:12-12;2 Corinthians\\12:6-6;2 Peter\\1:5-7;3 John\\1:3-3;Deuteronomy\\4:5-6;James\\4:10-10;Nehemiah\\9:10-10;Proverbs\\3:3-4;Psalms\\52:9-9;Romans\\12:3-3;Romans\\8:15-15",id:"29",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\10:16-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  The cup of blessing which we bless, isn't it a sharing of the blood of Christ? The bread which we break, isn't it a sharing of the body of Christ?\r {BR}17  Because there is one loaf of bread, we, who are many, are one body; for we all partake of the one loaf of bread.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\2:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  having good behavior among the nations, so in that of which they speak against you as evildoers, they may by your good works, which they see, glorify God in the day of visitation.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\12:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  For if I would desire to boast, I will not be foolish; for I will speak the truth. But I refrain, so that no man may think more of me than that which he sees in me, or hears from me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Peter\\1:5-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Yes, and for this very cause adding on your part all diligence, in your faith supply moral excellence; and in moral excellence, knowledge;\r {BR}6  and in knowledge, self-control; and in self-control patience; and in patience godliness;\r {BR}7  and in godliness brotherly affection; and in brotherly affection, love.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\3 John\\1:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  For I rejoiced greatly, when brothers came and testified about your truth, even as you walk in truth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\4:5-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Behold, I have taught you statutes and ordinances, even as Yahweh my God commanded me, that you should do so in the midst of the land where you go in to possess it.\r {BR}6  Keep therefore and do them; for this is your wisdom and your understanding in the sight of the peoples, who shall hear all these statutes, and say, Surely this great nation is a wise and understanding people.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\4:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Humble yourselves in the sight of the Lord, and he will exalt you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Nehemiah\\9:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  and showed signs and wonders on Pharaoh, and on all his servants, and on all the people of his land; for you knew that they dealt proudly against them, and made a name for you, as it is this day.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:3-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Don't let kindness and truth forsake you. Bind them around your neck. Write them on the tablet of your heart.\r {BR}4  So you will find favor, and good understanding in the sight of God and man.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\52:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  I will give you thanks forever, because you have done it. I will hope in your name, for it is good, in the presence of your saints.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\12:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  For I say, through the grace that was given me, to every man who is among you, not to think of himself more highly than he ought to think; but to think reasonably, as God has apportioned to each person a measure of faith.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\8:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  For you didn't receive the spirit of bondage again to fear, but you received the Spirit of adoption, by whom we cry, Abba! Father!\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Reassurance",lessonscriptures:"1 Peter\\3:12-12;Deuteronomy\\1:30-30;Hebrews\\13:5-5;Hebrews\\7:24-25;Isaiah\\41:13-13;Isaiah\\57:15-15;Matthew\\21:22-22;Matthew\\6:8-8;Philippians\\1:6-6;Proverbs\\15:29-29;Proverbs\\23:18-18;Psalms\\34:15-15;Romans\\8:37-37",id:"30",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\3:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  For the eyes of the Lord are on the righteous, and his ears open to their prayer; but the face of the Lord is against those who do evil.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\1:30-30{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}30  Yahweh your God who goes before you, he will fight for you, according to all that he did for you in Egypt before your eyes,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\13:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Be free from the love of money, content with such things as you have, for he has said, I will in no way leave you, neither will I in any way forsake you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\7:24-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  But he, because he lives forever, has his priesthood unchangeable.\r {BR}25  Therefore he is also able to save to the uttermost those who draw near to God through him, seeing that he lives forever to make intercession for them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\41:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  For I, Yahweh your God, will hold your right hand, saying to you, 'Don't be afraid. I will help you.'\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\57:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  For thus says the high and lofty One who inhabits eternity, whose name is Holy: I dwell in the high and holy place, with him also who is of a contrite and humble spirit, to revive the spirit of the humble, and to revive the heart of the contrite.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\21:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  {I}{B}All things, whatever you ask in prayer, believing, you will receive.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\6:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  {I}{B}Therefore don't be like them, for your Father knows what things you need, before you ask him.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\1:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  being confident of this very thing, that he who began a good work in you will complete it until the day of Jesus Christ.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\15:29-29{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}29  Yahweh is far from the wicked, but he hears the prayer of the righteous.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\23:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  Indeed surely there is a future hope, and your hope will not be cut off.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Yahweh's eyes are toward the righteous. His ears listen to their cry.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\8:37-37{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}37  No, in all these things, we are more than conquerors through him who loved us.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Prosperity",lessonscriptures:"1 Chronicles\\22:13-13;1 Corinthians\\15:58-58;Jeremiah\\29:11-11;Job\\22:21-21;Job\\36:11-11;Matthew\\25:29-29;Matthew\\6:33-33;Proverbs\\21:5-5;Proverbs\\28:25-25;Psalms\\103:5-5;Psalms\\67:1-1;Psalms\\90:17-17;Romans\\8:28-28",id:"31",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Chronicles\\22:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  Then you shall prosper, if you observe to do the statutes and the ordinances which Yahweh gave Moses concerning Israel. Be strong, and of good courage. Don't be afraid, neither be dismayed.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\15:58-58{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}58  Therefore, my beloved brothers, be steadfast, immovable, always abounding in the Lord's work, because you know that your labor is not in vain in the Lord.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\29:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  For I know the thoughts that I think toward you, says Yahweh, thoughts of peace, and not of evil, to give you hope in your latter end.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Job\\22:21-21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  Acquaint yourself with him, now, and be at peace. Thereby good shall come to you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Job\\36:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  If they listen and serve him, they shall spend their days in prosperity, and their years in pleasures.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\25:29-29{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}29  {I}{B}For to everyone who has will be given, and he will have abundance, but from him who doesn't have, even that which he has will be taken away.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\6:33-33{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}33  {I}{B}But seek first God's Kingdom, and his righteousness; and all these things will be given to you as well.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\21:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  The plans of the diligent surely lead to profit; and everyone who is hasty surely rushes to poverty.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\28:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  One who is greedy stirs up strife; but one who trusts in Yahweh will prosper.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\103:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  who satisfies your desire with good things, so that your youth is renewed like the eagle's.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\67:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  May God be merciful to us, bless us, and cause his face to shine on us. Selah.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\90:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Let the favor of the Lord our God be on us; establish the work of our hands for us; yes, establish the work of our hands.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\8:28-28{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  We know that all things work together for good for those who love God, to those who are called according to his purpose.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Prayer",lessonscriptures:"1 Chronicles\\16:11-11;1 John\\5:14-15;1 Thessalonians\\5:16-18;Hosea\\14:8-8;James\\5:16-16;Jeremiah\\33:3-3;John\\15:7-7;John\\16:24-24;John\\9:31-31;Lamentations\\3:57-57;Matthew\\18:19-20;Matthew\\6:6-6;Matthew\\7:7-8;Psalms\\116:1-2;Psalms\\4:3-3;Psalms\\69:13-13;Matthew\\7:7-7;Isaiah\\65:24-24;1 Thessalonians\\5:17-17;Psalms\\66:18-19;Luke\\22:31-32;Hebrews\\7:25-25;1 Timothy\\2:8-8;Romans\\8:26-27;Mark\\11:24-24;1 John\\3:22-22;Matthew\\26:39-39;Matthew\\6:6-7;Hebrews\\4:16-16;Ephesians\\6:18-18;Psalms\\55:17-17;Psalms\\102:17-17;Isaiah\\30:19-19;Matthew\\6:5-5;Matthew\\18:18-20;John\\14:13-14;John\\16:23-24;James\\4:8-8;Isaiah\\45:11-11;Jeremiah\\29:13-13;Matthew\\21:21-22;Luke\\11:9-10;Romans\\4:20-21;Ephesians\\3:20-20;Hebrews\\11:6-6;James\\1:6-7;1 John\\5:14-14;Psalms\\5:3-3;Psalms\\63:1-1;Psalms\\119:2-2;2 Samuel\\22:5-7;Psalms\\22:24-24;Psalms\\50:15-15;Psalms\\62:8-8;Psalms\\106:44-45;Psalms\\119:10-10;Isaiah\\55:6-6;Isaiah\\64:7-7;Lamentations\\2:19-19;Lamentations\\3:40-41;Joel\\2:12-12;Matthew\\17:21-21",id:"32",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Chronicles\\16:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  Seek Yahweh and his strength. Seek his face forever more.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\5:14-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  This is the boldness which we have toward him, that, if we ask anything according to his will, he listens to us.\r {BR}15  And if we know that he listens to us, whatever we ask, we know that we have the petitions which we have asked of him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Thessalonians\\5:16-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  Rejoice always.\r {BR}17  Pray without ceasing.\r {BR}18  In everything give thanks, for this is the will of God in Christ Jesus toward you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hosea\\14:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Ephraim, what have I to do any more with idols? I answer, and will take care of him. I am like a green fir tree; from me your fruit is found.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\5:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  Confess your offenses to one another, and pray for one another, that you may be healed. The insistent prayer of a righteous person is powerfully effective.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\33:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Call to me, and I will answer you, and will show you great things, and difficult, which you don't know.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\15:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  {I}{B}If you remain in me, and my words remain in you, you will ask whatever you desire, and it will be done for you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\16:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  {I}{B}Until now, you have asked nothing in my name. Ask, and you will receive, that your joy may be made full.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\9:31-31{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}31  We know that God doesn't listen to sinners, but if anyone is a worshipper of God, and does his will, he listens to him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Lamentations\\3:57-57{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}57  You drew near in the day that I called on you; you said, Don't be afraid.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\18:19-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  {I}{B}Again, assuredly I tell you, that if two of you will agree on earth concerning anything that they will ask, it will be done for them by my Father who is in heaven.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}20  {I}{B}For where two or three are gathered together in my name, there I am in the midst of them.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\6:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  {I}{B}But you, when you pray, enter into your inner chamber, and having shut your door, pray to your Father who is in secret, and your Father who sees in secret will reward you openly.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\7:7-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  {I}{B}Ask, and it will be given you. Seek, and you will find. Knock, and it will be opened for you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}8  {I}{B}For everyone who asks receives. He who seeks finds. To him who knocks it will be opened.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\116:1-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  I love Yahweh, because he listens to my voice, and my cries for mercy.\r {BR}2  Because he has turned his ear to me, therefore I will call on him as long as I live.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\4:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  But know that Yahweh has set apart for himself him who is godly: Yahweh will hear when I call to him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\69:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  But as for me, my prayer is to you, Yahweh, in an acceptable time. God, in the abundance of your loving kindness, answer me in the truth of your salvation.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\7:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  {I}{B}Ask, and it will be given you. Seek, and you will find. Knock, and it will be opened for you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\65:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  It shall happen that, before they call, I will answer; and while they are yet speaking, I will hear.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Thessalonians\\5:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Pray without ceasing.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\66:18-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  If I cherished sin in my heart, the Lord wouldn't have listened.\r {BR}19  But most certainly, God has listened. He has heard the voice of my prayer.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\22:31-32{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}31  The Lord said, {I}{B}Simon, Simon, behold, Satan asked to have you, that he might sift you as wheat,{/B}{/I}\r {BR}32  {I}{B}but I prayed for you, that your faith wouldn't fail. You, when once you have turned again, establish your brothers.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\7:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  Therefore he is also able to save to the uttermost those who draw near to God through him, seeing that he lives forever to make intercession for them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Timothy\\2:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  I desire therefore that the men in every place pray, lifting up holy hands without anger and doubting.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\8:26-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}26  In the same way, the Spirit also helps our weaknesses, for we don't know how to pray as we ought. But the Spirit himself makes intercession for us with groanings which can't be uttered.\r {BR}27  He who searches the hearts knows what is on the Spirit's mind, because he makes intercession for the saints according to God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Mark\\11:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  {I}{B}Therefore I tell you, all things whatever you pray and ask for, believe that you have received them, and you shall have them.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\3:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  and whatever we ask, we receive from him, because we keep his commandments and do the things that are pleasing in his sight.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\26:39-39{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}39  He went forward a little, fell on his face, and prayed, saying, {I}{B}My Father, if it is possible, let this cup pass away from me; nevertheless, not what I desire, but what you desire.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\6:6-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  {I}{B}But you, when you pray, enter into your inner chamber, and having shut your door, pray to your Father who is in secret, and your Father who sees in secret will reward you openly.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}7  {I}{B}In praying, don't use vain repetitions, as the Gentiles do; for they think that they will be heard for their much speaking.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\4:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  Let us therefore draw near with boldness to the throne of grace, that we may receive mercy, and may find grace for help in time of need.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\6:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  with all prayer and requests, praying at all times in the Spirit, and being watchful to this end in all perseverance and requests for all the saints:\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\55:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Evening, morning, and at noon, I will cry out in distress. He will hear my voice.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\102:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  He has responded to the prayer of the destitute, and has not despised their prayer.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\30:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  For the people will dwell in Zion at Jerusalem. You will weep no more. He will surely be gracious to you at the voice of your cry. When he hears you, he will answer you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\6:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  {I}{B}When you pray, you shall not be as the hypocrites, for they love to stand and pray in the synagogues and in the corners of the streets, that they may be seen by men. Most certainly, I tell you, they have received their reward.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\18:18-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  {I}{B}Most certainly I tell you, whatever things you bind on earth will have been bound in heaven, and whatever things you release on earth will have been released in heaven.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}19  {I}{B}Again, assuredly I tell you, that if two of you will agree on earth concerning anything that they will ask, it will be done for them by my Father who is in heaven.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}20  {I}{B}For where two or three are gathered together in my name, there I am in the midst of them.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\14:13-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  {I}{B}Whatever you will ask in my name, that will I do, that the Father may be glorified in the Son.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}14  {I}{B}If you will ask anything in my name, I will do it.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\16:23-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  {I}{B}In that day you will ask me no questions. Most certainly I tell you, whatever you may ask of the Father in my name, he will give it to you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}24  {I}{B}Until now, you have asked nothing in my name. Ask, and you will receive, that your joy may be made full.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\4:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Draw near to God, and he will draw near to you. Cleanse your hands, you sinners; and purify your hearts, you double-minded.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\45:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  Thus says Yahweh, the Holy One of Israel, and his Maker: You ask me about the things that are to come, concerning my sons, and you command me concerning the work of my hands!\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\29:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  You shall seek me, and find me, when you shall search for me with all your heart.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\21:21-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  Jesus answered them, {I}{B}Most certainly I tell you, if you have faith, and don't doubt, you will not only do what was done to the fig tree, but even if you told this mountain, 'Be taken up and cast into the sea,' it would be done.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}22  {I}{B}All things, whatever you ask in prayer, believing, you will receive.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\11:9-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  {I}{B}I tell you, keep asking, and it will be given you. Keep seeking, and you will find. Keep knocking, and it will be opened to you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}10  {I}{B}For everyone who asks receives. He who seeks finds. To him who knocks it will be opened.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\4:20-21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  Yet, looking to the promise of God, he didn't waver through unbelief, but grew strong through faith, giving glory to God,\r {BR}21  and being fully assured that what he had promised, he was able also to perform.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\3:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  Now to him who is able to do exceedingly abundantly above all that we ask or think, according to the power that works in us,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\11:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Without faith it is impossible to be well pleasing to him, for he who comes to God must believe that he exists, and that he is a rewarder of those who seek him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\1:6-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  But let him ask in faith, without any doubting, for he who doubts is like a wave of the sea, driven by the wind and tossed.\r {BR}7  For let that man not think that he will receive anything from the Lord.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\5:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  This is the boldness which we have toward him, that, if we ask anything according to his will, he listens to us.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\5:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Yahweh, in the morning you shall hear my voice. In the morning I will lay my requests before you, and will watch expectantly.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\63:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  God, you are my God. I will earnestly seek you. My soul thirsts for you. My flesh longs for you, in a dry and weary land, where there is no water.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  Blessed are those who keep his statutes, who seek him with their whole heart.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Samuel\\22:5-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  For the waves of death surrounded me. The floods of ungodliness made me afraid.\r {BR}6  The cords of Sheol were around me. The snares of death caught me.\r {BR}7  In my distress I called on Yahweh. Yes, I called to my God. He heard my voice out of his temple. My cry ({I}{B}came{/B}{/I}) into his ears.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\22:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  For he has not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the afflicted, Neither has he hidden his face from him; but when he cried to him, he heard.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\50:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Call on me in the day of trouble. I will deliver you, and you will honor me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\62:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Trust in him at all times, you people. Pour out your heart before him. God is a refuge for us. Selah.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\106:44-45{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}44  Nevertheless he regarded their distress, when he heard their cry.\r {BR}45  He remembered for them his covenant, and repented according to the multitude of his loving kindnesses.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  With my whole heart, I have sought you. Don't let me wander from your commandments.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\55:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Seek Yahweh while he may be found; call you on him while he is near:\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\64:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  There is none who calls on your name, who stirs up himself to take hold of you; for you have hid your face from us, and have consumed us by means of our iniquities.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Lamentations\\2:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  Arise, cry out in the night, at the beginning of the watches; Pour out your heart like water before the face of the Lord: Lift up your hands toward him for the life of your young children, that faint for hunger at the head of every street.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Lamentations\\3:40-41{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}40  Let us search and try our ways, and turn again to Yahweh.\r {BR}41  Let us lift up our heart with our hands to God in the heavens.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Joel\\2:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  Yet even now, says Yahweh, turn to me with all your heart, and with fasting, and with weeping, and with mourning.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\17:21-21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  {I}{B}But this kind doesn't go out except by prayer and fasting.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Disagreeableness",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\15:1",id:"33",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\15:1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  A gentle answer turns away wrath, but a harsh word stirs up anger.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Satisfaction",lessonscriptures:"Luke\\12:19",id:"34",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\12:19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  {I}{B}I will tell my soul, Soul, you have many goods laid up for many years. Take your ease, eat, drink, be merry. '{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Confusion",lessonscriptures:"Jeremiah\\3:25",id:"35",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\3:25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  Let us lie down in our shame, and let our confusion cover us; for we have sinned against Yahweh our God, we and our fathers, from our youth even to this day; and we have not obeyed the voice of Yahweh our God.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Ugliness",lessonscriptures:"1 Corinthians\\13:5",id:"36",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\13:5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  doesn't behave itself inappropriately, doesn't seek its own way, is not provoked, takes no account of evil;\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Malice",lessonscriptures:"1 Peter\\2:1",id:"37",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\2:1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Putting away therefore all wickedness, all deceit, hypocrisies, envies, and all evil speaking,\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Gloominess",lessonscriptures:"Matthew\\6:16",id:"38",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\6:16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  {I}{B}Moreover when you fast, don't be like the hypocrites, with sad faces. For they disfigure their faces, that they may be seen by men to be fasting. Most certainly I tell you, they have received their reward.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Vacillation",lessonscriptures:"Galatians\\1:6",id:"39",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Galatians\\1:6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  I marvel that you are so quickly deserting him who called you in the grace of Christ to a different good news;\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Fear",lessonscriptures:"Philippians\\2:12",id:"40",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\2:12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  So then, my beloved, even as you have always obeyed, not only in my presence, but now much more in my absence, work out your own salvation with fear and trembling.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Dissatisfaction",lessonscriptures:"Exodus\\16:3",id:"41",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Exodus\\16:3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  and the children of Israel said to them, We wish that we had died by the hand of Yahweh in the land of Egypt, when we sat by the meat pots, when we ate our fill of bread, for you have brought us out into this wilderness, to kill this whole assembly with hunger.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Cowardice",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\29:25",id:"42",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\29:25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  The fear of man proves to be a snare, but whoever puts his trust in Yahweh is kept safe.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Discourtesy",lessonscriptures:"1 Corinthians\\13:5",id:"43",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\13:5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  doesn't behave itself inappropriately, doesn't seek its own way, is not provoked, takes no account of evil;\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Indecision",lessonscriptures:"James\\1:8",id:"44",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\James\\1:8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  He is a double-minded man, unstable in all his ways.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Impudence",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\7:13",id:"45",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\7:13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  So she caught him, and kissed him. With an impudent face she said to him:\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Dullness",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\6:6",id:"46",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\6:6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Go to the ant, you sluggard. Consider her ways, and be wise;\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Imprudence",lessonscriptures:"Ecclesiastes\\5:2",id:"47",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Ecclesiastes\\5:2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  Don't be rash with your mouth, and don't let your heart be hasty to utter anything before God; for God is in heaven, and you on earth. Therefore let your words be few.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Discouragement",lessonscriptures:"Colossians\\3:21",id:"48",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Colossians\\3:21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  Fathers, don't provoke your children, so that they won't be discouraged.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Darkness",lessonscriptures:"Micah\\3:6",id:"49",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Micah\\3:6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Therefore night is over you, with no vision, and it is dark to you, that you may not divine; and the sun will go down on the prophets, and the day will be black over them.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Indifference",lessonscriptures:"Isaiah\\1:3",id:"50",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\1:3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  The ox knows his owner, and the donkey his master's crib; but Israel doesn't know, my people don't consider.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Suspicion",lessonscriptures:"Song of Solomon\\8:6",id:"51",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Song of Solomon\\8:6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Set me as a seal on your heart, as a seal on your arm; for love is strong as death. Jealousy is as cruel as Sheol. Its flashes are flashes of fire, a very flame of Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Rashness",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\19:2",id:"52",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\19:2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  It isn't good to have zeal without knowledge; nor being hasty with one's feet and missing the way.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Improvidence",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\18:9",id:"53",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\18:9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  One who is slack in his work is brother to him who is a master of destruction.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Misery",lessonscriptures:"Romans\\2:9",id:"54",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\2:9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  oppression and anguish, on every soul of man who works evil, to the Jew first, and also to the Greek.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Dishonesty",lessonscriptures:"2 Corinthians\\4:2",id:"55",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\4:2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  But we have renounced the hidden things of shame, not walking in craftiness, nor handling the word of God deceitfully; but by the manifestation of the truth commending ourselves to every man's conscience in the sight of God.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Dishonor",lessonscriptures:"Romans\\2:23",id:"56",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\2:23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  You who glory in the law, through your disobedience of the law do you dishonor God?\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Despair",lessonscriptures:"Ephesians\\2:12",id:"57",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\2:12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  that you were at that time separate from Christ, alienated from the commonwealth of Israel, and strangers from the covenants of the promise, having no hope and without God in the world.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Inaction",lessonscriptures:"Deuteronomy\\1:6",id:"58",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\1:6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Yahweh our God spoke to us in Horeb, saying, You have lived long enough in this mountain:\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Stupidity",lessonscriptures:"Luke\\12:20",id:"59",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\12:20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  {I}{B}But God said to him, 'You foolish one, tonight your soul is required of you. The things which you have prepared-whose will they be?'{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Sorrow",lessonscriptures:"2 Corinthians\\7:10",id:"60",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\7:10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  For godly sorrow works repentance to salvation, which brings no regret. But the sorrow of the world works death.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Indiscrimination",lessonscriptures:"Matthew\\7:3-6",id:"61",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\7:3-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  {I}{B}Why do you see the speck that is in your brother's eye, but don't consider the beam that is in your own eye?{/B}{/I}\r {BR}4  {I}{B}Or how will you tell your brother, 'Let me remove the speck from your eye;' and behold, the beam is in your own eye?{/B}{/I}\r {BR}5  {I}{B}You hypocrite! First remove the beam out of your own eye, and then you can see clearly to remove the speck out of your brother's eye.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}6  {I}{B}Don't give that which is holy to the dogs, neither throw your pearls before the pigs, lest perhaps they trample them under their feet, and turn and tear you to pieces.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Injustice",lessonscriptures:"Job\\17:16",id:"62",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Job\\17:16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  Shall it go down with me to the gates of Sheol, or descend together into the dust?\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Harshness",lessonscriptures:"Hebrews\\11:36",id:"63",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\11:36{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}36  Others were tried by mocking and scourging, yes, moreover by bonds and imprisonment.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Ignorance",lessonscriptures:"Romans\\10:3",id:"64",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\10:3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  For being ignorant of God's righteousness, and seeking to establish their own righteousness, they didn't subject themselves to the righteousness of God.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Stinginess",lessonscriptures:"2 Corinthians\\9:6-7",id:"65",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\9:6-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Remember this: he who sows sparingly will also reap sparingly. He who sows bountifully will also reap bountifully.\r {BR}7  Let each man give according as he has determined in his heart; not grudgingly, or under compulsion; for God loves a cheerful giver.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Hate",lessonscriptures:"Galatians\\5:20",id:"66",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Galatians\\5:20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  idolatry, sorcery, hatred, strife, jealousies, outbursts of anger, rivalries, divisions, heresies,\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Disloyalty",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\25:19",id:"67",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\25:19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  Confidence in someone unfaithful in time of trouble is like a bad tooth, or a lame foot.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Immorality",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\6:24-26",id:"68",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\6:24-26{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  to keep you from the immoral woman, from the flattery of the wayward wife's tongue.\r {BR}25  Don't lust after her beauty in your heart, neither let her captivate you with her eyelids.\r {BR}26  For a prostitute reduces you to a piece of bread. The adulteress hunts for your precious life.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Insubordination",lessonscriptures:"Hebrews\\4:7",id:"69",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\4:7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  he again defines a certain day, today, saying through David so long a time afterward  (just as has been said), Today if you will hear his voice, don't harden your hearts.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Heedlessness",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\29:1",id:"70",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\29:1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  He who is often rebuked and stiffens his neck will be destroyed suddenly, with no remedy.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Egotism",lessonscriptures:"Romans\\12:16",id:"71",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\12:16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  Be of the same mind one toward another. Don't set your mind on high things, but associate with the humble. Don't be wise in your own conceits.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Pessimism",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\13:1-2",id:"72",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\13:1-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  How long, Yahweh? Will you forget me forever? How long will you hide your face from me?\r {BR}2  How long shall I take counsel in my soul, having sorrow in my heart every day? How long shall my enemy triumph over me?\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Impatience",lessonscriptures:"1 Samuel\\13:11-13",id:"73",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Samuel\\13:11-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  Samuel said, What have you done? Saul said, Because I saw that the people were scattered from me, and that you didn't come within the days appointed, and that the Philistines assembled themselves together at Michmash;\r {BR}12  therefore said I, Now will the Philistines come down on me to Gilgal, and I haven't entreated the favor of Yahweh: I forced myself therefore, and offered the burnt offering.\r {BR}13  Samuel said to Saul, You have done foolishly; you have not kept the commandment of Yahweh your God, which he commanded you: for now would Yahweh have established your kingdom on Israel forever.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Treason",lessonscriptures:"1 Kings\\16:19-20",id:"74",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Kings\\16:19-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  for his sins which he sinned in doing that which was evil in the sight of Yahweh, in walking in the way of Jeroboam, and in his sin which he did, to make Israel to sin.\r {BR}20  Now the rest of the acts of Zimri, and his treason that he did, aren't they written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel?\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Hesitation",lessonscriptures:"1 Kings\\18:21",id:"75",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Kings\\18:21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  Elijah came near to all the people, and said, How long will you waver between the two sides? If Yahweh is God, follow him; but if Baal, then follow him. The people answered him not a word.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Incivility",lessonscriptures:"1 Corinthians\\13:5",id:"76",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\13:5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  doesn't behave itself inappropriately, doesn't seek its own way, is not provoked, takes no account of evil;\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Irresolution",lessonscriptures:"2 Timothy\\3:7",id:"77",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\2 Timothy\\3:7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  always learning, and never able to come to the knowledge of the truth.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Imbecility",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\10:10",id:"78",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\10:10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  One winking with the eye causes sorrow, but a chattering fool will fall.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Atheism",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\14:1",id:"79",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\14:1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  The fool has said in his heart, There is no God. They are corrupt. They have done abominable works. There is none who does good.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Deprivation",lessonscriptures:"Matthew\\25:28-29",id:"80",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\25:28-29{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  {I}{B}Take away therefore the talent from him, and give it to him who has the ten talents.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}29  {I}{B}For to everyone who has will be given, and he will have abundance, but from him who doesn't have, even that which he has will be taken away.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Impulsiveness",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\25:8",id:"81",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\25:8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Don't be hasty in bringing charges to court. What will you do in the end when your neighbor shames you?\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Debasement",lessonscriptures:"Isaiah\\57:9",id:"82",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\57:9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  You went to the king with oil, and did increase your perfumes, and did send your ambassadors far off, and did debase yourself even to Sheol.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Insincerity",lessonscriptures:"Philippians\\1:16",id:"83",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\1:16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  The former insincerely preach Christ from selfish ambition, thinking that they add affliction to my chains;\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Uncompassionateness",lessonscriptures:"Ephesians\\4:19",id:"84",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\4:19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  who having become callous gave themselves up to lust, to work all uncleanness with greediness.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Carelessness",lessonscriptures:"Isaiah\\47:8",id:"85",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\47:8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Now therefore hear this, you who are given to pleasures, who sit securely, who say in your heart, I am, and there is none else besides me; I shall not sit as a widow, neither shall I know the loss of children:\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Indiscretion",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\11:22",id:"86",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\11:22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  Like a gold ring in a pig's snout, is a beautiful woman who lacks discretion.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Inexorability",lessonscriptures:"Jeremiah\\6:10",id:"87",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\6:10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  To whom shall I speak and testify, that they may hear? behold, their ear is uncircumcised, and they can't listen: behold, the word of Yahweh is become to them a reproach; they have no delight in it.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Intemperance",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\23:29-30",id:"88",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\23:29-30{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}29  Who has woe? Who has sorrow? Who has strife? Who has complaints? Who has needless bruises? Who has bloodshot eyes?\r {BR}30  Those who stay long at the wine; those who go to seek out mixed wine.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Aimlessness",lessonscriptures:"Jude\\1:13",id:"89",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Jude\\1:13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  wild waves of the sea, foaming out their own shame; wandering stars, for whom the blackness of darkness has been reserved forever.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Extravagance",lessonscriptures:"Luke\\15:12-17",id:"90",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\15:12-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  {I}{B}The younger of them said to his father, 'Father, give me my share of your property.' He divided his livelihood between them.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}13  {I}{B}Not many days after, the younger son gathered all of this together and traveled into a far country. There he wasted his property with riotous living.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}14  {I}{B}When he had spent all of it, there arose a severe famine in that country, and he began to be in need.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}15  {I}{B}He went and joined himself to one of the citizens of that country, and he sent him into his fields to feed pigs.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}16  {I}{B}He wanted to fill his belly with the husks that the pigs ate, but no one gave him any.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}17  {I}{B}But when he came to himself he said, 'How many hired servants of my father's have bread enough to spare, and I'm dying with hunger!{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Falsehood",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\20:17",id:"91",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\20:17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Fraudulent food is sweet to a man, but afterwards his mouth is filled with gravel.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Selfishness",lessonscriptures:"1 Corinthians\\13:5",id:"92",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\13:5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  doesn't behave itself inappropriately, doesn't seek its own way, is not provoked, takes no account of evil;\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Foolishness",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\15:14",id:"93",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\15:14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  The heart of one who has understanding seeks knowledge, but the mouths of fools feed on folly.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Laziness",lessonscriptures:"Romans\\12:11",id:"94",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\12:11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  not lagging in diligence; fervent in spirit; serving the Lord;\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Our Salvation",lessonscriptures:"John\\3:16-16;Romans\\3:23-23;Romans\\6:23-23;John\\14:6-6;John\\1:12-12;John\\3:3-3;Hebrews\\9:22-22;Matthew\\18:3-3;Revelation\\3:20-20;1 John\\1:9-9;Romans\\10:9-13;Ephesians\\2:8-9;Titus\\3:5-5;Acts\\16:31-31;John\\3:36-36;John\\10:28-28;2 Corinthians\\5:17-17",id:"95",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\John\\3:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  {I}{B}For God so loved the world, that he gave his one and only Son, that whoever believes in him should not perish, but have eternal life.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\3:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  for all have sinned, and fall short of the glory of God;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\6:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  For the wages of sin is death, but the free gift of God is eternal life in Christ Jesus our Lord.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\14:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Jesus said to him, {I}{B}I am the way, the truth, and the life. No one comes to the Father, except through me.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\1:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  But as many as received him, to them he gave the right to become God's children, to those who believe in his name:\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\3:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Jesus answered him, {I}{B}Most certainly, I tell you, unless one is born anew, he can't see the Kingdom of God.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\9:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  According to the law, nearly everything is cleansed with blood, and apart from shedding of blood there is no remission.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\18:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  and said, {I}{B}Most certainly I tell you, unless you turn, and become as little children, you will in no way enter into the Kingdom of Heaven.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Revelation\\3:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  {I}{B}Behold, I stand at the door and knock. If anyone hears my voice and opens the door, then I will come in to him, and will dine with him, and he with me.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\1:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  If we confess our sins, he is faithful and righteous to forgive us the sins, and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\10:9-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  that if you will confess with your mouth that Jesus is Lord, and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.\r {BR}10  For with the heart, one believes unto righteousness; and with the mouth confession is made unto salvation.\r {BR}11  For the Scripture says, Whoever believes in him will not be disappointed.\r {BR}12  For there is no distinction between Jew and Greek; for the same Lord is Lord of all, and is rich to all who call on him.\r {BR}13  For, Whoever will call on the name of the Lord will be saved.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\2:8-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  for by grace you have been saved through faith, and that not of yourselves; it is the gift of God,\r {BR}9  not of works, that no one would boast.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Titus\\3:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  not by works of righteousness, which we did ourselves, but according to his mercy, he saved us, through the washing of regeneration and renewing by the Holy Spirit,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Acts\\16:31-31{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}31  They said, Believe in the Lord Jesus Christ, and you will be saved, you and your household.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\3:36-36{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}36  One who believes in the Son has eternal life, but one who disobeys the Son won't see life, but the wrath of God remains on him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\10:28-28{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  {I}{B}I give eternal life to them. They will never perish, and no one will snatch them out of my hand.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\5:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Therefore if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation. The old things have passed away. Behold, all things have become new.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Praise",lessonscriptures:"Nehemiah\\8:10-10;Psalms\\34:1-1;Psalms\\50:23-23;Psalms\\150;Psalms\\89:15-15;Psalms\\100:1-2;Psalms\\97:1-1;Psalms\\97:12-12;Psalms\\103:1-2;Psalms\\149:1-5;Acts\\16:25-25;2 Chronicles\\20:21-22;1 Thessalonians\\5:18-18;Hebrews\\13:15-15;Psalms\\71:8-8;Psalms\\71:14-14;Psalms\\113:3-3;Ephesians\\5:19-20;Revelation\\19:5-5",id:"96",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Nehemiah\\8:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Then he said to them, Go your way, eat the fat, and drink the sweet, and send portions to him for whom nothing is prepared; for this day is holy to our Lord. Don't be grieved; for the joy of Yahweh is your strength.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  I will bless Yahweh at all times. His praise will always be in my mouth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\50:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  Whoever offers the sacrifice of thanksgiving glorifies me, and prepares his way so that I will show God's salvation to him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\150{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Praise Yah! Praise God in his sanctuary! Praise him in his heavens for his acts of power!\r {BR}2  Praise him for his mighty acts! Praise him according to his excellent greatness!\r {BR}3  Praise him with the sounding of the trumpet! Praise him with harp and lyre!\r {BR}4  Praise him with tambourine and dancing! Praise him with stringed instruments and flute!\r {BR}5  Praise him with loud cymbals! Praise him with resounding cymbals!\r {BR}6  Let everything that has breath praise Yah! Praise Yah!\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\89:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Blessed are the people who learn to acclaim you. They walk in the light of your presence, Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\100:1-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Shout for joy to Yahweh, all you lands!\r {BR}2  Serve Yahweh with gladness. Come before his presence with singing.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\97:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Yahweh reigns! Let the earth rejoice! Let the multitude of islands be glad!\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\97:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  Be glad in Yahweh, you righteous people! Give thanks to his holy Name.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\103:1-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Praise Yahweh, my soul! All that is within me, praise his holy name!\r {BR}2  Praise Yahweh, my soul, and don't forget all his benefits;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\149:1-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Praise Yahweh! Sing to Yahweh a new song, his praise in the assembly of the saints.\r {BR}2  Let Israel rejoice in him who made them. Let the children of Zion be joyful in their King.\r {BR}3  Let them praise his name in the dance! Let them sing praises to him with tambourine and harp!\r {BR}4  For Yahweh takes pleasure in his people. He crowns the humble with salvation.\r {BR}5  Let the saints rejoice in honor. Let them sing for joy on their beds.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Acts\\16:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  But about midnight Paul and Silas were praying and singing hymns to God, and the prisoners were listening to them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Chronicles\\20:21-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  When he had taken counsel with the people, he appointed those who should sing to Yahweh, and give praise in holy array, as they went out before the army, and say, Give thanks to Yahweh; for his loving kindness endures forever.\r {BR}22  When they began to sing and to praise, Yahweh set ambushers against the children of Ammon, Moab, and Mount Seir, who had come against Judah; and they were struck.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Thessalonians\\5:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  In everything give thanks, for this is the will of God in Christ Jesus toward you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\13:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Through him, then, let us offer up a sacrifice of praise to God continually, that is, the fruit of lips which proclaim allegiance to his name.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\71:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  My mouth shall be filled with your praise, with your honor all the day.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\71:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  But I will always hope, and will add to all of your praise.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\113:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  From the rising of the sun to the going down of the same, Yahweh's name is to be praised.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\5:19-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  speaking to one another in psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs; singing, and making melody in your heart to the Lord;\r {BR}20  giving thanks always concerning all things in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, to God, even the Father;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Revelation\\19:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  A voice came forth from the throne, saying, Give praise to our God, all you his servants, you who fear him, the small and the great!\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Faith",lessonscriptures:"Romans\\10:17-17;Proverbs\\3:5-6;Mark\\9:23-23;2 Corinthians\\5:17-17;Luke\\1:37-37;Matthew\\9:29-29;Hebrews\\11:1-1;James\\1:5-8;Hebrews\\11:6-6;James\\2:26-26;Romans\\14:23-23;Hebrews\\10:38-38;Job\\13:15-15;Isaiah\\30:15-15;2 Timothy\\2:13-13;1 John\\5:4-4;Ephesians\\6:16-16;Matthew\\17:20-20;Hebrews\\12:2-2;Romans\\5:1-1;Mark\\11:22-22;1 Peter\\1:6-9",id:"97",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\10:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  So faith comes by hearing, and hearing by the word of God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:5-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Trust in Yahweh with all your heart, and don't lean on your own understanding.\r {BR}6  In all your ways acknowledge him, and he will make your paths straight.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Mark\\9:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  Jesus said to him, {I}{B}If you can believe, all things are possible to him who believes.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\5:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Therefore if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation. The old things have passed away. Behold, all things have become new.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\1:37-37{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}37  For everything spoken by God is possible.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\9:29-29{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}29  Then he touched their eyes, saying, {I}{B}According to your faith be it done to you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\11:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Now faith is assurance of things hoped for, proof of things not seen.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\1:5-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  But if any of you lacks wisdom, let him ask of God, who gives to all liberally and without reproach; and it will be given to him.\r {BR}6  But let him ask in faith, without any doubting, for he who doubts is like a wave of the sea, driven by the wind and tossed.\r {BR}7  For let that man not think that he will receive anything from the Lord.\r {BR}8  He is a double-minded man, unstable in all his ways.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\11:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Without faith it is impossible to be well pleasing to him, for he who comes to God must believe that he exists, and that he is a rewarder of those who seek him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\2:26-26{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}26  For as the body apart from the spirit is dead, even so faith apart from works is dead.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\14:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  But he who doubts is condemned if he eats, because it isn't of faith; and whatever is not of faith is sin.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\10:38-38{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}38  But the righteous will live by faith. If he shrinks back, my soul has no pleasure in him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Job\\13:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Behold, he will kill me. I have no hope. Nevertheless, I will maintain my ways before him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\30:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  For thus said the Lord Yahweh, the Holy One of Israel, You will be saved in returning and rest. Your strength will be in quietness and in confidence. You refused,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Timothy\\2:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  If we are faithless, he remains faithful. He can't deny himself.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\5:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  For whatever is born of God overcomes the world. This is the victory that has overcome the world: your faith.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\6:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  above all, taking up the shield of faith, with which you will be able to quench all the fiery darts of the evil one.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\17:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  He said to them, {I}{B}Because of your unbelief. For most certainly I tell you, if you have faith as a grain of mustard seed, you will tell this mountain, 'Move from here to there,' and it will move; and nothing will be impossible for you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\12:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  looking to Jesus, the author and perfecter of faith, who for the joy that was set before him endured the cross, despising its shame, and has sat down at the right hand of the throne of God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\5:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Being therefore justified by faith, we have peace with God through our Lord Jesus Christ;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Mark\\11:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  Jesus answered them, {I}{B}Have faith in God.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\1:6-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Wherein you greatly rejoice, though now for a little while, if need be, you have been put to grief in various trials,\r {BR}7  that the proof of your faith, which is more precious than gold that perishes even though it is tested by fire, may be found to result in praise, glory, and honor at the revelation of Jesus Christ--\r {BR}8  whom not having known you love; in whom, though now you don't see him, yet believing, you rejoice greatly with joy unspeakable and full of glory--\r {BR}9  receiving the result of your faith, the salvation of your souls.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Love",lessonscriptures:"1 Corinthians\\13:13-13;Matthew\\22:37-40;John\\3:16-16;1 Peter\\4:8-8;1 John\\3:16-18;1 John\\4:7-8;Galatians\\5:14-14;John\\14:15-15;Matthew\\25:40-40;Matthew\\7:12-12;Colossians\\3:13-14;1 Corinthians\\16:14-14;John\\15:13-13;1 John\\4:19-19;Romans\\8:38-39;John\\13:34-35;John\\14:21-24;Romans\\12:9-9;1 John\\4:11-11;1 John\\4:21-21",id:"98",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\13:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  But now faith, hope, and love remain--these three. The greatest of these is love.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\22:37-40{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}37  Jesus said to him, {I}{B} 'You shall love the Lord your God with all your heart, with all your soul, and with all your mind.'{/B}{/I}\r {BR}38  {I}{B}This is the first and great commandment.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}39  {I}{B}A second likewise is this, 'You shall love your neighbor as yourself.'{/B}{/I}\r {BR}40  {I}{B}The whole law and the prophets depend on these two commandments.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\3:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  {I}{B}For God so loved the world, that he gave his one and only Son, that whoever believes in him should not perish, but have eternal life.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\4:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  And above all things be earnest in your love among yourselves, for love covers a multitude of sins.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\3:16-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  By this we know love, because he laid down his life for us. And we ought to lay down our lives for the brothers.\r {BR}17  But whoever has the world's goods, and sees his brother in need, and closes his heart of compassion against him, how does the love of God remain in him?\r {BR}18  My little children, let's not love in word only, neither with the tongue only, but in deed and truth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\4:7-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Beloved, let us love one another, for love is of God; and everyone who loves is born of God, and knows God.\r {BR}8  He who doesn't love doesn't know God, for God is love.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Galatians\\5:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  For the whole law is fulfilled in one word, in this: You shall love your neighbor as yourself.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\14:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  {I}{B}If you love me, keep my commandments.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\25:40-40{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}40  {I}{B}The King will answer them, 'Most certainly I tell you, inasmuch as you did it to one of the least of these my brothers, you did it to me.'{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\7:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  {I}{B}Therefore whatever you desire for men to do to you, you shall also do to them; for this is the law and the prophets.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Colossians\\3:13-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  bearing with one another, and forgiving each other, if any man has a complaint against any; even as Christ forgave you, so you also do.\r {BR}14  Above all these things, walk in love, which is the bond of perfection.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\16:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  Let all that you do be done in love.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\15:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  {I}{B}Greater love has no one than this, that someone lay down his life for his friends.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\4:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  We love him, because he first loved us.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\8:38-39{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}38  For I am persuaded, that neither death, nor life, nor angels, nor principalities, nor things present, nor things to come, nor powers,\r {BR}39  nor height, nor depth, nor any other created thing, will be able to separate us from the love of God, which is in Christ Jesus our Lord.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\13:34-35{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}34  {I}{B}A new commandment I give to you, that you love one another, just like I have loved you; that you also love one another.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}35  {I}{B}By this everyone will know that you are my disciples, if you have love for one another.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\14:21-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  {I}{B}One who has my commandments, and keeps them, that person is one who loves me. One who loves me will be loved by my Father, and I will love him, and will reveal myself to him.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}22  Judas (not Iscariot) said to him, Lord, what has happened that you are about to reveal yourself to us, and not to the world?\r {BR}23  Jesus answered him, {I}{B}If a man loves me, he will keep my word. My Father will love him, and we will come to him, and make our home with him.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}24  {I}{B}He who doesn't love me doesn't keep my words. The word which you hear isn't mine, but the Father's who sent me.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\12:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  Let love be without hypocrisy. Abhor that which is evil. Cling to that which is good.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\4:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  Beloved, if God loved us in this way, we also ought to love one another.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\4:21-21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  This commandment we have from him, that he who loves God should also love his brother.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"The Word",lessonscriptures:"John\\1:1-14;Matthew\\4:4-4;Psalms\\119:11-11;John\\15:3-3;Psalms\\119:130-130;2 Timothy\\2:15-15;Hebrews\\4:12-12;John\\6:63-63;Matthew\\24:35-35;1 Peter\\2:2-2",id:"99",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\John\\1:1-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God.\r {BR}2  The same was in the beginning with God.\r {BR}3  All things were made through him. Without him was not anything made that has been made.\r {BR}4  In him was life, and the life was the light of men.\r {BR}5  The light shines in the darkness, and the darkness hasn't overcome it.\r {BR}6  There came a man, sent from God, whose name was John.\r {BR}7  The same came as a witness, that he might testify about the light, that all might believe through him.\r {BR}8  He was not the light, but was sent that he might testify about the light.\r {BR}9  The true light that enlightens everyone was coming into the world.\r {BR}10  He was in the world, and the world was made through him, and the world didn't recognize him.\r {BR}11  He came to his own, and those who were his own didn't receive him.\r {BR}12  But as many as received him, to them he gave the right to become God's children, to those who believe in his name:\r {BR}13  who were born not of blood, nor of the will of the flesh, nor of the will of man, but of God.\r {BR}14  The Word became flesh, and lived among us. We saw his glory, such glory as of the one and only Son of the Father, full of grace and truth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\4:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  But he answered, {I}{B}It is written, 'Man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word that proceeds out of the mouth of God.' {/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  I have hidden your word in my heart, that I might not sin against you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\15:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  {I}{B}You are already pruned clean because of the word which I have spoken to you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:130-130{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}130  The entrance of your words gives light. It gives understanding to the simple.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Timothy\\2:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Give diligence to present yourself approved by God, a workman who doesn't need to be ashamed, properly handling the Word of Truth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\4:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  For the word of God is living, and active, and sharper than any two-edged sword, and piercing even to the dividing of soul and spirit, of both joints and marrow, and is able to discern the thoughts and intentions of the heart.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\6:63-63{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}63  {I}{B}It is the spirit who gives life. The flesh profits nothing. The words that I speak to you are spirit, and are life.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\24:35-35{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}35  {I}{B}Heaven and earth will pass away, but my words will not pass away.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\2:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  as newborn babies, long for the pure milk of the Word, that you may grow thereby,\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Freedom from Fear",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\27:1-5;Psalms\\34:4-4;Proverbs\\1:33-33;Isaiah\\35:4-4;Isaiah\\41:10-10;Romans\\8:15-15;2 Timothy\\1:7-7;Psalms\\46:1-3;Psalms\\56:3-4;Psalms\\91:5-6;Proverbs\\3:24-24;Jeremiah\\1:8-8;1 John\\4:18-18;Hebrews\\13:5-6;John\\14:27-27;Hebrews\\2:14-15",id:"100",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\27:1-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Yahweh is my light and my salvation. Whom shall I fear? Yahweh is the strength of my life. Of whom shall I be afraid?\r {BR}2  When evildoers came at me to eat up my flesh, even my adversaries and my foes, they stumbled and fell.\r {BR}3  Though an army should encamp against me, my heart shall not fear. Though war should rise against me, even then I will be confident.\r {BR}4  One thing I have asked of Yahweh, that I will seek after, that I may dwell in the house of Yahweh all the days of my life, to see Yahweh's beauty, and to inquire in his temple.\r {BR}5  For in the day of trouble he will keep me secretly in his pavilion. In the covert of his tabernacle he will hide me. He will lift me up on a rock.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  I sought Yahweh, and he answered me, and delivered me from all my fears.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\1:33-33{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}33  But whoever listens to me will dwell securely, and will be at ease, without fear of harm.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\35:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  Tell those who have a fearful heart, Be strong. Don't be afraid. Behold, your God will come with vengeance, God's retribution. He will come and save you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\41:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Don't you be afraid, for I am with you. Don't be dismayed, for I am your God. I will strengthen you. Yes, I will help you. Yes, I will uphold you with the right hand of my righteousness.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\8:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  For you didn't receive the spirit of bondage again to fear, but you received the Spirit of adoption, by whom we cry, Abba! Father!\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Timothy\\1:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  For God didn't give us a spirit of fear, but of power, love, and self-control.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\46:1-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  God is our refuge and strength, a very present help in trouble.\r {BR}2  Therefore we won't be afraid, though the earth changes, though the mountains are shaken into the heart of the seas;\r {BR}3  though its waters roar and are troubled, though the mountains tremble with their swelling. Selah.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\56:3-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  When I am afraid, I will put my trust in you.\r {BR}4  In God, I praise his word. In God, I put my trust. I will not be afraid. What can flesh do to me?\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\91:5-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  You shall not be afraid of the terror by night, nor of the arrow that flies by day;\r {BR}6  nor of the pestilence that walks in darkness, nor of the destruction that wastes at noonday.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  When you lie down, you will not be afraid. Yes, you will lie down, and your sleep will be sweet.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\1:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Don't be afraid because of them; for I am with you to deliver you, says Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\4:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  There is no fear in love; but perfect love casts out fear, because fear has punishment. He who fears is not made perfect in love.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\13:5-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Be free from the love of money, content with such things as you have, for he has said, I will in no way leave you, neither will I in any way forsake you.\r {BR}6  So that with good courage we say, The Lord is my helper. I will not fear. What can man do to me?\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\14:27-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}27  {I}{B}Peace I leave with you. My peace I give to you; not as the world gives, give I to you. Don't let your heart be troubled, neither let it be fearful.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\2:14-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  Since then the children have shared in flesh and blood, he also himself in like manner partook of the same, that through death he might bring to nothing him who had the power of death, that is, the devil,\r {BR}15  and might deliver all of them who through fear of death were all their lifetime subject to bondage.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Supply",lessonscriptures:"1 Timothy\\6:10-10;Matthew\\6:33-33;Malachi\\3:8-10;Philippians\\4:19-19;Psalms\\37:25-25;1 John\\5:14-15;Psalms\\23:1-1;Psalms\\34:10-10;Psalms\\68:19-19;Psalms\\81:10-10;Psalms\\84:11-11;Psalms\\145:15-16;Proverbs\\13:25-25;Isaiah\\1:19-20;Ezekiel\\34:26-26;Matthew\\6:8-8;Matthew\\7:7-8;Matthew\\7:11-11;Matthew\\21:22-22;Luke\\22:35-35;1 Corinthians\\-9:14-14;1 John\\3:22-22",id:"101",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Timothy\\6:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  For the love of money is a root of all kinds of evil. Some have been led astray from the faith in their greed, and have pierced themselves through with many sorrows.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\6:33-33{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}33  {I}{B}But seek first God's Kingdom, and his righteousness; and all these things will be given to you as well.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Malachi\\3:8-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Will a man rob God? Yet you rob me! But you say, 'How have we robbed you?' In tithes and offerings.\r {BR}9  You are cursed with the curse; for you rob me, even this whole nation.\r {BR}10  Bring the whole tithe into the storehouse, that there may be food in my house, and test me now in this, says Yahweh of Armies, if I will not open you the windows of heaven, and pour you out a blessing, that there shall not be room enough for.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\4:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  My God will supply every need of yours according to his riches in glory in Christ Jesus.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\37:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  I have been young, and now am old, yet I have not seen the righteous forsaken, nor his children begging for bread.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\5:14-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  This is the boldness which we have toward him, that, if we ask anything according to his will, he listens to us.\r {BR}15  And if we know that he listens to us, whatever we ask, we know that we have the petitions which we have asked of him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\23:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Yahweh is my shepherd: I shall lack nothing.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  The young lions do lack, and suffer hunger, but those who seek Yahweh shall not lack any good thing.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\68:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  Blessed be the Lord, who daily bears our burdens, even the God who is our salvation. Selah.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\81:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  I am Yahweh, your God, who brought you up out of the land of Egypt. Open your mouth wide, and I will fill it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\84:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  For Yahweh God is a sun and a shield. Yahweh will give grace and glory. He withholds no good thing from those who walk blamelessly.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\145:15-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  The eyes of all wait for you. You give them their food in due season.\r {BR}16  You open your hand, and satisfy the desire of every living thing.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\13:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  The righteous one eats to the satisfying of his soul, but the belly of the wicked goes hungry.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\1:19-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  If you are willing and obedient, you shall eat the good of the land;\r {BR}20  but if you refuse and rebel, you shall be devoured with the sword; for the mouth of Yahweh has spoken it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ezekiel\\34:26-26{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}26  I will make them and the places around my hill a blessing; and I will cause the shower to come down in its season; there shall be showers of blessing.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\6:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  {I}{B}Therefore don't be like them, for your Father knows what things you need, before you ask him.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\7:7-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  {I}{B}Ask, and it will be given you. Seek, and you will find. Knock, and it will be opened for you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}8  {I}{B}For everyone who asks receives. He who seeks finds. To him who knocks it will be opened.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\7:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  {I}{B}If you then, being evil, know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more will your Father who is in heaven give good things to those who ask him!{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\21:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  {I}{B}All things, whatever you ask in prayer, believing, you will receive.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\22:35-35{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}35  He said to them, {I}{B}When I sent you out without purse, and wallet, and shoes, did you lack anything?{/B}{/I} They said, Nothing.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\-9:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\3:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  and whatever we ask, we receive from him, because we keep his commandments and do the things that are pleasing in his sight.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Forgiveness",lessonscriptures:"Matthew\\6:14-15;Luke\\23:34-34;John\\8:11-11;Isaiah\\43:25-25;Matthew\\5:7-7;Hebrews\\8:12-12;Matthew\\18:21-22;1 John\\1:9-9;Psalms\\103:12-12;Leviticus\\19:18-18;Psalms\\18:25-25;Psalms\\86:5-5;Proverbs\\3:3-4;Matthew\\18:35-35;Mark\\11:25-25;Luke\\6:37-37;Ephesians\\4:32-32;Colossians\\3:13-13;Hebrews\\12:15-15",id:"102",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\6:14-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  {I}{B}For if you forgive men their trespasses, your heavenly Father will also forgive you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}15  {I}{B}But if you don't forgive men their trespasses, neither will your Father forgive your trespasses.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\23:34-34{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}34  Jesus said, {I}{B}Father, forgive them, for they don't know what they are doing.{/B}{/I} Dividing his garments among them, they cast lots.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\8:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  She said, No one, Lord. Jesus said, {I}{B}Neither do I condemn you. Go your way. From now on, sin no more.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\43:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  I, even I, am he who blots out your transgressions for my own sake; and I will not remember your sins.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\5:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  {I}{B}Blessed are the merciful, for they shall obtain mercy.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\8:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  For I will be merciful to their unrighteousness. I will remember their sins and lawless deeds no more.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\18:21-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  Then Peter came and said to him, Lord, how often shall my brother sin against me, and I forgive him? Until seven times?\r {BR}22  Jesus said to him, {I}{B}I don't tell you until seven times, but, until seventy times seven.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\1:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  If we confess our sins, he is faithful and righteous to forgive us the sins, and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\103:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  As far as the east is from the west, so far has he removed our transgressions from us.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Leviticus\\19:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18   'You shall not take vengeance, nor bear any grudge against the children of your people; but you shall love your neighbor as yourself. I am Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\18:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  With the merciful you will show yourself merciful. With the perfect man, you will show yourself perfect.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\86:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  For you, Lord, are good, and ready to forgive; abundant in loving kindness to all those who call on you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:3-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Don't let kindness and truth forsake you. Bind them around your neck. Write them on the tablet of your heart.\r {BR}4  So you will find favor, and good understanding in the sight of God and man.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\18:35-35{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}35  {I}{B}So my heavenly Father will also do to you, if you don't each forgive your brother from your hearts for his misdeeds.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Mark\\11:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  {I}{B}Whenever you stand praying, forgive, if you have anything against anyone; so that your Father, who is in heaven, may also forgive you your transgressions.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\6:37-37{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}37  {I}{B}Don't judge, and you won't be judged. Don't condemn, and you won't be condemned. Set free, and you will be set free.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\4:32-32{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}32  And be kind to one another, tenderhearted, forgiving each other, just as God also in Christ forgave you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Colossians\\3:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  bearing with one another, and forgiving each other, if any man has a complaint against any; even as Christ forgave you, so you also do.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\12:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  looking carefully lest there be any man who falls short of the grace of God; lest any root of bitterness springing up trouble you, and many be defiled by it;\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Growth spiritual",lessonscriptures:"Job\\23:10-10;Proverbs\\3:12-12;Jeremiah\\18:4-4;Ezekiel\\22:14-14;Matthew\\7:24-24;Matthew\\9:17-17;Luke\\12:48-48;Luke\\22:31-32;John\\3:30-30;John\\12:24-24;John\\15:2-2;John\\15:4-4;Romans\\6:13-13;Romans\\12:1-2;2 Corinthians\\4:16-17;1 Corinthians\\10:13-13;2 Corinthians\\10:3-4;2 Corinthians\\12:9-10;Philippians\\1:6-6;1 Timothy\\6:12-12;2 Timothy\\2:3-3;James\\1:2-3;James\\4:7-7;1 Peter\\1:6-7;1 Peter\\4:12-13;Psalms\\40:3-3;Ezekiel\\36:26-26;Romans\\6:4-4;2 Corinthians\\5:17-17;Ephesians\\4:23-24;Philippians\\3:13-14",id:"103",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Job\\23:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  But he knows the way that I take. When he has tried me, I shall come forth like gold.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  for whom Yahweh loves, he reproves; even as a father reproves the son in whom he delights.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\18:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  When the vessel that he made of the clay was marred in the hand of the potter, he made it again another vessel, as seemed good to the potter to make it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ezekiel\\22:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  Can your heart endure, or can your hands be strong, in the days that I shall deal with you? I, Yahweh, have spoken it, and will do it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\7:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  {I}{B}Everyone therefore who hears these words of mine, and does them, I will liken him to a wise man, who built his house on a rock.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\9:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  {I}{B}Neither do people put new wine into old wineskins, or else the skins would burst, and the wine be spilled, and the skins ruined. No, they put new wine into fresh wineskins, and both are preserved.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\12:48-48{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}48  {I}{B}but he who didn't know, and did things worthy of stripes, will be beaten with few stripes. To whoever much is given, of him will much be required; and to whom much was entrusted, of him more will be asked.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\22:31-32{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}31  The Lord said, {I}{B}Simon, Simon, behold, Satan asked to have you, that he might sift you as wheat,{/B}{/I}\r {BR}32  {I}{B}but I prayed for you, that your faith wouldn't fail. You, when once you have turned again, establish your brothers.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\3:30-30{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}30  He must increase, but I must decrease.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\12:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  {I}{B}Most certainly I tell you, unless a grain of wheat falls into the earth and dies, it remains by itself alone. But if it dies, it bears much fruit.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\15:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  {I}{B}Every branch in me that doesn't bear fruit, he takes away. Every branch that bears fruit, he prunes, that it may bear more fruit.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\15:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  {I}{B}Remain in me, and I in you. As the branch can't bear fruit by itself, unless it remains in the vine, so neither can you, unless you remain in me.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\6:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  Neither present your members to sin as instruments of unrighteousness, but present yourselves to God, as alive from the dead, and your members as instruments of righteousness to God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\12:1-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Therefore I urge you, brothers, by the mercies of God, to present your bodies a living sacrifice, holy, acceptable to God, which is your spiritual service.\r {BR}2  Don't be conformed to this world, but be transformed by the renewing of your mind, so that you may prove what is the good, well-pleasing, and perfect will of God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\4:16-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  Therefore we don't faint, but though our outward man is decaying, yet our inward man is renewed day by day.\r {BR}17  For our light affliction, which is for the moment, works for us more and more exceedingly an eternal weight of glory;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\10:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  No temptation has taken you except what is common to man. God is faithful, who will not allow you to be tempted above what you are able, but will with the temptation also make the way of escape, that you may be able to endure it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\10:3-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  For though we walk in the flesh, we don't wage war according to the flesh;\r {BR}4  for the weapons of our warfare are not of the flesh, but mighty before God to the throwing down of strongholds,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\12:9-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  He has said to me, My grace is sufficient for you, for my power is made perfect in weakness. Most gladly therefore I will rather glory in my weaknesses, that the power of Christ may rest on me.\r {BR}10  Therefore I take pleasure in weaknesses, in injuries, in necessities, in persecutions, in distresses, for Christ's sake. For when I am weak, then am I strong.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\1:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  being confident of this very thing, that he who began a good work in you will complete it until the day of Jesus Christ.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Timothy\\6:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  Fight the good fight of faith. Lay hold of the eternal life to which you were called, and you confessed the good confession in the sight of many witnesses.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Timothy\\2:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  You therefore must endure hardship, as a good soldier of Christ Jesus.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\1:2-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  Count it all joy, my brothers, when you fall into various temptations,\r {BR}3  knowing that the testing of your faith produces endurance.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\4:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Be subject therefore to God. But resist the devil, and he will flee from you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\1:6-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Wherein you greatly rejoice, though now for a little while, if need be, you have been put to grief in various trials,\r {BR}7  that the proof of your faith, which is more precious than gold that perishes even though it is tested by fire, may be found to result in praise, glory, and honor at the revelation of Jesus Christ--\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\4:12-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  Beloved, don't be astonished at the fiery trial which has come upon you, to test you, as though a strange thing happened to you.\r {BR}13  But because you are partakers of Christ's sufferings, rejoice; that at the revelation of his glory you also may rejoice with exceeding joy.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\40:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  He has put a new song in my mouth, even praise to our God. Many shall see it, and fear, and shall trust in Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ezekiel\\36:26-26{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}26  A new heart also will I give you, and a new spirit will I put within you; and I will take away the stony heart out of your flesh, and I will give you a heart of flesh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\6:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  We were buried therefore with him through baptism to death, that just like Christ was raised from the dead through the glory of the Father, so we also might walk in newness of life.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\5:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Therefore if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation. The old things have passed away. Behold, all things have become new.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\4:23-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  and that you be renewed in the spirit of your mind,\r {BR}24  and put on the new man, who in the likeness of God has been created in righteousness and holiness of truth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\3:13-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  Brothers, I don't regard myself as yet having taken hold, but one thing I do. Forgetting the things which are behind, and stretching forward to the things which are before,\r {BR}14  I press on toward the goal for the prize of the high calling of God in Christ Jesus.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Giving",lessonscriptures:"Matthew\\10:8-8;Proverbs\\3:27-27;Luke\\6:38-38;James\\2:15-17;Proverbs\\11:24-25;Matthew\\5:42-42;Deuteronomy\\15:11-11;Proverbs\\3:9-10;Proverbs\\21:13-13;Malachi\\3:10-10;Matthew\\6:2-4;Matthew\\25:40-40;2 Corinthians\\9:6-12",id:"104",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\10:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  {I}{B}Heal the sick, cleanse the lepers, and cast out demons. Freely you received, so freely give.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:27-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}27  Don't withhold good from those to whom it is due, when it is in the power of your hand to do it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\6:38-38{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}38  {I}{B}Give, and it will be given to you: good measure, pressed down, shaken together, and running over, will be given to you. For with the same measure you measure it will be measured back to you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\2:15-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  And if a brother or sister is naked and in lack of daily food,\r {BR}16  and one of you tells them, Go in peace, be warmed and filled; and yet you didn't give them the things the body needs, what good is it?\r {BR}17  Even so faith, if it has no works, is dead in itself.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\11:24-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  There is one who scatters, and increases yet more. There is one who withholds more than is appropriate, but gains poverty.\r {BR}25  The liberal soul shall be made fat. He who waters shall be watered also himself.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\5:42-42{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}42  {I}{B}Give to him who asks you, and don't turn away him who desires to borrow from you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\15:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  For the poor will never cease out of the land: therefore I command you, saying, You shall surely open your hand to your brother, to your needy, and to your poor, in your land.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:9-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  Honor Yahweh with your substance, with the first fruits of all your increase:\r {BR}10  so your barns will be filled with plenty, and your vats will overflow with new wine.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\21:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  Whoever stops his ears at the cry of the poor, he will also cry out, but shall not be heard.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Malachi\\3:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Bring the whole tithe into the storehouse, that there may be food in my house, and test me now in this, says Yahweh of Armies, if I will not open you the windows of heaven, and pour you out a blessing, that there shall not be room enough for.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\6:2-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  {I}{B}Therefore when you do merciful deeds, don't sound a trumpet before yourself, as the hypocrites do in the synagogues and in the streets, that they may get glory from men. Most certainly I tell you, they have received their reward.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}3  {I}{B}But when you do merciful deeds, don't let your left hand know what your right hand does,{/B}{/I}\r {BR}4  {I}{B}so that your merciful deeds may be in secret, then your Father who sees in secret will reward you openly.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\25:40-40{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}40  {I}{B}The King will answer them, 'Most certainly I tell you, inasmuch as you did it to one of the least of these my brothers, you did it to me.'{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\9:6-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Remember this: he who sows sparingly will also reap sparingly. He who sows bountifully will also reap bountifully.\r {BR}7  Let each man give according as he has determined in his heart; not grudgingly, or under compulsion; for God loves a cheerful giver.\r {BR}8  And God is able to make all grace abound to you, that you, always having all sufficiency in everything, may abound to every good work.\r {BR}9  As it is written, He has scattered abroad, he has given to the poor. His righteousness remains forever.\r {BR}10  Now may he who supplies seed to the sower and bread for food, supply and multiply your seed for sowing, and increase the fruits of your righteousness;\r {BR}11  you being enriched in everything to all liberality, which works through us thanksgiving to God.\r {BR}12  For this service of giving that you perform not only makes up for lack among the saints, but abounds also through many givings of thanks to God;\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Healing",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\34:19-19;James\\5:14-16;Psalms\\107:20-20;2 Kings\\20:5-5;Jeremiah\\30:17-17;Isaiah\\40:29-29;Psalms\\103:3-3;Isaiah\\53:5-5;Exodus\\15:26-26;Luke\\17:14-14;Matthew\\10:1-1;Malachi\\4:2-2;Acts\\9:34-34;Mark\\16:17-18;Hebrews\\12:13-13;2 Corinthians\\12:7-9;Psalms\\22:24-24;Psalms\\31:24-24;Psalms\\119:50-50;Psalms\\119:92-92;Psalms\\119:107-107;Psalms\\147:3-3;Isaiah\\59:1-1;Jeremiah\\32:27-27;Ezekiel\\34:16-16;Matthew\\9:22-22;Luke\\5:17-17;James\\5:16-16",id:"105",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  Many are the afflictions of the righteous, but Yahweh delivers him out of them all.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\5:14-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  Is any among you sick? Let him call for the elders of the assembly, and let them pray over him, anointing him with oil in the name of the Lord,\r {BR}15  and the prayer of faith will heal him who is sick, and the Lord will raise him up. If he has committed sins, he will be forgiven.\r {BR}16  Confess your offenses to one another, and pray for one another, that you may be healed. The insistent prayer of a righteous person is powerfully effective.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\107:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  He sends his word, and heals them, and delivers them from their graves.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Kings\\20:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Turn back, and tell Hezekiah the prince of my people, Thus says Yahweh, the God of David your father, I have heard your prayer, I have seen your tears: behold, I will heal you; on the third day you shall go up to the house of Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\30:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  For I will restore health to you, and I will heal you of your wounds, says Yahweh; because they have called you an outcast, ({I}{B}saying{/B}{/I}), It is Zion, whom no man seeks after.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\40:29-29{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}29  He gives power to the weak. He increases the strength of him who has no might.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\103:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  who forgives all your sins; who heals all your diseases;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\53:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  But he was pierced for our transgressions. He was crushed for our iniquities. The punishment that brought our peace was on him; and by his wounds we are healed.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Exodus\\15:26-26{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}26  and he said, If you will diligently listen to the voice of Yahweh your God, and will do that which is right in his eyes, and will pay attention to his commandments, and keep all his statutes, I will put none of the diseases on you, which I have put on the Egyptians; for I am Yahweh who heals you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\17:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  When he saw them, he said to them, {I}{B}Go and show yourselves to the priests.{/B}{/I} It happened that as they went, they were cleansed.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\10:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  He called to himself his twelve disciples, and gave them authority over unclean spirits, to cast them out, and to heal every disease and every sickness.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Malachi\\4:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  But to you who fear my name shall the sun of righteousness arise with healing in its wings. You will go out, and leap like calves of the stall.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Acts\\9:34-34{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}34  Peter said to him, Aeneas, Jesus Christ heals you. Get up and make your bed! Immediately he arose.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Mark\\16:17-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  {I}{B}These signs will accompany those who believe: in my name they will cast out demons; they will speak with new languages;{/B}{/I}\r {BR}18  {I}{B}they will take up serpents; and if they drink any deadly thing, it will in no way hurt them; they will lay hands on the sick, and they will recover.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\12:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  and make straight paths for your feet,  so that which is lame may not be dislocated, but rather be healed.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\12:7-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  By reason of the exceeding greatness of the revelations, that I should not be exalted excessively, there was given to me a thorn in the flesh, a messenger of Satan to torment me, that I should not be exalted excessively.\r {BR}8  Concerning this thing, I begged the Lord three times that it might depart from me.\r {BR}9  He has said to me, My grace is sufficient for you, for my power is made perfect in weakness. Most gladly therefore I will rather glory in my weaknesses, that the power of Christ may rest on me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\22:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  For he has not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the afflicted, Neither has he hidden his face from him; but when he cried to him, he heard.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\31:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  Be strong, and let your heart take courage, all you who hope in Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:50-50{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}50  This is my comfort in my affliction, for your word has revived me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:92-92{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}92  Unless your law had been my delight, I would have perished in my affliction.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:107-107{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}107  I am afflicted very much. Revive me, Yahweh, according to your word.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\147:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  He heals the broken in heart, and binds up their wounds.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\59:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Behold, Yahweh's hand is not shortened, that it can't save; neither his ear heavy, that it can't hear:\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\32:27-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}27  Behold, I am Yahweh, the God of all flesh: is there anything too hard for me?\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ezekiel\\34:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  I will seek that which was lost, and will bring back that which was driven away, and will bind up that which was broken, and will strengthen that which was sick: but the fat and the strong I will destroy; I will feed them in justice.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\9:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  But Jesus, turning around and seeing her, said, {I}{B}Daughter, cheer up! Your faith has made you well.{/B}{/I} And the woman was made well from that hour.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\5:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  It happened on one of those days, that he was teaching; and there were Pharisees and teachers of the law sitting by, who had come out of every village of Galilee, Judea, and Jerusalem. The power of the Lord was with him to heal them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\5:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  Confess your offenses to one another, and pray for one another, that you may be healed. The insistent prayer of a righteous person is powerfully effective.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Protection",lessonscriptures:"Leviticus\\25:18-18;Deuteronomy\\33:12-12;2 Samuel\\7:29-29;2 Samuel\\8:6-6;1 Chronicles\\17:8-8;Psalms\\21:7-9;Psalms\\63:11-11;Psalms\\132:17-18;Psalms\\144:10-10;Deuteronomy\\33:27-27;Psalms\\4:8-8;Psalms\\16:8-8;Psalms\\34:7-7;Psalms\\46:1-1;Psalms\\91:9-10;Psalms\\127:1-1;Proverbs\\3:26-26;Proverbs\\14:26-26;Proverbs\\18:10-10;Proverbs\\21:31-31;Proverbs\\30:5-5;Amos\\3:7-7",id:"106",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Leviticus\\25:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18   'Therefore you shall do my statutes, and keep my ordinances and do them; and you shall dwell in the land in safety.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\33:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  Of Benjamin he said, The beloved of Yahweh shall dwell in safety by him. He covers him all the day long. He dwells between his shoulders.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Samuel\\7:29-29{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}29  now therefore let it please you to bless the house of your servant, that it may continue forever before you; for you, Lord Yahweh, have spoken it: and with your blessing let the house of your servant be blessed forever.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Samuel\\8:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Then David put garrisons in Syria of Damascus; and the Syrians became servants to David, and brought tribute. Yahweh gave victory to David wherever he went.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Chronicles\\17:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  and I have been with you wherever you have gone, and have cut off all your enemies from before you; and I will make you a name, like the name of the great ones who are in the earth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\21:7-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  For the king trusts in Yahweh. Through the loving kindness of the Most High, he shall not be moved.\r {BR}8  Your hand will find out all of your enemies. Your right hand will find out those who hate you.\r {BR}9  You will make them as a fiery furnace in the time of your anger. Yahweh will swallow them up in his wrath. The fire shall devour them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\63:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  But the king shall rejoice in God. Everyone who swears by him will praise him, for the mouth of those who speak lies shall be silenced.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\132:17-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  There I will make the horn of David to bud. I have ordained a lamp for my anointed.\r {BR}18  I will clothe his enemies with shame, but on himself, his crown will be resplendent.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\144:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  You are he who gives salvation to kings, who rescues David, his servant, from the deadly sword.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\33:27-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}27  The eternal God is ({I}{B}your{/B}{/I}) dwelling place. Underneath are the everlasting arms. He thrust out the enemy from before you, and said, Destroy.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\4:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  In peace I will both lay myself down and sleep, for you, Yahweh alone, make me live in safety.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\16:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  I have set Yahweh always before me. Because he is at my right hand, I shall not be moved.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  The angel of Yahweh encamps around those who fear him, and delivers them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\46:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  God is our refuge and strength, a very present help in trouble.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\91:9-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  Because you have made Yahweh your refuge, and the Most High your dwelling place,\r {BR}10  no evil shall happen to you, neither shall any plague come near your dwelling.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\127:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Unless Yahweh builds the house, they labor in vain who build it. Unless Yahweh watches over the city, the watchman guards it in vain.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:26-26{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}26  for Yahweh will be your confidence, and will keep your foot from being taken.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\14:26-26{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}26  In the fear of Yahweh is a secure fortress, and he will be a refuge for his children.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\18:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  The name of Yahweh is a strong tower: the righteous run to him, and are safe.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\21:31-31{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}31  The horse is prepared for the day of battle; but victory is with Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\30:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Every word of God is flawless. He is a shield to those who take refuge in him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Amos\\3:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Surely the Lord Yahweh will do nothing, unless he reveals his secret to his servants the prophets.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Pastoring",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\27:23-23;Ezekiel\\34:11-11;John\\21:16-16;1 Corinthians\\3:6-7;1 Corinthians\\3:10-10;1 Corinthians\\9:11-11;2 Corinthians\\9:6-6;2 Timothy\\2:2-2;1 Peter\\5:2-2",id:"107",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\27:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  Know well the state of your flocks, and pay attention to your herds:\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ezekiel\\34:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  For thus says the Lord Yahweh: Behold, I myself, even I, will search for my sheep, and will seek them out.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\21:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  He said to him again a second time, {I}{B}Simon, son of Jonah, do you love me?{/B}{/I} He said to him, Yes, Lord; you know that I have affection for you. He said to him, {I}{B}Tend my sheep.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\3:6-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  I planted. Apollos watered. But God gave the increase.\r {BR}7  So then neither he who plants is anything, nor he who waters, but God who gives the increase.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\3:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  According to the grace of God which was given to me, as a wise master builder I laid a foundation, and another builds on it. But let each man be careful how he builds on it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\9:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  If we sowed to you spiritual things, is it a great thing if we reap your fleshly things?\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\9:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Remember this: he who sows sparingly will also reap sparingly. He who sows bountifully will also reap bountifully.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Timothy\\2:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  The things which you have heard from me among many witnesses, commit the same to faithful men, who will be able to teach others also.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\5:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  Shepherd the flock of God which is among you, exercising the oversight, not under compulsion, but voluntarily, not for dishonest gain, but willingly;\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Fight",lessonscriptures:"Deuteronomy\\20:3-3;Psalms\\144:1-1;Matthew\\16:18-18;2 Corinthians\\2:14-14;Ephesians\\3:16-16;1 Timothy\\6:12-12;2 Timothy\\2:3-3;2 Timothy\\2:4-4;1 John\\2:14-14;Jude\\1",id:"108",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\20:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  and shall tell them, Hear, Israel, you draw near this day to battle against your enemies: don't let your heart faint; don't be afraid, nor tremble, neither be scared of them;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\144:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Blessed be Yahweh, my rock, who teaches my hands to war, and my fingers to battle:\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\16:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  {I}{B}I also tell you that you are Peter, and on this rock I will build my assembly, and the gates of Hades will not prevail against it.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\2:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  Now thanks be to God, who always leads us in triumph in Christ, and reveals through us the sweet aroma of his knowledge in every place.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\3:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  that he would grant you, according to the riches of his glory, that you may be strengthened with power through his Spirit in the inward man;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Timothy\\6:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  Fight the good fight of faith. Lay hold of the eternal life to which you were called, and you confessed the good confession in the sight of many witnesses.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Timothy\\2:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  You therefore must endure hardship, as a good soldier of Christ Jesus.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Timothy\\2:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  No soldier on duty entangles himself in the affairs of life, that he may please him who enrolled him as a soldier.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\2:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  I have written to you, fathers, because you know him who is from the beginning. I have written to you, young men, because you are strong, and the word of God remains in you, and you have overcome the evil one.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jude\\1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Jude, a servant of Jesus Christ, and brother of James, to those who are called, sanctified by God the Father, and kept for Jesus Christ:\r {BR}2  Mercy to you and peace and love be multiplied.\r {BR}3  Beloved, while I was very eager to write to you about our common salvation, I was constrained to write to you exhorting you to contend earnestly for the faith which was once for all delivered to the saints.\r {BR}4  For there are certain men who crept in secretly, even those who were long ago written about for this condemnation: ungodly men, turning the grace of our God into lasciviousness, and denying our only Master, God, and Lord, Jesus Christ.\r {BR}5  Now I desire to remind you, though you already know this, that the Lord, having saved a people out of the land of Egypt, afterward destroyed those who didn't believe.\r {BR}6  Angels who didn't keep their first domain, but deserted their own dwelling place, he has kept in everlasting bonds under darkness for the judgment of the great day.\r {BR}7  Even as Sodom and Gomorrah, and the cities around them, having, in the same way as these, given themselves over to sexual immorality and gone after strange flesh, are set forth as an example, suffering the punishment of eternal fire.\r {BR}8  Yet in like manner these also in their dreaming defile the flesh, despise authority, and slander celestial beings.\r {BR}9  But Michael, the archangel, when contending with the devil and arguing about the body of Moses, dared not bring against him an abusive condemnation, but said, May the Lord rebuke you!\r {BR}10  But these speak evil of whatever things they don't know. What they understand naturally, like the creatures without reason, they are destroyed in these things.\r {BR}11  Woe to them! For they went in the way of Cain, and ran riotously in the error of Balaam for hire, and perished in Korah's rebellion.\r {BR}12  These are hidden rocky reefs in your love feasts when they feast with you, shepherds who without fear feed themselves; clouds without water, carried along by winds; autumn leaves without fruit, twice dead, plucked up by the roots;\r {BR}13  wild waves of the sea, foaming out their own shame; wandering stars, for whom the blackness of darkness has been reserved forever.\r {BR}14  About these also Enoch, the seventh from Adam, prophesied, saying, Behold, the Lord came with ten thousands of his holy ones,\r {BR}15  to execute judgment on all, and to convict all the ungodly of all their works of ungodliness which they have done in an ungodly way, and of all the hard things which ungodly sinners have spoken against him.\r {BR}16  These are murmurers and complainers, walking after their lusts  (and their mouth speaks proud things), showing respect of persons to gain advantage.\r {BR}17  But you, beloved, remember the words which have been spoken before by the apostles of our Lord Jesus Christ.\r {BR}18  They said to you that In the last time there will be mockers, walking after their own ungodly lusts.\r {BR}19  These are they who cause divisions, and are sensual, not having the Spirit.\r {BR}20  But you, beloved, keep building up yourselves on your most holy faith, praying in the Holy Spirit.\r {BR}21  Keep yourselves in the love of God, looking for the mercy of our Lord Jesus Christ to eternal life.\r {BR}22  On some have compassion, making a distinction,\r {BR}23  and some save, snatching them out of the fire with fear, hating even the clothing stained by the flesh.\r {BR}24  Now to him who is able to keep them from stumbling, and to present you faultless before the presence of his glory in great joy,\r {BR}25  to God our Savior, who alone is wise, be glory and majesty, dominion and power, both now and forever. Amen.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Happiness",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\5:11-11;Psalms\\16:11-11;Psalms\\30:5-5;Psalms\\126:5-5;Psalms\\128:1-2;Isaiah\\35:10-10;John\\15:11-11;Romans\\14:17-17",id:"109",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\5:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  But let all those who take refuge in you rejoice, Let them always shout for joy, because you defend them. Let them also who love your name be joyful in you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\16:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  You will show me the path of life. In your presence is fullness of joy. In your right hand there are pleasures forevermore.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\30:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  For his anger is but for a moment. His favor is for a lifetime. Weeping may stay for the night, but joy comes in the morning.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\126:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Those who sow in tears will reap in joy.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\128:1-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Blessed is everyone who fears Yahweh, who walks in his ways.\r {BR}2  For you will eat the labor of your hands. You will be happy, and it will be well with you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\35:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  The Yahweh's ransomed ones will return, and come with singing to Zion; and everlasting joy will be on their heads. They will obtain gladness and joy, and sorrow and sighing will flee away.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\15:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  {I}{B}I have spoken these things to you, that my joy may remain in you, and that your joy may be made full.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\14:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  for the Kingdom of God is not eating and drinking, but righteousness, peace, and joy in the Holy Spirit.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Encouragement",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\34:18-18;Psalms\\34:22-22;Psalms\\37:23-24;Psalms\\71:20-21;Psalms\\94:19-19;Psalms\\119:50-50;Psalms\\138:7-7;Psalms\\142:3-3;Isaiah\\25:4-4;Isaiah\\41:10-10;Isaiah\\41:17-17;Isaiah\\41:18-18;Isaiah\\61:3-3;Lamentations\\3:31-33;Romans\\8:28-28;Philippians\\1:6-6;2 Timothy\\2:12-12",id:"110",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  Yahweh is near to those who have a broken heart, and saves those who have a crushed spirit.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  Yahweh redeems the soul of his servants. None of those who take refuge in him shall be condemned.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\37:23-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  A man's goings are established by Yahweh. He delights in his way.\r {BR}24  Though he stumble, he shall not fall, for Yahweh holds him up with his hand.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\71:20-21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  You, who have shown us many and bitter troubles, you will let me live. You will bring us up again from the depths of the earth.\r {BR}21  Increase my honor, and comfort me again.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\94:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  In the multitude of my thoughts within me, your comforts delight my soul.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:50-50{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}50  This is my comfort in my affliction, for your word has revived me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\138:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Though I walk in the midst of trouble, you will revive me. You will stretch forth your hand against the wrath of my enemies. Your right hand will save me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\142:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  When my spirit was overwhelmed within me, you knew my path. In the way in which I walk, they have hidden a snare for me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\25:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  For you have been a stronghold to the poor, a stronghold to the needy in his distress, a refuge from the storm, a shade from the heat, when the blast of the dreaded ones is like a storm against the wall.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\41:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Don't you be afraid, for I am with you. Don't be dismayed, for I am your God. I will strengthen you. Yes, I will help you. Yes, I will uphold you with the right hand of my righteousness.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\41:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  The poor and needy seek water, and there is none. Their tongue fails for thirst. I, Yahweh, will answer them. I, the God of Israel, will not forsake them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\41:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  I will open rivers on the bare heights, and springs in the midst of the valleys. I will make the wilderness a pool of water, and the dry land springs of water.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\61:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  to appoint to those who mourn in Zion, to give to them a garland for ashes, the oil of joy for mourning, the garment of praise for the spirit of heaviness; that they may be called trees of righteousness, the planting of Yahweh, that he may be glorified.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Lamentations\\3:31-33{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}31  For the Lord will not cast off forever.\r {BR}32  For though he cause grief, yet he will have compassion according to the multitude of his loving kindnesses.\r {BR}33  For he does not afflict willingly, nor grieve the children of men.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\8:28-28{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  We know that all things work together for good for those who love God, to those who are called according to his purpose.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\1:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  being confident of this very thing, that he who began a good work in you will complete it until the day of Jesus Christ.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Timothy\\2:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  If we endure, we will also reign with him. If we deny him, he also will deny us.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Victory",lessonscriptures:"Exodus\\14:13-13;Psalms\\35:1-1;Psalms\\98:1-1;Isaiah\\35:4-4;2 Timothy\\4:18-18;Hebrews\\13:6-6;1 John\\3:8-8;Revelation\\12:11-11",id:"111",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Exodus\\14:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  Moses said to the people, Don't be afraid. Stand still, and see the salvation of Yahweh, which he will work for you today: for the Egyptians whom you have seen today, you shall never see them again.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\35:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Contend, Yahweh, with those who contend with me. Fight against those who fight against me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\98:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Sing to Yahweh a new song, for he has done marvelous things! His right hand, and his holy arm, have worked salvation for him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\35:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  Tell those who have a fearful heart, Be strong. Don't be afraid. Behold, your God will come with vengeance, God's retribution. He will come and save you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Timothy\\4:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  And the Lord will deliver me from every evil work, and will preserve me for his heavenly Kingdom; to whom be the glory forever and ever. Amen.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\13:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  So that with good courage we say, The Lord is my helper. I will not fear. What can man do to me?\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\3:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  He who sins is of the devil, for the devil has been sinning from the beginning. To this end the Son of God was revealed, that he might destroy the works of the devil.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Revelation\\12:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  They overcame him because of the Lamb's blood, and because of the word of their testimony. They didn't love their life, even to death.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Honesty",lessonscriptures:"Colossians\\3:9-9;Romans\\12:17-17;2 Corinthians\\8:21-21;Proverbs\\11:1-3;Proverbs\\12:13-17;Proverbs\\28:13-13;James\\5:16-16;2 Corinthians\\4:2-2",id:"112",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Colossians\\3:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  Don't lie to one another, seeing that you have put off the old man with his doings,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\12:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Repay no one evil for evil. Respect what is honorable in the sight of all men.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\8:21-21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  Having regard for honorable things, not only in the sight of the Lord, but also in the sight of men.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\11:1-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  A false balance is an abomination to Yahweh, but accurate weights are his delight.\r {BR}2  When pride comes, then comes shame, but with humility comes wisdom.\r {BR}3  The integrity of the upright shall guide them, but the perverseness of the treacherous shall destroy them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\12:13-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  An evil man is trapped by sinfulness of lips, but the righteous shall come out of trouble.\r {BR}14  A man shall be satisfied with good by the fruit of his mouth. The work of a man's hands shall be rewarded to him.\r {BR}15  The way of a fool is right in his own eyes, but he who is wise listens to counsel.\r {BR}16  A fool shows his annoyance the same day, but one who overlooks an insult is prudent.\r {BR}17  He who is truthful testifies honestly, but a false witness lies.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\28:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  He who conceals his sins doesn't prosper, but whoever confesses and renounces them finds mercy.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\5:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  Confess your offenses to one another, and pray for one another, that you may be healed. The insistent prayer of a righteous person is powerfully effective.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\4:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  But we have renounced the hidden things of shame, not walking in craftiness, nor handling the word of God deceitfully; but by the manifestation of the truth commending ourselves to every man's conscience in the sight of God.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Child Correction",lessonscriptures:"Proverbs\\3:12-12;Proverbs\\13:24-24;Proverbs\\19:18-18;Proverbs\\22:15-15;Proverbs\\23:13-13;Colossians\\3:21-21;1 Timothy\\3:4-4;Hebrews\\12:5-9;Psalms\\34:11-11;Psalms\\119:9-9;Psalms\\138:8-8;Psalms\\144:12-12;Proverbs\\3:1-1;Proverbs\\8:32-33;Proverbs\\22:6-6;Isaiah\\54:13-13;John\\21:15-15;2 Timothy\\2:22-22;3 John\\1:4-4;Deuteronomy\\6:7-7;Deuteronomy\\12:28-28;Deuteronomy\\32:46-47;Proverbs\\4:4-5;Proverbs\\4:5-5;Proverbs\\20:7-7;Nehemiah\\4:14-14;Ephesians\\6:4-4;2 Timothy\\2:2-2",id:"113",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  for whom Yahweh loves, he reproves; even as a father reproves the son in whom he delights.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\13:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  One who spares the rod hates his son, but one who loves him is careful to discipline him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\19:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  Discipline your son, for there is hope; don't be a willing party to his death.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\22:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Folly is bound up in the heart of a child: the rod of discipline drives it far from him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\23:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  Don't withhold correction from a child. If you punish him with the rod, he will not die.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Colossians\\3:21-21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  Fathers, don't provoke your children, so that they won't be discouraged.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Timothy\\3:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  one who rules his own house well, having children in subjection with all reverence;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\12:5-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  and you have forgotten the exhortation which reasons with you as with children, My son, don't take lightly the chastening of the Lord, nor faint when you are reproved by him;\r {BR}6  For whom the Lord loves, he chastens, and scourges every son whom he receives.\r {BR}7  It is for discipline that you endure. God deals with you as with children, for what son is there whom his father doesn't discipline?\r {BR}8  But if you are without discipline, of which all have been made partakers, then are you illegitimate, and not children.\r {BR}9  Furthermore, we had the fathers of our flesh to chasten us, and we paid them respect. Shall we not much rather be in subjection to the Father of spirits, and live?\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  Come, you children, listen to me. I will teach you the fear of Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  How can a young man keep his way pure? By living according to your word.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\138:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Yahweh will fulfill that which concerns me; your loving kindness, Yahweh, endures forever. Don't forsake the works of your own hands.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\144:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  Then our sons will be like well-nurtured plants, our daughters like pillars carved to adorn a palace.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  My son, don't forget my teaching; but let your heart keep my commandments:\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\8:32-33{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}32  Now therefore, my sons, listen to me, for blessed are those who keep my ways.\r {BR}33  Hear instruction, and be wise. Don't refuse it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\22:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Train up a child in the way he should go, and when he is old he will not depart from it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\54:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  All your children shall be taught of Yahweh; and great shall be the peace of your children.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\21:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  So when they had eaten their breakfast, Jesus said to Simon Peter, {I}{B}Simon, son of Jonah, do you love me more than these?{/B}{/I} He said to him, Yes, Lord; you know that I have affection for you. He said to him, {I}{B}Feed my lambs.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Timothy\\2:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  Flee from youthful lusts; but pursue righteousness, faith, love, and peace with those who call on the Lord out of a pure heart.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\3 John\\1:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  I have no greater joy than this, to hear about my children walking in truth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\6:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  and you shall teach them diligently to your children, and shall talk of them when you sit in your house, and when you walk by the way, and when you lie down, and when you rise up.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\12:28-28{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  Observe and hear all these words which I command you, that it may go well with you, and with your children after you forever, when you do that which is good and right in the eyes of Yahweh your God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\32:46-47{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}46  He said to them, Set your heart to all the words which I testify to you this day, which you shall command your children to observe to do, ({I}{B}even{/B}{/I}) all the words of this law.\r {BR}47  For it is no vain thing for you; because it is your life, and through this thing you shall prolong your days in the land, where you go over the Jordan to possess it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\4:4-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  He taught me, and said to me: Let your heart retain my words. Keep my commandments, and live.\r {BR}5  Get wisdom. Get understanding. Don't forget, neither swerve from the words of my mouth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\4:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Get wisdom. Get understanding. Don't forget, neither swerve from the words of my mouth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\20:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  A righteous man walks in integrity. Blessed are his children after him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Nehemiah\\4:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  I looked, and rose up, and said to the nobles, and to the rulers, and to the rest of the people, Don't be afraid of them: remember the Lord, who is great and awesome, and fight for your brothers, your sons, and your daughters, your wives, and your houses.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\6:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  You fathers, don't provoke your children to wrath, but nurture them in the discipline and instruction of the Lord.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Timothy\\2:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  The things which you have heard from me among many witnesses, commit the same to faithful men, who will be able to teach others also.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Childbearing",lessonscriptures:"Genesis\\49:25-25;Exodus\\1:7-7;Deuteronomy\\7:13-14;Job\\31:15-15;Psalms\\112:2-2;Psalms\\113:9-9;Psalms\\127:3-3;Psalms\\139:13-13;Psalms\\147:13-13;Isaiah\\40:11-11;Isaiah\\44:3-4;Jeremiah\\1:5-5;Luke\\1:45-45;Hebrews\\11:11-11;Psalms\\18:19-19;Psalms\\31:2-2;Psalms\\34:7-7;Psalms\\40:13-13;Psalms\\40:17-17;Psalms\\50:15-15;Psalms\\61:2-2;Psalms\\91:14-14;Proverbs\\11:21-21;Isaiah\\40:29-31;Isaiah\\65:23-23;Isaiah\\66:7-9;John\\16:21-21;1 Corinthians\\10:13\\;2 Corinthians\\12:9-9;Galatians\\6:9-9;Philippians\\4:13-13;1 Timothy\\2:15-15",id:"114",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Genesis\\49:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  even by the God of your father, who will help you; by the Almighty, who will bless you, with blessings of heaven above, blessings of the deep that lies below, blessings of the breasts, and of the womb.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Exodus\\1:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  The children of Israel were fruitful, and increased abundantly, and multiplied, and grew exceedingly mighty; and the land was filled with them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\7:13-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  and he will love you, and bless you, and multiply you; he will also bless the fruit of your body and the fruit of your ground, your grain and your new wine and your oil, the increase of your livestock and the young of your flock, in the land which he swore to your fathers to give you.\r {BR}14  You shall be blessed above all peoples: there shall not be male or female barren among you, or among your livestock.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Job\\31:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Didn't he who made me in the womb make him? Didn't one fashion us in the womb?\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\112:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  His seed will be mighty in the land. The generation of the upright will be blessed.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\113:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  He settles the barren woman in her home, as a joyful mother of children. Praise Yah!\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\127:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Behold, children are a heritage of Yahweh. The fruit of the womb is his reward.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\139:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  For you formed my inmost being. You knit me together in my mother's womb.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\147:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  For he has strengthened the bars of your gates. He has blessed your children within you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\40:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  He will feed his flock like a shepherd. He will gather the lambs in his arm, and carry them in his bosom. He will gently lead those who have their young.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\44:3-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  For I will pour water on him who is thirsty, and streams on the dry ground. I will pour my Spirit on your seed, and my blessing on your offspring:\r {BR}4  and they will spring up among the grass, as willows by the watercourses.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\1:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Before I formed you in the belly I knew you, and before you came forth out of the womb I sanctified you; I have appointed you a prophet to the nations.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\1:45-45{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}45  Blessed is she who believed, for there will be a fulfillment of the things which have been spoken to her from the Lord!\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\11:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  By faith, even Sarah herself received power to conceive, and she bore a child when she was past age, since she counted him faithful who had promised.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\18:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  He brought me forth also into a large place. He delivered me, because he delighted in me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\31:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  Bow down your ear to me. Deliver me speedily. Be to me a strong rock, a house of defense to save me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  The angel of Yahweh encamps around those who fear him, and delivers them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\40:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  Be pleased, Yahweh, to deliver me. Hurry to help me, Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\40:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  But I am poor and needy. May the Lord think about me. You are my help and my deliverer. Don't delay, my God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\50:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Call on me in the day of trouble. I will deliver you, and you will honor me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\61:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  From the end of the earth, I will call to you, when my heart is overwhelmed. Lead me to the rock that is higher than I.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\91:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  Because he has set his love on me, therefore I will deliver him. I will set him on high, because he has known my name.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\11:21-21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  Most certainly, the evil man will not be unpunished, but the seed of the righteous will be delivered.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\40:29-31{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}29  He gives power to the weak. He increases the strength of him who has no might.\r {BR}30  Even the youths faint and get weary, and the young men utterly fall;\r {BR}31  But those who wait for Yahweh will renew their strength. They will mount up with wings like eagles. They will run, and not be weary. They will walk, and not faint.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\65:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  They shall not labor in vain, nor bring forth for calamity; for they are the seed of the blessed of Yahweh, and their offspring with them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\66:7-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Before she travailed, she brought forth; before her pain came, she delivered a son.\r {BR}8  Who has heard such a thing? who has seen such things? Shall a land be born in one day? shall a nation be brought forth at once? for as soon as Zion travailed, she brought forth her children.\r {BR}9  Shall I bring to the birth, and not cause to bring forth? says Yahweh: shall I who cause to bring forth shut ({I}{B}the womb{/B}{/I})? says your God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\16:21-21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  {I}{B}A woman, when she gives birth, has sorrow, because her time has come. But when she has delivered the child, she doesn't remember the anguish any more, for the joy that a human being is born into the world.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\10:13\\{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  No temptation has taken you except what is common to man. God is faithful, who will not allow you to be tempted above what you are able, but will with the temptation also make the way of escape, that you may be able to endure it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\12:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  He has said to me, My grace is sufficient for you, for my power is made perfect in weakness. Most gladly therefore I will rather glory in my weaknesses, that the power of Christ may rest on me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Galatians\\6:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  Let us not be weary in doing good, for we will reap in due season, if we don't give up.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\4:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  I can do all things through Christ, who strengthens me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Timothy\\2:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  but she will be saved through her childbearing, if they continue in faith, love, and sanctification with sobriety.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Abortion",lessonscriptures:"Deuteronomy\\5:17-17;Psalms\\139:16-16;Genesis\\1:27-27;Psalms\\127:3-3;Psalms\\139:13-15;Job\\31:15-15;Jeremiah\\1:5-5",id:"115",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\5:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  You shall not murder.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\139:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  Your eyes saw my body. In your book they were all written, the days that were ordained for me, when as yet there were none of them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Genesis\\1:27-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}27  God created man in his own image. In God's image he created him; male and female he created them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\127:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Behold, children are a heritage of Yahweh. The fruit of the womb is his reward.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\139:13-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  For you formed my inmost being. You knit me together in my mother's womb.\r {BR}14  I will give thanks to you, for I am fearfully and wonderfully made. Your works are wonderful. My soul knows that very well.\r {BR}15  My frame wasn't hidden from you, when I was made in secret, woven together in the depths of the earth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Job\\31:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Didn't he who made me in the womb make him? Didn't one fashion us in the womb?\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\1:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Before I formed you in the belly I knew you, and before you came forth out of the womb I sanctified you; I have appointed you a prophet to the nations.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Thankfulness",lessonscriptures:"2 Chronicles\\20:22-22;Nehemiah\\8:10-10;Psalms\\50:23-23;Psalms\\89:15-15;Jeremiah\\30:19-19;Acts\\2:47-47;Philippians\\4:6-6;Matthew\\5:10-10;John\\16:33-33;Acts\\5:41-41;Romans\\9:20-20;2 Corinthians\\6:10-10;Philippians\\4:11-11;1 Thessalonians\\5:18-18;Hebrews\\10:34-34;1 Peter\\1:8-8;1 Peter\\3:14-14;1 Peter\\4:13-16;Psalms\\32:11-11;Psalms\\33:1-1;Psalms\\34:1-1;Psalms\\35:28-28;Psalms\\68:19-19;Psalms\\71:8-8;Psalms\\92:1-2;Psalms\\100:4-4;Psalms\\103:1-2;Psalms\\107:8-8;Psalms\\107:22-22;Psalms\\113:3-3;Lamentations\\3:41-41;Jonah\\2:9-9;Ephesians\\5:19-20;Hebrews\\13:15-15;Revelation\\19:5-5",id:"116",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\2 Chronicles\\20:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  When they began to sing and to praise, Yahweh set ambushers against the children of Ammon, Moab, and Mount Seir, who had come against Judah; and they were struck.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Nehemiah\\8:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Then he said to them, Go your way, eat the fat, and drink the sweet, and send portions to him for whom nothing is prepared; for this day is holy to our Lord. Don't be grieved; for the joy of Yahweh is your strength.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\50:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  Whoever offers the sacrifice of thanksgiving glorifies me, and prepares his way so that I will show God's salvation to him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\89:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Blessed are the people who learn to acclaim you. They walk in the light of your presence, Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\30:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  Out of them shall proceed thanksgiving and the voice of those who make merry: and I will multiply them, and they shall not be few; I will also glorify them, and they shall not be small.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Acts\\2:47-47{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}47  praising God, and having favor with all the people. The Lord added to the assembly day by day those who were being saved.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\4:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  In nothing be anxious, but in everything, by prayer and petition with thanksgiving, let your requests be made known to God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\5:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  {I}{B}Blessed are those who have been persecuted for righteousness' sake, for theirs is the Kingdom of Heaven.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\16:33-33{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}33  {I}{B}I have told you these things, that in me you may have peace. In the world you have oppression; but cheer up! I have overcome the world.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Acts\\5:41-41{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}41  They therefore departed from the presence of the council, rejoicing that they were counted worthy to suffer dishonor for Jesus' name.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\9:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  But indeed, O man, who are you to reply against God? Will the thing formed ask him who formed it, Why did you make me like this?\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\6:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  as sorrowful, yet always rejoicing; as poor, yet making many rich; as having nothing, and yet possessing all things.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\4:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  Not that I speak in respect to lack, for I have learned in whatever state I am, to be content in it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Thessalonians\\5:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  In everything give thanks, for this is the will of God in Christ Jesus toward you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\10:34-34{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}34  For you both had compassion on me in my chains, and joyfully accepted the plundering of your possessions, knowing that you have for yourselves a better possession and an enduring one in the heavens.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\1:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  whom not having known you love; in whom, though now you don't see him, yet believing, you rejoice greatly with joy unspeakable and full of glory--\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\3:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  But even if you should suffer for righteousness' sake, you are blessed. Don't fear what they fear, neither be troubled.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\4:13-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  But because you are partakers of Christ's sufferings, rejoice; that at the revelation of his glory you also may rejoice with exceeding joy.\r {BR}14  If you are insulted for the name of Christ, you are blessed; because the Spirit of glory and of God rests on you. On their part he is blasphemed, but on your part he is glorified.\r {BR}15  For let none of you suffer as a murderer, or a thief, or an evil doer, or a meddler in other men's matters.\r {BR}16  But if one of you suffers for being a Christian, let him not be ashamed; but let him glorify God in this matter.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\32:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  Be glad in Yahweh, and rejoice, you righteous! Shout for joy, all you who are upright in heart!\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\33:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Rejoice in Yahweh, you righteous! Praise is fitting for the upright.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  I will bless Yahweh at all times. His praise will always be in my mouth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\35:28-28{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  My tongue shall talk about your righteousness and about your praise all day long.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\68:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  Blessed be the Lord, who daily bears our burdens, even the God who is our salvation. Selah.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\71:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  My mouth shall be filled with your praise, with your honor all the day.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\92:1-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  It is a good thing to give thanks to Yahweh, to sing praises to your name, Most High;\r {BR}2  to proclaim your loving kindness in the morning, and your faithfulness every night,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\100:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  Enter into his gates with thanksgiving, into his courts with praise. Give thanks to him, and bless his name.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\103:1-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Praise Yahweh, my soul! All that is within me, praise his holy name!\r {BR}2  Praise Yahweh, my soul, and don't forget all his benefits;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\107:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Let them praise Yahweh for his loving kindness, for his wonderful works to the children of men!\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\107:22-22{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  Let them offer the sacrifices of thanksgiving, and declare his works with singing.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\113:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  From the rising of the sun to the going down of the same, Yahweh's name is to be praised.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Lamentations\\3:41-41{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}41  Let us lift up our heart with our hands to God in the heavens.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jonah\\2:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  But I will sacrifice to you with the voice of thanksgiving. I will pay that which I have vowed. Salvation belongs to Yahweh.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\5:19-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  speaking to one another in psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs; singing, and making melody in your heart to the Lord;\r {BR}20  giving thanks always concerning all things in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, to God, even the Father;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\13:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Through him, then, let us offer up a sacrifice of praise to God continually, that is, the fruit of lips which proclaim allegiance to his name.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Revelation\\19:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  A voice came forth from the throne, saying, Give praise to our God, all you his servants, you who fear him, the small and the great!\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Desperation",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\9:10-10;Psalms\\34:17-17;Psalms\\86:7-7;Psalms\\91:15-15;Psalms\\145:18-19",id:"117",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\9:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Those who know your name will put their trust in you, for you, Yahweh, have not forsaken those who seek you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  The righteous cry, and Yahweh hears, and delivers them out of all their troubles.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\86:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  In the day of my trouble I will call on you, for you will answer me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\91:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  He will call on me, and I will answer him. I will be with him in trouble. I will deliver him, and honor him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\145:18-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  Yahweh is near to all those who call on him, to all who call on him in truth.\r {BR}19  He will fulfill the desire of those who fear him. He also will hear their cry, and will save them.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Vacations",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\3:5-5;Psalms\\4:8-8;Psalms\\91:5-5;Psalms\\127:2-2;Proverbs\\3:24-24;Ecclesiastes\\5:12-12;Isaiah\\57:2-2;Isaiah\\58:13-14;1 Corinthians\\10:31-31;Hebrews\\4:9-10",id:"118",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\3:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  I laid myself down and slept. I awakened; for Yahweh sustains me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\4:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  In peace I will both lay myself down and sleep, for you, Yahweh alone, make me live in safety.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\91:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  You shall not be afraid of the terror by night, nor of the arrow that flies by day;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\127:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  It is vain for you to rise up early, to stay up late, eating the bread of toil; for he gives sleep to his loved ones.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  When you lie down, you will not be afraid. Yes, you will lie down, and your sleep will be sweet.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ecclesiastes\\5:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  The sleep of a laboring man is sweet, whether he eats little or much; but the abundance of the rich will not allow him to sleep.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\57:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  He enters into peace; they rest in their beds, each one who walks in his uprightness.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\58:13-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  If you turn away your foot from the Sabbath, from doing your pleasure on my holy day; and call the Sabbath a delight, ({I}{B}and{/B}{/I}) the holy of Yahweh honorable; and shall honor it, not doing your own ways, nor finding your own pleasure, nor speaking ({I}{B}your own{/B}{/I}) words:\r {BR}14  then you shall delight yourself in Yahweh; and I will make you to ride on the high places of the earth; and I will feed you with the heritage of Jacob your father: for the mouth of Yahweh has spoken it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\10:31-31{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}31  Whether therefore you eat, or drink, or whatever you do, do all to the glory of God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\4:9-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  There remains therefore a Sabbath rest for the people of God.\r {BR}10  For he who has entered into his rest has himself also rested from his works, as God did from his.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Courage",lessonscriptures:"Exodus\\14:13-14;Deuteronomy\\20:1-1;Deuteronomy\\31:8-8;Joshua\\23:10-10;1 Samuel\\2:9-9;1 Samuel\\14:6-6;1 Samuel\\17:47-47;2 Chronicles\\32:7-8;Psalms\\17:5-5;Psalms\\26:1-1;Psalms\\60:11-11;Psalms\\62:5-5;Psalms\\84:5-7;Psalms\\112:7-8;Psalms\\118:8-8;Psalms\\143:8-8;Proverbs\\3:5-6;Isaiah\\30:15-15;Zechariah\\4:6-6;John\\15:5-5;1 John\\5:4-4",id:"119",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Exodus\\14:13-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  Moses said to the people, Don't be afraid. Stand still, and see the salvation of Yahweh, which he will work for you today: for the Egyptians whom you have seen today, you shall never see them again.\r {BR}14  Yahweh will fight for you, and you shall be still.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\20:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  When you go forth to battle against your enemies, and see horses, and chariots, ({I}{B}and{/B}{/I}) a people more than you, you shall not be afraid of them; for Yahweh your God is with you, who brought you up out of the land of Egypt.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\31:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Yahweh, he it is who does go before you; he will be with you, he will not fail you, neither forsake you: don't be afraid, neither be dismayed.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Joshua\\23:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  One man of you shall chase a thousand; for it is Yahweh your God who fights for you, as he spoke to you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Samuel\\2:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  He will keep the feet of his holy ones, but the wicked shall be put to silence in darkness; for no man shall prevail by strength.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Samuel\\14:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Jonathan said to the young man who bore his armor, Come, and let us go over to the garrison of these uncircumcised: it may be that Yahweh will work for us; for there is no restraint to Yahweh to save by many or by few.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Samuel\\17:47-47{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}47  and that all this assembly may know that Yahweh doesn't save with sword and spear: for the battle is Yahweh's, and he will give you into our hand.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Chronicles\\32:7-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Be strong and of good courage, don't be afraid nor dismayed for the king of Assyria, nor for all the multitude who is with him; for there is a greater with us than with him:\r {BR}8  with him is an arm of flesh; but with us is Yahweh our God to help us, and to fight our battles. The people rested themselves on the words of Hezekiah king of Judah.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\17:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  My steps have held fast to your paths. My feet have not slipped.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\26:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Judge me, Yahweh, for I have walked in my integrity. I have trusted also in Yahweh without wavering.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\60:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  Give us help against the adversary, for the help of man is vain.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\62:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  My soul, wait in silence for God alone, for my expectation is from him.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\84:5-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Blessed are those whose strength is in you; who have set their hearts on a pilgrimage.\r {BR}6  Passing through the valley of Weeping, they make it a place of springs. Yes, the autumn rain covers it with blessings.\r {BR}7  They go from strength to strength. Everyone of them appears before God in Zion.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\112:7-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  He will not be afraid of evil news. His heart is steadfast, trusting in Yahweh.\r {BR}8  His heart is established. He will not be afraid in the end when he sees his adversaries.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\118:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  It is better to take refuge in Yahweh, than to put confidence in man.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\143:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Cause me to hear your loving kindness in the morning, for I trust in you. Cause me to know the way in which I should walk, for I lift up my soul to you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:5-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Trust in Yahweh with all your heart, and don't lean on your own understanding.\r {BR}6  In all your ways acknowledge him, and he will make your paths straight.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\30:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  For thus said the Lord Yahweh, the Holy One of Israel, You will be saved in returning and rest. Your strength will be in quietness and in confidence. You refused,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Zechariah\\4:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Then he answered and spoke to me, saying, This is the word of Yahweh to Zerubbabel, saying, 'Not by might, nor by power, but by my Spirit,' says Yahweh of Armies.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\15:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  {I}{B}I am the vine. You are the branches. He who remains in me, and I in him, the same bears much fruit, for apart from me you can do nothing.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\5:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  For whatever is born of God overcomes the world. This is the victory that has overcome the world: your faith.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Simplicity",lessonscriptures:"John\\12:32-32;1 Corinthians\\1:17-17;1 Corinthians\\1:27-29;1 Corinthians\\2:4-4",id:"120",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\John\\12:32-32{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}32  {I}{B}And I, if I am lifted up from the earth, will draw all people to myself.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\1:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  For Christ sent me not to baptize, but to preach the Good News--not in wisdom of words, so that the cross of Christ wouldn't be made void.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\1:27-29{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}27  but God chose the foolish things of the world that he might put to shame those who are wise. God chose the weak things of the world, that he might put to shame the things that are strong;\r {BR}28  and God chose the lowly things of the world, and the things that are despised, and the things that are not, that he might bring to nothing the things that are:\r {BR}29  that no flesh should boast before God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\2:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  My speech and my preaching were not in persuasive words of human wisdom, but in demonstration of the Spirit and of power,\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Conviction",lessonscriptures:"Psalms\\119:46-46;Proverbs\\29:25-25;Isaiah\\40:9-9;Isaiah\\50:4-4;Jeremiah\\1:7-7;Ezekiel\\3:9-9;Matthew\\5:14-16;Mark\\8:38-38;Acts\\1:8-8;Acts\\4:13-13;Acts\\5:29-29;Romans\\1:16-16;Ephesians\\6:19-20;1 Thessalonians\\2:4-4;2 Timothy\\1:8-8;Titus\\2:15-15;1 Peter\\2:12-12",id:"121",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\119:46-46{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}46  I will also speak of your statutes before kings, and will not be disappointed.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\29:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  The fear of man proves to be a snare, but whoever puts his trust in Yahweh is kept safe.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\40:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  You who tell good news to Zion, go up on a high mountain. You who tell good news to Jerusalem, lift up your voice with strength. Lift it up. Don't be afraid. Say to the cities of Judah, Behold, your God!\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\50:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  The Lord Yahweh has given me the tongue of those who are taught, that I may know how to sustain with words him who is weary: he wakens morning by morning, he wakens my ear to hear as those who are taught.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Jeremiah\\1:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  But Yahweh said to me, Don't say, I am a child; for to whoever I shall send you, you shall go, and whatever I shall command you, you shall speak.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ezekiel\\3:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  As an adamant harder than flint have I made your forehead: don't be afraid of them, neither be dismayed at their looks, though they are a rebellious house.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\5:14-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  {I}{B}You are the light of the world. A city located on a hill can't be hidden.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}15  {I}{B}Neither do you light a lamp, and put it under a measuring basket, but on a stand; and it shines to all who are in the house.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}16  {I}{B}Even so, let your light shine before men; that they may see your good works, and glorify your Father who is in heaven.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Mark\\8:38-38{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}38  {I}{B}For whoever will be ashamed of me and of my words in this adulterous and sinful generation, the Son of Man also will be ashamed of him, when he comes in the glory of his Father with the holy angels.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Acts\\1:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  {I}{B}But you will receive power when the Holy Spirit has come upon you. You will be witnesses to me in Jerusalem, in all Judea and Samaria, and to the uttermost parts of the earth.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Acts\\4:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, and had perceived that they were unlearned and ignorant men, they marveled. They recognized that they had been with Jesus.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Acts\\5:29-29{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}29  But Peter and the apostles answered, We must obey God rather than men.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\1:16-16{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}16  For I am not ashamed of the Good News of Christ, for it is the power of God for salvation for everyone who believes; for the Jew first, and also for the Greek.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\6:19-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  on my behalf, that utterance may be given to me in opening my mouth, to make known with boldness the mystery of the Good News,\r {BR}20  for which I am an ambassador in chains; that in it I may speak boldly, as I ought to speak.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Thessalonians\\2:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  But even as we have been approved by God to be entrusted with the Good News, so we speak; not as pleasing men, but God, who tests our hearts.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Timothy\\1:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Therefore don't be ashamed of the testimony of our Lord, nor of me his prisoner; but endure hardship for the Good News according to the power of God,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Titus\\2:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Say these things and exhort and reprove with all authority. Let no man despise you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\2:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  having good behavior among the nations, so in that of which they speak against you as evildoers, they may by your good works, which they see, glorify God in the day of visitation.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Vice",lessonscriptures:"Ephesians\\5:18-18;Romans\\14:11-12;Romans\\12:1-2;1 Corinthians\\6:9-11;1 Corinthians\\6:12-12;Romans\\6:11-13;John\\8:36-36;Proverbs\\20:1-1;Proverbs\\28:13-13;1 John\\1:8-9;Galatians\\5:22-23;1 Corinthians\\10:13-13;1 Corinthians\\6:19-19;1 Timothy\\5:23-23;1 Peter\\4:2-7",id:"122",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\5:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  Don't be drunken with wine, in which is dissipation, but be filled with the Spirit,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\14:11-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  For it is written,  'As I live,' says the Lord, 'to me every knee will bow. Every tongue will confess to God.' \r {BR}12  So then each one of us will give account of himself to God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\12:1-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Therefore I urge you, brothers, by the mercies of God, to present your bodies a living sacrifice, holy, acceptable to God, which is your spiritual service.\r {BR}2  Don't be conformed to this world, but be transformed by the renewing of your mind, so that you may prove what is the good, well-pleasing, and perfect will of God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\6:9-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  Or don't you know that the unrighteous will not inherit the Kingdom of God? Don't be deceived. Neither the sexually immoral, nor idolaters, nor adulterers, nor male prostitutes, nor homosexuals,\r {BR}10  nor thieves, nor covetous, nor drunkards, nor slanderers, nor extortioners, will inherit the Kingdom of God.\r {BR}11  Such were some of you, but you were washed. But you were sanctified. But you were justified in the name of the Lord Jesus, and in the Spirit of our God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\6:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  All things are lawful for me, but not all things are expedient. All things are lawful for me, but I will not be brought under the power of anything.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\6:11-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  Thus consider yourselves also to be dead to sin, but alive to God in Christ Jesus our Lord.\r {BR}12  Therefore don't let sin reign in your mortal body, that you should obey it in its lusts.\r {BR}13  Neither present your members to sin as instruments of unrighteousness, but present yourselves to God, as alive from the dead, and your members as instruments of righteousness to God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\8:36-36{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}36  {I}{B}If therefore the Son makes you free, you will be free indeed.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\20:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Wine is a mocker, and beer is a brawler. Whoever is led astray by them is not wise.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\28:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  He who conceals his sins doesn't prosper, but whoever confesses and renounces them finds mercy.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\1:8-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  If we say that we have no sin, we deceive ourselves, and the truth is not in us.\r {BR}9  If we confess our sins, he is faithful and righteous to forgive us the sins, and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Galatians\\5:22-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faith,\r {BR}23  gentleness, and self-control. Against such things there is no law.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\10:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  No temptation has taken you except what is common to man. God is faithful, who will not allow you to be tempted above what you are able, but will with the temptation also make the way of escape, that you may be able to endure it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\6:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  Or don't you know that your body is a temple of the Holy Spirit which is in you, which you have from God? You are not your own,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Timothy\\5:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  Be no longer a drinker of water only, but use a little wine for your stomach's sake and your frequent infirmities.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\4:2-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  that you no longer should live the rest of your time in the flesh for the lusts of men, but for the will of God.\r {BR}3  For we have spent enough of our past time doing the desire of the Gentiles, and having walked in lewdness, lusts, drunken binges, orgies, carousings, and abominable idolatries.\r {BR}4  They think it is strange that you don't run with them into the same excess of riot, blaspheming:\r {BR}5  who will give account to him who is ready to judge the living and the dead.\r {BR}6  For to this end the Good News was preached even to the dead, that they might be judged indeed as men in the flesh, but live as to God in the spirit.\r {BR}7  But the end of all things is near. Therefore be of sound mind, self-controlled, and sober in prayer.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Pride",lessonscriptures:"1 Samuel\\2:3-3;Proverbs\\11:2-2;Proverbs\\13:10-10;Proverbs\\15:25-25;Proverbs\\22:4-4;Proverbs\\29:23-23;1 Corinthians\\10:12-12;James\\4:10-10;Luke\\14:11-11;Galatians\\5:22-23;Philippians\\2:3-5;Proverbs\\16:5-5;Proverbs\\16:18-18;Proverbs\\16:25-25;Proverbs\\18:12-12;James\\4:6-6;Psalms\\25:9-9;1 Peter\\5:5-7;1 Kings\\20:11-11;Isaiah\\66:2-2",id:"123",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\1 Samuel\\2:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  Talk no more so exceeding proudly. Don't let arrogance come out of your mouth, For Yahweh is a God of knowledge. By him actions are weighed.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\11:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  When pride comes, then comes shame, but with humility comes wisdom.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\13:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Pride only breeds quarrels, but with ones who take advice is wisdom.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\15:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  Yahweh will uproot the house of the proud, but he will keep the widow's borders intact.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\22:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  The result of humility and the fear of Yahweh is wealth, honor, and life.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\29:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23  A man's pride brings him low, but one of lowly spirit gains honor.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\10:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  Therefore let him who thinks he stands be careful that he doesn't fall.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\4:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Humble yourselves in the sight of the Lord, and he will exalt you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\14:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  {I}{B}For everyone who exalts himself will be humbled, and whoever humbles himself will be exalted.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Galatians\\5:22-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faith,\r {BR}23  gentleness, and self-control. Against such things there is no law.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\2:3-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  doing nothing through rivalry or through conceit, but in humility, each counting others better than himself;\r {BR}4  each of you not just looking to his own things, but each of you also to the things of others.\r {BR}5  Have this in your mind, which was also in Christ Jesus,\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\16:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Everyone who is proud in heart is an abomination to Yahweh: they shall certainly not be unpunished.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\16:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  Pride goes before destruction, and a haughty spirit before a fall.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\16:25-25{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  There is a way which seems right to a man, but in the end it leads to death.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\18:12-12{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  Before destruction the heart of man is proud, but before honor is humility.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\James\\4:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  But he gives more grace. Therefore it says, God resists the proud, but gives grace to the humble.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\25:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  He will guide the humble in justice. He will teach the humble his way.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\5:5-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  Likewise, you younger ones, be subject to the elder. Yes, all of you gird yourselves with humility, to subject yourselves to one another; for God resists the proud, but gives grace to the humble.\r {BR}6  Humble yourselves therefore under the mighty hand of God, that he may exalt you in due time;\r {BR}7  casting all your worries on him, because he cares for you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Kings\\20:11-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}11  The king of Israel answered, Tell him, Don't let him who girds on ({I}{B}his armor{/B}{/I}) boast himself as he who puts it off.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\66:2-2{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  For all these things has my hand made, and ({I}{B}so{/B}{/I}) all these things came to be, says Yahweh: but to this man will I look, even to him who is poor and of a contrite spirit, and who trembles at my word.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Separation",lessonscriptures:"Genesis\\31:49-49;1 Samuel\\1:27-28;Psalms\\23:4-4;Psalms\\27:10-10;Psalms\\34:18-18;Psalms\\147:3-3;Song of Solomon\\8:7-7;John\\14:18-18;Romans\\8:18-18;2 Corinthians\\1:4-4;Philippians\\3:7-8;1 Thessalonians\\4:13-13;1 Peter\\1:7-7;Hebrews\\10:36-36",id:"124",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Genesis\\31:49-49{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}49  and Mizpah, for he said, Yahweh watch between me and you, when we are absent one from another.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Samuel\\1:27-28{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}27  For this child I prayed; and Yahweh has given me my petition which I asked of him:\r {BR}28  therefore also I have granted him to Yahweh; as long as he lives he is granted to Yahweh. He worshiped Yahweh there.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\23:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  Even though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil, for you are with me. Your rod and your staff, they comfort me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\27:10-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  When my father and my mother forsake me, then Yahweh will take me up.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\34:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  Yahweh is near to those who have a broken heart, and saves those who have a crushed spirit.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\147:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  He heals the broken in heart, and binds up their wounds.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Song of Solomon\\8:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  Many waters can't quench love, neither can floods drown it. If a man would give all the wealth of his house for love, he would be utterly scorned.  Friends\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\14:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  {I}{B}I will not leave you orphans. I will come to you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\8:18-18{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  For I consider that the sufferings of this present time are not worthy to be compared with the glory which will be revealed toward us.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\1:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  who comforts us in all our affliction, that we may be able to comfort those who are in any affliction, through the comfort with which we ourselves are comforted by God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Philippians\\3:7-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  However, what things were gain to me, these have I counted loss for Christ.\r {BR}8  Yes most certainly, and I count all things to be loss for the excellency of the knowledge of Christ Jesus, my Lord, for whom I suffered the loss of all things, and count them nothing but refuse, that I may gain Christ\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Thessalonians\\4:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  But we don't want you to be ignorant, brothers, concerning those who have fallen asleep, so that you don't grieve like the rest, who have no hope.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\1:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  that the proof of your faith, which is more precious than gold that perishes even though it is tested by fire, may be found to result in praise, glory, and honor at the revelation of Jesus Christ--\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\10:36-36{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}36  For you need endurance so that, having done the will of God, you may receive the promise.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Legalities",lessonscriptures:"Matthew\\17:24-27;Matthew\\22:17-21;1 Peter\\2:12-14;Matthew\\5:25-26;Matthew\\10:18-19;Romans\\13:8-8;John\\19:10-11;Luke\\2:1-5;Isaiah\\40:15-17;1 Corinthians\\16:9-9;Romans\\13:1-7",id:"125",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\17:24-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  When they had come to Capernaum, those who collected the didrachma coins came to Peter, and said, Doesn't your teacher pay the didrachma?\r {BR}25  He said, Yes. When he came into the house, Jesus anticipated him, saying, {I}{B}What do you think, Simon? From whom do the kings of the earth receive toll or tribute? From their children, or from strangers?{/B}{/I}\r {BR}26  Peter said to him, From strangers. Jesus said to him, {I}{B}Therefore the children are exempt.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}27  {I}{B}But, lest we cause them to stumble, go to the sea, cast a hook, and take up the first fish that comes up. When you have opened its mouth, you will find a stater coin. Take that, and give it to them for me and you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\22:17-21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Tell us therefore, what do you think? Is it lawful to pay taxes to Caesar, or not?\r {BR}18  But Jesus perceived their wickedness, and said, {I}{B}Why do you test me, you hypocrites?{/B}{/I}\r {BR}19  {I}{B}Show me the tax money.{/B}{/I} They brought to him a denarius.\r {BR}20  He asked them, {I}{B}Whose is this image and inscription?{/B}{/I}\r {BR}21  They said to him, Caesar's. Then he said to them, {I}{B}Give therefore to Caesar the things that are Caesar's, and to God the things that are God's.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\2:12-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}12  having good behavior among the nations, so in that of which they speak against you as evildoers, they may by your good works, which they see, glorify God in the day of visitation.\r {BR}13  Therefore subject yourselves to every ordinance of man for the Lord's sake: whether to the king, as supreme;\r {BR}14  or to governors, as sent by him for vengeance on evildoers and for praise to those who do well.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\5:25-26{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}25  {I}{B}Agree with your adversary quickly, while you are with him in the way; lest perhaps the prosecutor deliver you to the judge, and the judge deliver you to the officer, and you be cast into prison.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}26  {I}{B}Most certainly I tell you, you shall by no means get out of there, until you have paid the last penny.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\10:18-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  {I}{B}Yes, and you will be brought before governors and kings for my sake, for a testimony to them and to the nations.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}19  {I}{B}But when they deliver you up, don't be anxious how or what you will say, for it will be given you in that hour what you will say.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\13:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Owe no one anything, except to love one another; for he who loves his neighbor has fulfilled the law.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\John\\19:10-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Pilate therefore said to him, Aren't you speaking to me? Don't you know that I have power to release you, and have power to crucify you?\r {BR}11  Jesus answered, {I}{B}You would have no power at all against me, unless it were given to you from above. Therefore he who delivered me to you has greater sin.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\2:1-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Now it happened in those days, that a decree went out from Caesar Augustus that all the world should be enrolled.\r {BR}2  This was the first enrollment made when Quirinius was governor of Syria.\r {BR}3  All went to enroll themselves, everyone to his own city.\r {BR}4  Joseph also went up from Galilee, out of the city of Nazareth, into Judea, to the city of David, which is called Bethlehem, because he was of the house and family of David;\r {BR}5  to enroll himself with Mary, who was pledged to be married to him as wife, being pregnant.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\40:15-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Behold, the nations are like a drop in a bucket, and are regarded as a speck of dust on a balance. Behold, he lifts up the islands like a very little thing.\r {BR}16  Lebanon is not sufficient to burn, nor its animals sufficient for a burnt offering.\r {BR}17  All the nations are like nothing before him. They are regarded by him as less than nothing, and vanity.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\16:9-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  for a great and effective door has opened to me, and there are many adversaries.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\13:1-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  Let every soul be in subjection to the higher authorities, for there is no authority except from God, and those who exist are ordained by God.\r {BR}2  Therefore he who resists the authority, withstands the ordinance of God; and those who withstand will receive to themselves judgment.\r {BR}3  For rulers are not a terror to the good work, but to the evil. Do you desire to have no fear of the authority? Do that which is good, and you will have praise from the same,\r {BR}4  for he is a servant of God to you for good. But if you do that which is evil, be afraid, for he doesn't bear the sword in vain; for he is a servant of God, an avenger for wrath to him who does evil.\r {BR}5  Therefore you need to be in subjection, not only because of the wrath, but also for conscience' sake.\r {BR}6  For this reason you also pay taxes, for they are servants of God's service, attending continually on this very thing.\r {BR}7  Give therefore to everyone what you owe: taxes to whom taxes are due; customs to whom customs; respect to whom respect; honor to whom honor.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Perversion",lessonscriptures:"Romans\\1:18-28;Ephesians\\4:22-24;Leviticus\\20:13-13;1 Corinthians\\6:9-11;Ephesians\\5:3-3;Hebrews\\13:4-4",id:"126",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Romans\\1:18-28{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  For the wrath of God is revealed from heaven against all ungodliness and unrighteousness of men, who suppress the truth in unrighteousness,\r {BR}19  because that which is known of God is revealed in them, for God revealed it to them.\r {BR}20  For the invisible things of him since the creation of the world are clearly seen, being perceived through the things that are made, even his everlasting power and divinity; that they may be without excuse.\r {BR}21  Because, knowing God, they didn't glorify him as God, neither gave thanks, but became vain in their reasoning, and their senseless heart was darkened.\r {BR}22  Professing themselves to be wise, they became fools,\r {BR}23  and traded the glory of the incorruptible God for the likeness of an image of corruptible man, and of birds, and four-footed animals, and creeping things.\r {BR}24  Therefore God also gave them up in the lusts of their hearts to uncleanness, that their bodies should be dishonored among themselves,\r {BR}25  who exchanged the truth of God for a lie, and worshiped and served the creature rather than the Creator, who is blessed forever. Amen.\r {BR}26  For this reason, God gave them up to vile passions. For their women changed the natural function into that which is against nature.\r {BR}27  Likewise also the men, leaving the natural function of the woman, burned in their lust toward one another, men doing what is inappropriate with men, and receiving in themselves the due penalty of their error.\r {BR}28  Even as they refused to have God in their knowledge, God gave them up to a reprobate mind, to do those things which are not fitting;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\4:22-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}22  that you put away, as concerning your former way of life, the old man, that grows corrupt after the lusts of deceit;\r {BR}23  and that you be renewed in the spirit of your mind,\r {BR}24  and put on the new man, who in the likeness of God has been created in righteousness and holiness of truth.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Leviticus\\20:13-13{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13   'If a man lies with a male, as with a woman, both of them have committed an abomination: they shall surely be put to death; their blood shall be upon them.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Corinthians\\6:9-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  Or don't you know that the unrighteous will not inherit the Kingdom of God? Don't be deceived. Neither the sexually immoral, nor idolaters, nor adulterers, nor male prostitutes, nor homosexuals,\r {BR}10  nor thieves, nor covetous, nor drunkards, nor slanderers, nor extortioners, will inherit the Kingdom of God.\r {BR}11  Such were some of you, but you were washed. But you were sanctified. But you were justified in the name of the Lord Jesus, and in the Spirit of our God.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\5:3-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}3  But sexual immorality, and all uncleanness, or covetousness, let it not even be mentioned among you, as becomes saints;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\13:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  Let marriage be held in honor among all, and let the bed be undefiled: but God will judge the sexually immoral and adulterers.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Resistance",lessonscriptures:"Isaiah\\59:19-19;Matthew\\10:1-1;Matthew\\16:19-19;Mark\\8:33-33;Luke\\9:1-1;Luke\\10:17-17;Luke\\10:19-19;2 Corinthians\\10:4-5;Ephesians\\4:27-27;Ephesians\\6:10-11;1 John\\4:4-4;1 Peter\\5:8-9;1 John\\3:8-8",id:"127",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\59:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  So shall they fear the name of Yahweh from the west, and his glory from the rising of the sun; for he will come as a rushing stream, which the breath of Yahweh drives.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\10:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  He called to himself his twelve disciples, and gave them authority over unclean spirits, to cast them out, and to heal every disease and every sickness.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\16:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  {I}{B}I will give to you the keys of the Kingdom of Heaven, and whatever you bind on earth will have been bound in heaven; and whatever you release on earth will have been released in heaven.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Mark\\8:33-33{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}33  But he, turning around, and seeing his disciples, rebuked Peter, and said, {I}{B}Get behind me, Satan! For you have in mind not the things of God, but the things of men.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\9:1-1{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}1  He called the twelve together, and gave them power and authority over all demons, and to cure diseases.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\10:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  The seventy returned with joy, saying, Lord, even the demons are subject to us in your name!\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Luke\\10:19-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}19  {I}{B}Behold, I give you authority to tread on serpents and scorpions, and over all the power of the enemy. Nothing will in any way hurt you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Corinthians\\10:4-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  for the weapons of our warfare are not of the flesh, but mighty before God to the throwing down of strongholds,\r {BR}5  throwing down imaginations and every high thing that is exalted against the knowledge of God, and bringing every thought into captivity to the obedience of Christ;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\4:27-27{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}27  neither give place to the devil.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Ephesians\\6:10-11{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}10  Finally, be strong in the Lord, and in the strength of his might.\r {BR}11  Put on the whole armor of God, that you may be able to stand against the wiles of the devil.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\4:4-4{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}4  You are of God, little children, and have overcome them; because greater is he who is in you than he who is in the world.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 Peter\\5:8-9{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Be sober and self-controlled. Be watchful. Your adversary the devil, walks around like a roaring lion, seeking whom he may devour.\r {BR}9  Withstand him steadfast in your faith, knowing that your brothers who are in the world are undergoing the same sufferings.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\1 John\\3:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  He who sins is of the devil, for the devil has been sinning from the beginning. To this end the Son of God was revealed, that he might destroy the works of the devil.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Claims",lessonscriptures:"Genesis\\13:17-17;Leviticus\\25:23-23;Deuteronomy\\11:24-24;2 Samuel\\22:20-20;Psalms\\2:8-8;Psalms\\107:6-7;Isaiah\\30:21-21;Matthew\\7:7-7;Hebrews\\11:8-8;Genesis\\28:15-15;Exodus\\23:20-20;Exodus\\32:34-34;Exodus\\33:14-14;Deuteronomy\\28:6-6;Psalms\\105:13-15;Psalms\\107:28-30;Psalms\\121:8-8;Psalms\\139:9-10;Isaiah\\45:2-3",id:"128",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Genesis\\13:17-17{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}17  Arise, walk through the land in its length and in its breadth; for I will give it to you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Leviticus\\25:23-23{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}23   'The land shall not be sold in perpetuity, for the land is mine; for you are strangers and live as foreigners with me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\11:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  Every place whereon the sole of your foot shall tread shall be yours: from the wilderness, and Lebanon, from the river, the river Euphrates, even to the hinder sea shall be your border.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\2 Samuel\\22:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  He also brought me out into a large place. He delivered me, because he delighted in me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\2:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Ask of me, and I will give the nations for your inheritance, the uttermost parts of the earth for your possession.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\107:6-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  Then they cried to Yahweh in their trouble, and he delivered them out of their distresses,\r {BR}7  he led them also by a straight way, that they might go to a city to live in.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\30:21-21{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}21  and when you turn to the right hand, and when you turn to the left, your ears will hear a voice behind you, saying, This is the way. Walk in it.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Matthew\\7:7-7{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}7  {I}{B}Ask, and it will be given you. Seek, and you will find. Knock, and it will be opened for you.{/B}{/I}\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Hebrews\\11:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  By faith, Abraham, when he was called, obeyed to go out to the place which he was to receive for an inheritance. He went out, not knowing where he went.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Genesis\\28:15-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}15  Behold, I am with you, and will keep you, wherever you go, and will bring you again into this land. For I will not leave you, until I have done that which I have spoken of to you.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Exodus\\23:20-20{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}20  Behold, I send an angel before you, to keep you by the way, and to bring you into the place which I have prepared.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Exodus\\32:34-34{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}34  Now go, lead the people to the place of which I have spoken to you. Behold, my angel shall go before you. Nevertheless in the day when I punish, I will punish them for their sin.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Exodus\\33:14-14{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}14  He said, My presence will go with you, and I will give you rest.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Deuteronomy\\28:6-6{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}6  You shall be blessed when you come in, and you shall be blessed when you go out.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\105:13-15{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}13  They went about from nation to nation, from one kingdom to another people.\r {BR}14  He allowed no one to do them wrong. Yes, he reproved kings for their sakes,\r {BR}15  Don't touch my anointed ones! Do my prophets no harm!\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\107:28-30{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}28  Then they cry to Yahweh in their trouble, and he brings them out of their distress.\r {BR}29  He makes the storm a calm, so that its waves are still.\r {BR}30  Then they are glad because it is calm, so he brings them to their desired haven.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\121:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  Yahweh will keep your going out and your coming in, from this time forth, and forevermore.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\139:9-10{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}9  If I take the wings of the dawn, and settle in the uttermost parts of the sea;\r {BR}10  Even there your hand will lead me, and your right hand will hold me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Isaiah\\45:2-3{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}2  I will go before you, and make the rough places smooth. I will break the doors of brass in pieces, and cut apart the bars of iron.\r {BR}3  I will give you the treasures of darkness, and hidden riches of secret places, that you may know that it is I, Yahweh, who call you by your name, even the God of Israel.\r {BR}{BR}"},{lessontitle:"Sleep",lessonscriptures:"Job\\11:18-19;Psalms\\3:5-5;Psalms\\4:8-8;Psalms\\91:5-5;Proverbs\\3:24-24",id:"129",verses:"{I}{B}WEB\\Job\\11:18-19{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}18  You shall be secure, because there is hope. Yes, you shall search, and shall take your rest in safety.\r {BR}19  Also you shall lie down, and none shall make you afraid. Yes, many shall court your favor.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\3:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  I laid myself down and slept. I awakened; for Yahweh sustains me.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\4:8-8{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}8  In peace I will both lay myself down and sleep, for you, Yahweh alone, make me live in safety.\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Psalms\\91:5-5{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}5  You shall not be afraid of the terror by night, nor of the arrow that flies by day;\r {BR}{BR}{I}{B}WEB\\Proverbs\\3:24-24{/I}{/B}{BR}{BR}24  When you lie down, you will not be afraid. Yes, you will lie down, and your sleep will be sweet.\r {BR}{BR}"}],tablename:"Life"};